title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Slice tomatoes a little over 1/4-inch thick.
Heat bacon fat in a heavy skillet.
Dip tomato slices in egg; coat with bread crumbs.
Fry over medium heat until golden brown on both sides and tender throughout when pricked with a fork.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve hot as a dinner or breakfast vegetable.
Yields 4 servings.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Heat half of oleo and add shrimp; saute until pink.
Remove from skillet.
Add remaining oleo; cook celery, mushrooms, peppers and garlic until slightly browned.
Pour off 1/4 cup of juice from tomatoes and set aside.
Add remaining tomatoes to sauteed vegetables and boil.
Stir salt, sugar, thyme, chili powder and flour into reserved juice; stir into vegetable mixture.
Over low heat, cook 3 to 5 minutes until thick.
Simmer until desired doneness, 3 to 5 minutes.
Add shrimp and heat through.
Serve over rice.

title: grandma's brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, sugar and cocoa together first.
Add eggs and oil.
Mixture will be very thick.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
This makes a square pan.
Double for 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: blueberry streusel pie
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in mixing bowl.
Beat at medium speed 5 minutes until smooth.
Fold in blueberries.
Spoon into pie shell.
Bake at 400` for 25 minutes.
Combine 3 tablespoons flour and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Stir in pecans.
Sprinkle this mixture over pie.
Bake another 15 minutes.

title: chicken in parchment
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl.
Marinate for 1 hour.
Wrap each piece of chicken in 2 1/2-inch square piece of parchment paper or aluminum foil with all loose corners tucked in.
Fry in deep fat 5 minutes.
Serves 3.

title: crock-pot dressing
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Saute onions, celery and parsley. Pour over bread.
Add seasonings and mix.
Add eggs.
Pour in crock-pot.
Cook on High for 45 minutes.
Reduce to low for 4 to 5 hours.

title: party tomatoes
directions: Peel and slice tomatoes.
Place in a shallow dish.
Mix vinegar and olive oil and pour over sliced tomatoes.
Sprinkle salt, pepper and basil on top.
Let marinate in refrigerator for several hours.
Either serve cold or sprinkle Parmesan cheese and bread crumbs on top and broil!!!

title: creole shrimp
directions: Mix all together.
Last, add 1 pound or more fresh shrimp. Place in hot oven and heat.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix 1 stick margarine and cracker crumbs well.
Put in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cream powdered sugar, margarine and eggs no less than 15 minutes.
Spread over crumbs.
Slice bananas over creamed mixture.
Cover with pineapple.
Spread whipped topping on top.
Sprinkle with nuts and cherries (optional).
Refrigerate overnight.

title: coffee glazed pecans
directions: In large skillet, combine pecans, sugar, water, coffee and cinnamon.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Stir constantly. Boil 3 minutes; stir constantly.
Spread on waxed paper.

title: chocolate refresher bars
directions: Combine dates, brown sugar, butter and water in saucepan. Cook until dates are soft.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Add eggs and beat.
Add dry ingredients with orange juice and milk; blend well. Add nuts.
Spread in 15 x 10-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: In a large skillet saute cut up chicken breast chunks in oil until cooked.
Wash broccoli and steam cook.
Drain broccoli and add salt and pepper over top.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Put the coconut and chopped nuts in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the cake mix.
Pour batter over nuts and coconut.
Mix oleo, cream cheese and confectioners sugar.
Spoon this over cake batter. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: snow ice cream
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar and continue beating until light and fluffy.
Add cream and mix well.
Add clean snow, beating well until thick as desired.
Add vanilla and mix.
May be kept in freezer or eaten right away.

title: banana chocolate chip muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Prepare muffin pan (makes 12 medium muffins).
In large bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add egg, banana and baking soda and combine well.
In smaller bowl, combine flour, salt and nutmeg.
Fold wet and dry ingredients together in large bowl until well blended.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Spoon into muffin pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool on rack.

title: blueberries 'n cheese squares
directions: Roll Keebler crackers to fine crumbs.
In an 11 3/4 x 7 1/2-inch baking dish, combine crumbs and butter or margarine, mixing well.
Reserve 1/2 cup crumb mixture for topping.
Press remaining crumbs in bottom of dish.
Chill while preparing cream cheese.
Blend cream cheese, sugar and milk until smooth.
Spread evenly over crumb layer.
Spread pie filling over cheese and chill while preparing cream.
Using chilled beaters and bowl, whip cream and sugar until stiff.
Spread evenly over blueberries.
Sprinkle with reserved crumbs.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: uncle bill's turnip appetizer
directions: Saute 2 cups of chopped onion in 1/2 cup oil until brown. Combine turnips, 1/2 cup oil, salt, pepper and 1/4 cup finely grated onion.
Add the sauteed onion and mix well.

title: beef and onion dip
directions: Thin cream cheese with mayonnaise, Worcestershire sauce and garlic salt.
Dice onion tops and beef.
Add to mixture.
Serve at room temperature.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, vanilla and salt together.
Add condensed milk and whipping cream, mixing well.
Pour into ice cream maker. Then add enough milk to come up to the fill line.
Churn well and freeze.

title: ginger's brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a large bowl, beat eggs well. Add to the eggs the oil and vanilla. Gradually add flour, sugar and cocoa.
Pour into an 8 x 8 pan. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes until set.

title: cheese appetizer cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients. Chill dough 1 hour. Shape into 1-inch balls. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: old fashioned vinegar pie
directions: Cream together butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add vinegar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until knife blade comes out clean when inserted.
Cool on rack.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Fry bacon and drain.
Cut in small pieces. Add broccoli, cheese and onions.
Toss with dressing and let stand for 2 hours.

title: baked parmesan chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine bread crumbs, cheese and seasonings in shallow dish.
Dip chicken in crumb mixture.
Coat both sides.
Melt margarine in baking dish in oven.
Add chicken, turning to coat both sides with margarine.
Bake uncovered for 1 hour.

title: banana stue
directions: Combine and mix well.
Freeze in small plastic cups for 24 hours.
Serve with a spoon.

title: chocolate pudding
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and cocoa. Add a little milk to moisten. Scald milk.
Add to cocoa mixture. Place in double boiler. Stir constantly until thick.
Add vanilla and butter. Stir until blended. Serve plain, with whipped cream or warm over vanilla ice cream.

title: cinnamon raisin biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease cookie sheet.
In a large bowl, combine dry ingredients.
Cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in raisins.
Add milk and egg, mixing only until flour is moistened.
Turn dough out onto cookie sheet.
Pat dough into 7-inch circle.
Cut into 8 wedges; do not separate. Brush top with egg (optional).
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes, or until light golden brown.
Break wedges apart to serve.
Makes 8.

title: creamy jello mold
directions: Spray your mold lightly with Pam to ensure ease of removal. Cream together the Cool Whip and the cream cheese until smooth. Drain the pineapple, reserving juice for use in the Jell-O.
Make Jell-O as directed on the boxes (2 large boxes) using only 3/4 amount of water and the reserved juice as part of the cold liquid. Reserve 1 cup Jell-O.
Quick chill remaining Jell-O until almost set, stirring occasionally.

title: homemade chicken pot pie
directions: Cook chicken and debone.
Mix mushroom soup and celery soup in casserole dish.
Cut up chicken and add to mixture.
Add garden peas, cooked potatoes and cooked carrots.
Add enough chicken broth to make soupy.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix self-rising flour and mayonnaise.
Add enough milk to make soupy.
Pour over casserole.
Bake at 325° until brown on top and hot and bubbly. Tastes great!

title: dilly bread
directions: Heat to lukewarm the cottage cheese with 1 tablespoon squeeze oleo.
Dissolve dry yeast in warm water.
Then add egg, dill seed, onion, salt, sugar, baking soda and squeeze oleo and mix. Add next the flour.
Mix until able to knead on floured board. Knead 10 minutes, sprinkling flour on board if necessary until velvety smooth.
Put in a greased bowl, turning upside down to butter the underside.
Cover with towel and let rise in warm place until double in bulk, about 1 1/4 hours.
Punch down and shape into 2 loaves (8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch) bread pans and let rise again until double in size.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: enchiladas
directions: Mix chili, onion and sauce.
Let shells thaw.
Fill shells with chili mixture and roll up.
Place in 9 1/2 x 13-inch baking dish.
Put cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until cheese bubbles.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook the chicken and put in pan. Boil the chicken soup with the chicken broth and pour over chicken.
Mix the butter, pepper, flour, buttermilk and salt. Spoon over the chicken. Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: creole okra
directions: Saute okra, onions and green pepper in oleo 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cook over low heat 10 to 15 minutes.

title: fresh fruit cobbler
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to a boil and boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart baking dish and dot with butter.
Sift together the flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening with pastry blender or 2 knives until mixture looks like meal.
Stir in milk.
Drop by spoonfuls onto hot fruit or berries.
Bake until golden brown at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve warm with juice and cream. Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken corn soup
directions: Put
cut-up
chicken
and onion into the water and cook slowly until
tender; add salt.
Remove chicken; cut the meat into small (1-inch) pieces and return to broth, together with corn, which has been cut from the cob, celery and seasonings. Continue to simmer.

title: moravian white christmas cookies
directions: Sift flour and baking soda together; set aside.
Cream butter until softened.
Add sugar gradually, creaming until fluffy.
Add the eggs in thirds, beating well after each addition.
Alternately add dry ingredients in fourths and cream in thirds, mixing until well blended after each addition.
Stir in the water.
Chill dough for several hours.
Using a small amount of dough at a time, roll out about 1/8-inch thick on floured surface and cut with fancy cookie cutters.
Transfer to cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Combine melted butter with other ingredients.
Bake in a 9 x 12-inch pan for 30 minutes at 400°.

title: mom's best peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream peanut butter and butter.
Mix in sugars thoroughly. Beat in egg and vanilla. Sift dry ingredients, then mix slowly in creamed mixture. Chill 1/2 hour.
Roll into small balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten with fork.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: aloha cheesecake
directions: Combine crumbs and margarine; press onto bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Combine cream cheese, sugar and milk, mixing at medium speed on electric mixer until well blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Stir in nuts; pour over crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Loosen cake from rim of pan; cool before removing rim of pan.
Chill.
Before serving, top with fruit.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Cook all
ingredients in double boiler, except vanilla, until thick.
Add
vanilla after it thickens.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top
with
meringue.
Brown
meringue
in oven for about 10 to 15 minutes at 275°.

title: hot chocolate for breakfast
directions: Mix well and pour into boiling water.
Stir until thick.
Cover biscuits with mixture and top with butter.

title: texas caviar
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix lightly.
Cover; chill at least 2 hours or up to 24 hours, stirring occasionally.
Drain.
Makes 7 cups.
Serve as an appetizer with sturdy chips or in lettuce cups as an accompaniment salad.

title: frozen sliced sweet dill pickles
directions: Mix prepared cucumbers, onions, salt and water in a 2-quart bowl (not aluminum) and let stand about 2 hours.
Drain, but do not rinse.
Return cucumbers, etc. to bowl and add sugar, vinegar and dill.
Let stand, stirring from time to time, until sugar has dissolved completely and liquid covers vegetables.
Pack in glass or plastic freezer containers (leave 1-inch headspace).
Seal tightly and freeze.
Makes about 4 cups.

title: spicy pineapple sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients well. Let stand overnight in refrigerator. Serve with pork or other meats. Keep refrigerated.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into
9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: quesadilla amigos(guatemala)
directions: In a bowl, mix mayonnaise, cilantro and comino. Spread evenly over 4 tortillas. Sprinkle with cheese and olives. Place tortilla on top. Heat a 12 inch non-stick skillet to medium heat. Lightly spray with cooking spray. Cook quesadillas for 2-3 minutes or until starting to brown, turn over and cook 1-2 more minutes until lightly browned. Cut into small wedges and serve with salsa if desired.

title: mom's orange balls
directions: Mix wafers, butter, orange juice and powdered sugar; roll into small balls.
Makes about 100.

title: blueberry sally lunn(makes 1 loaf)
directions: In a large bowl, mix 1 1/2 cups flour, 2/3 cup sugar, salt and undissolved yeast.
Heat milk, water and butter until liquids are very warm (120° to 130°).
Butter does not need to melt. Gradually add to dry ingredients; beat 2 minutes at medium speed of electric mixer, scraping bowl occasionally.

Add eggs and 1 cup flour; beat at high speed 2 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally. With spoon, stir in enough additional flour to make soft batter. Cover; let rise in warm, draft free place, until doubled in size, about 45 minutes.
(For Fleischmann's RapidRise yeast, cover batter.
Let rest 10 minutes.
Proceed with recipe.)

title: lite fruit mix
directions: Prepare pudding mix as directed.
Don't drain fruit.
Mix all the fruit together with the box of vanilla instant pudding mix. Place in refrigerator.

title: yum-yum casserole
directions: A heartful of thankfulness,

title: no bake cookies
directions: Bring butter, sugar, milk and cocoa to a boil for two minutes or longer. Remove from heat and add peanut butter, vanilla and oats. Mix well.
Drop from teaspoon onto waxed paper and chill thoroughly.

title: chicken piccata
directions: On a plate, mix the flour, salt and pepper. Coat the chicken on both sides with flour mixture.
Shake off excess.

title: feather light biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in water. Add buttermilk and mix. In a separate bowl, combine flour and sugar. Cut in shortening; add buttermilk mixture. Roll out and cut into biscuits. Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pecan sandies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add water and vanilla; mix well.
Add flour and nuts; chill for several hours.
Shape in balls or crescents; place on ungreased cookie sheet in slow oven (325°) for about 20 minutes.
Cool slightly; roll in powdered sugar.

title: spinach salad
directions: Tear or cup spinach into pieces.
Cut tops off of onions and add to spinach.
Chop onions and add also add water chestnuts and bacon.
Mix dressing in the order as listed in a blender.
Pour over salad, toss to coat.
Serve.

title: white fruit cake - best on earth
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add well beaten eggs and blend chopped nuts and fruit in medium-size pieces.
Mix with part of flour.
Sift remaining flour and baking powder together.
Fold in eggs and butter and mix.
Add flavoring mix.
Add fruit and nuts; mix well.
Pour into greased paper lined tube pan.
Place in cold oven and bake at 250° for 3 hours.
Cool in pan.

title: pumpkin raisin tart
directions: Let pie crust come to room temperature according to package directions.
Preheat a baking sheet in a 375° oven.

title: jay's chili
directions: In Dutch oven, saute first four ingredients in hot oil until tender.
Add meat, 1 pound at a time.
When meat is cooked, drain. Add remaining ingredients, stirring after each addition.
Simmer 2 1/2 to 3 hours, stirring frequently.
Adjust seasoning to taste. Goes great with cornbread.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, Crisco and white sugar.
Add unbeaten eggs. Add plain flour and sweet milk.
Add vanilla and baking powder. Use 2 layers of wax paper in tube pan.
Put cake in cold oven. Bake at 340° to 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Cool in pan.

title: hot dog bites
directions: Cut each hot dog into 4 pieces.
Cut bacon slices in half. Wrap each hot dog piece with a half slice of bacon; fasten with toothpick.
Put in crock-pot on lowest temperature.
Cover with brown sugar and let go for 3 to 4 hours.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Reserve broth to cook spaghetti in. In a large skillet, mix together the bell pepper, onion, soups, pimentos and garlic, adding a little water, if needed.
Simmer until vegetables are tender.
Pour sauce in large casserole dish. Add chicken and cooked spaghetti.
Cover top with grated cheese and place in oven until the cheese is melted.

title: marty's lobster stew
directions: Combine veggies in saucepan with water; boil until veggies are 2/3 cooked.
Drain excess water.
Add meat, milk and cream to saucepan; simmer for 15 minutes.
Add cornstarch to thicken. Season to taste.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Place zucchini, onions and salt in a large bowl; mix well and cover.
Refrigerate overnight.
The next day, place mixture in a fine strainer.
Drain well, rinse under cold water and drain again for 1 hour.
Place mixture in a heavy pot with remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil and simmer, stirring occasionally, 30 minutes.
Cool completely and store, covered, in the refrigerator for up to 4 weeks.
Or sterilize 3 or 4 pint-size canning jars in boiling water for 10 minutes.
Carefully remove jars with tongs.
Let rest until relish comes to room temperature. Store in cool, dark place for up to 6 months.

title: dirt cake
directions: Cream together the cream cheese and butter.
Add milk and pudding, mixing slowly and thoroughly.
Add vanilla.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Alternate layers of crumbs and pudding mixture, beginning with crumbs.
End with layer of cookies approximately 1/2-inch thick.

title: ham and broccoli casserole
directions: Wash and cut up broccoli.
Partially boil in boiling water in which salt has been added.
Drain.
Layer broccoli and ham on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle cheese over all. Mix other ingredients in another bowl and pour over top.
Bake until done, about 45 to 55 minutes.
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: spoon bread
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Bake in well-greased skillet or pan for 35 minutes in 400° oven.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Drain fruit.
Add to cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Just before serving, add dry Jell-O and stir to mix.

title: cherry tarts
directions: You will need 36 foil baking cups.

title: vegetable-caroni
directions: Cook one cup macaroni until tender.
Saute the onion in butter.
Add tomato juice and thicken slightly.
Combine drained macaroni with the sauce and diced vegetables.
Place in a baking dish and bake until celery and carrots are done.

title: baked corn
directions: Throw everything in blender.
Fill blender with milk (evaporated milk works well).
Blend everything until thoroughly mixed.
Pour mixture into a buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour or until knife comes out clean.

title: strawberry pineapple-ade punch
directions: In large pitcher or punch bowl, stir together the lemonade, pineapple and daiquiri concentrates.
Add cold water, stirring gently.
Add ice cubes or ice ring, then float berry slices atop. Serves 15 (4 ounce) servings.

title: allyn's bacon wrapped pork tenderloin
directions: Wrap pork tenderloin in bacon. Combine next 6 ingredients and pour over bacon wrapped pork tenderloin. Marinate 2 hours to overnight (turning in marinade occasionally). Remove wrapped tenderloin from marinade (reserve marinade). Roast/bake in a 300° oven or grill on barbecue until tenderloin registers done on a meat thermometer. (Varies by cut/size of tenderloin and/or preference of doneness, i.e., medium-rare, etc.)

title: marinade sauce
directions: Mix together.
Great for steak or fish (skin up).
Marinate for 4 hours.

title: penthouse casserole
directions: Prepare Kraft dinner as directed on package.
Add soup, tuna fish, mushrooms, milk and onion; mix well.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole.

title: green chili stew
directions: Add all ingredients and cook in crock-pot overnight.

title: nan's banana pudding
directions: Mix milk, water and pudding mix.
Beat well, chill 5 minutes. Fold in Cool Whip.
Place a layer of wafers, bananas and mixture. Chill and serve.

title: crab casserole
directions: Melt
butter,
add flour and blend.
Gradually add milk and seasonings.
Cook over low heat until thickened.
Pour hot mixture into egg
yolk
and
beat.	Cook
mixture
minutes, remove from heat.
Add sherry, bread crumbs, crab, parsley and onion; mix gently.
Pour
into
1 1/2-quart casserole and bake for 20 to 25 minutes in 350° oven.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Melt butter and brown sugar.
Cook over low heat for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add milk; cook and stir to boil. Cool for 10 minutes; add confectioners sugar until of spreading consistency.
Beat well.
Spread on cooled cake.

title: bean soup
directions: Cook all day on low heat.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: In food processor beat eggs on high for 3 minutes.
Gradually add sugar, canned pumpkin and lemon juice.

title: peppermint ice cream pie
directions: Spray spring-form pan with cooking spray.
Remove filling from Oreos and crush cookies, also crush the peppermints.
Place half of the cookie crumbs in bottom of pan, then a layer of ice cream. Sprinkle peppermint on ice cream.
Repeat with crumbs and ice cream.
Cover with wax paper and pack in pan.
Uncover and sprinkle with remaining peppermints and freeze at least 2 hours.

title: apple cranberry crisp
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
For topping, combine oats, brown sugar, flour and cinnamon.
Mix well. Stir in melted margarine and water. Mix until crumbly.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Stir together first three ingredients, then add egg yolks. Stir milk into mixture a little at a time.
Cook on top of stove until thickened.

title: 7-n-one
directions: In a 5-quart pan, greased, place items in order. Cover.
Bake at 350° for 3 hours. Serve 6 to 8 people.

title: golden apple cake
directions: Stir together flour and allspice.
Combine oil, sugar, egg and vanilla; mix well.
Add flour mixture and oats.
Stir in apples and nuts; spread in greased and floured 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until done by toothpick test.

title: cheezy potatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients (hash browns may still be frozen, but they handle easier thawed).
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine 2 cups crushed corn flakes and 1/4 cup melted oleo.
Pour over vegetables in pan and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: birthday pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add flour; beat.
Put in a well-greased and floured tube cake pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: flemish beef and beer
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Saute onions and garlic until transparent, then put in small bowl.
Trim meat and cut into cubes.
Dredge meat in flour, salt and pepper and brown meat. Place meat into glass baking dish and spread veggies over top. Sprinkle with parsley, nutmeg, thyme and bay leaf.
Pour beer and sprinkle brown sugar over all.
Can use wild game meat, works well.
Cover and bake for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, onion, crushed pineapple and salt. Form a ball and roll in pecans.

title: vanilla caramels
directions: Combine sugar, 1 cup of half-and-half, syrup and butter.
Cook over medium heat for 7 to 8 minutes until mixture comes to a full boil.
Add remaining half-and-half and cook at a slow boil until mixture reaches 245 degrees on a candy thermometer (this takes a while).
Add vanilla.
Pour into a greased 8 or 9 inch square pan and let cool.
Cut into pieces.

title: oven stew
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large Dutch oven with tight cover.
Cook in a 300° oven, covered, for 4 hours.
Do not uncover while cooking.
Or cook in covered crock-pot for 6 to 8 hours. Makes 6 servings.

title: potato nacho cheese soup
directions: Cook potatoes, salts and onions in water until soft.
Add all ingredient to water mixture.
Heat until hot.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Clean cranberries and put orange and cranberries through food chopper.
Use orange rind; add pineapple, sugar and pecans.
Use juice from pineapple and cranberries to dissolve gelatin, adding water if necessary to bring to 2 cups.
Mix gelatin and cranberry mixture.
Serves 8.

title: chicken paprika
directions: Saute chopped onion in oil; lift brown onion out of pan.
Roll cut up chicken in flour, salt, pepper and paprika; brown well in the oil.
Put fried onion back in pan.
Add 1 1/2 cups water. Cover; let simmer until tender, about 45 minutes.
Add cooked noodles with a dash of paprika 5 minutes before serving (optional).
Add 1/2 pint sour cream 10 minutes before serving.

title: carrot cranberry casserole
directions: Mix all together and spoon into Pam sprayed casserole dish. Cover and cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Add eggs and oil.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, bananas and 1 cup nuts.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pine bark
directions: Line a large cookie sheet with foil and place saltines, sides touching, in rectangle shape on foil.
Turn sides of foil up close to crackers.
Melt butter; mix with sugar and boil 3 minutes (stir constantly or it will burn).
Pour sugar and butter over crackers to cover well.
Place in a 400° preheated oven for 7 minutes. Remove and pour chocolate morsels over hot crackers.
When they melt, spread over crackers well.
Chill in refrigerator until firm.
Break into pieces.

title: sandwich spread
directions: Michigan State University now recommends that we hot pack tomatoes for canning and not do them by cold pack.
Also, processing time for tomatoes, tomato juice, applesauce and fruit purees have been changed.
Use the times given to ensure a safe home canned product.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and pack into an ungreased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: sausage balls #2
directions: Grate cheese and mix with sausage and Bisquick.
You will have to use your fingers to work together until well blended.
Roll into small balls and bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: dilled cucumbers
directions: Cut cucumber lengthwise in half.
Seed and cut into thin slices.
Mix cucumber and remaining ingredients in 1 1/2-quart saucepan.
Cook over high heat 1 to 2 minutes, stirring frequently, until cucumber is crisp-tender.

title: impossible pie
directions: Place all ingredients in blender and blend.
Pour into pie plate and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: easy baked pork chops
directions: Place pork chops in baking pan.
Put brown sugar on them thickly, then pour chili sauce or catsup over the top.
Place 2 slices of lemon on each pork chop.
Bake at 360° for 1 hour.

title: good puddin'
directions: First layer: Mix flour, pecans, and melted butter and pat in bottom of pyrex dish. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Let cool.

title: mississippi cornbread
directions: Preheat oven
to
Combine eggs, oil, sour cream, corn and onions
in
meal; mix well.
Pour into greased baking dish or muffin pan.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: sauerbraten
directions: Three or four days before serving Sauerbraten, select roast. Rinse meat and pat dry with paper towel.
Rub meat thoroughly with salt and pepper.
Place in a deep earthenware or glass bowl. Combine bay leaves, peppercorns, cloves, onions, carrots, celery, wine vinegar, water, salt, pepper and sugar.
Pour over roast. Add more water, if necessary, to cover roast.
Cover bowl and refrigerate 3 to 4 days.
Turn occasionally.
Stir marinade over and around roast.
On the day to be cooked, drain meat, saving marinade.
Brown meat quickly on all sides in Dutch oven or heavy kettle for about 20 minutes.
Add 1 1/2 to 2 cups marinade to roast, cover kettle and cook 3 1/2 hours or until meat is thoroughly tender.
Add more marinade from time to time, if necessary.
For 2 cups of gravy, melt 1/4 cup sugar in greased skillet, stirring until brown.
Stir in 2 1/2 cups hot marinade and 1/4 cup water.
Add gingersnaps, stirring until mixture thickens.
Add sour cream and salt to taste.
Pour small amount of hot gravy over sliced meat and serve remaining gravy in bowl. Serves 6 or more.

title: fried eggplant
directions: Boil eggplant in water until "mush".
Drain and set aside to cool.
Place in bowl; add 1 egg and mix well.
Add enough flour to "hold together".
Drop by spoonful of batter in hot grease.
Fry until brown.
Drain and serve.

title: mexi-spiced nuts
directions: Place pecans and peanuts in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
In a small bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over nuts and toss to coat.
Bake in 325° oven for 30 minutes, stirring once every 10 minutes.
Cool and package in a food container to help keep it fresh.
A quick and easy gift! Makes four cups.

title: stretchable stew
directions: Place 3 small bacon pieces on the bottom of each hamburger patty.
Arrange patties bacon side down in a tight fitting lid. Top each patty with a thick onion slice.
Arrange carrots and potatoes around the patties.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Cook over high heat until bacon begins to sizzle.
Then cover and simmer over low heat for 1 hour or until meat is done. Serves 4.

title: scrambled eggs delight
directions: Saute green onions in butter, margarine or olive oil on medium heat until tender (approximately 5 minutes).
Beat eggs moderately.
Add cottage cheese.
Mix.
Add eggs and cottage cheese to sauteed onions.
Stir and cook on low or medium heat until done (approximately 5 minutes).

title: shauna's wild rice bake
directions: Rinse rice 1 to 2 minutes.
Combine rice and broth.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 40 minutes.
In a skillet cook mushrooms, celery, onion and butter for 5 minutes.
Stir in flour, nutmeg and coriander.
Add sour cream and milk.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Cook 1 more minute.
Add to undrained rice.
Put in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes and stir before serving.

title: baked corn pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 1 1/2-quart baking dish with oil.
Combine sugar and cornstarch in bowl.
Add eggs, corn and milk.
Mix well. Turn into baking dish.
Dot with butter.
Bake 1 hour, approximately.

title: angel food cake
directions: Egg whites have
to
be
room
temperature at least one hour. Preheat oven
Sift powdered sugar and flour 3 times.
In crock
or
glass
bowl,
beat
egg whites, cream of tartar, vanilla, almond flavor and salt with electric mixer on medium speed, until soft peak forms.
Gradually add one cup of sugar, 2 tablespoons
at
a
time, beating on high speed until stiff peaks form.
Sift
cup
of flour at a time over the beaten whites, just
lightly fold flour with hand beater.
Put in 10-inch tube pan
and
bake
to
45 minutes. When done, invert on a bottle.

title: pastry crust
directions: In large bowl, cut in flour and shortening with a pastry blender or two knives crossed.
Slowly add water as you are cutting in shortening to form a soft ball.
Be sure to cut shortening in well.
Roll out to 1/8-inch thickness and place in 8 or 9-inch pie pan.
Makes 1 double crust pie or 2 (8 or 9-inch) pies.
Flute edges and bake at 425° for 15 minutes and reduce heat to 350° for remainder of time.
Bake until crust is a golden brown.
Brush pastry with milk to give a golden color.

title: hot dogs and rice
directions: Melt
butter
in
skillet; add hot dogs, stirring until almost cooked.
Add onion and celery; stir until onion becomes clear. Stir
in
rice.
Add tomatoes and mix well.
Cover and simmer about 20 minutes.

title: "ritz-chicken casserole"
directions: Mix cracker crumbs with melted butter. (Reserve 1 cup for topping.) Line bottom of long casserole dish with crumbs. Mix remaining ingredients and spread over crumbs in dish. Top with reserved crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, until bubbly.

title: red devil cupcakes
directions: Cream shortening with sugar until very light.
Add egg. Alternate dry ingredients with liquids.
At very last, add hot water all at once.
Bake at 350° for 19 minutes.
A caramel icing is good with this.

title: la pari(sauce)
directions: Serve with chicken or vegetables.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix and bake at 375° until brown.

title: carrot salad
directions: Cook approximately 8 cups of carrots.
Cool and drain.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over carrots.
These will keep a long time in the refrigerator.
You can cook and add more carrots, onion and pepper, if you need more salad before the liquid is all used.

title: party mix
directions: Mix altogether.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: elegant crabmeat spread
directions: Heat undiluted soup.
Mix gelatin with 3 tablespoons water. Combine with soup.
Gradually mix with cream cheese.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill in mold or serving dish.
Serve with assorted crackers and/or raw vegetable cuts.
(Can mold into 2 cottage cheese size cups.)
Serves small crowd deliciously.

title: hot chicken dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and heat in a small crock-pot.
Serve warm with crackers or nacho chips.

title: dill pickles
directions: Sterilize jars.
Wash
cukes;
cut into spears and fill jars. Mix 2
quarts
water (boiled and cooled), 1/2 cup salt, 1/4 teaspoon cream
of	tartar	and 1 pint vinegar.
Pour over cukes. Add an 8-inch
stalk of dill to 1 quart of cukes.
Can be made in open crock.
Never fails, an excellent method.

title: strawberries
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and chill.
Shape into strawberry shapes.
Roll sides in red granulated sugar and dip tops in green sugar.
Use almond slivers (dyed green in food coloring) for the stems.
Let set 24 hours.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook elbows according to box directions.
In saucepan, put American cheese together with milk and heat until blended and creamy. Stir constantly.
Pour over noodles and stir with a large spoon.

title: beer rolls
directions: Mix and pour into greased muffin tin.
Bake 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix well.
Store in refrigerator.
Use 2 teaspoons of dry mixture for each cup of hot water.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Mix together powdered sugar, peanut butter, corn syrup, oleo and chopped peanuts
and
press into buttered cake pan or paper liners in small
muffin
tins.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin together and pour over peanut butter mixture.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix margarine, oil, sugar, powdered sugar and beaten eggs. Add the flour, soda, cream of tartar and vanilla.
Mix and roll into balls.
Roll balls in granulated sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with bottom of a cup or glass.
Bake at 350° until light brown on edges.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer in order given.

title: broccoli cheese dip
directions: Melt margarine and saute mushrooms and onion.
Stir in mushroom soup. Add cheese and stir until melted.
Blend in broccoli and almonds.

title: german chocolate
directions: Mix together and refrigerate overnight.
Roll in balls.
Dip in bark white chocolate (melted).
Drop onto waxed paper.

title: brian's santa fe chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients (except chicken) and mold to the bottom of a baking pan.
Place chicken on
top.
Sprinkle Season-All on chicken.
Cook 45 minutes at 375° until chicken is golden brown.

title: brown rice
directions: Brown rice in margarine.
Melt bouillon cubes in boiling water and add to rice.
Add mushroom steak sauce.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in covered casserole.

title: cheesy potato bake
directions: Mix altogether.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: corn bread and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Mix all ingredients except cheese. Pour half of mixture in a greased
heavy skillet at least 2 inches deep. Spread on cheese and pour remaining mixture on top. Bake for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: kansas dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies and melt butter.
Add 2/3 of cookie crumbs to melted butter.
Beat cream cheese and sugar, then add Cool Whip. Mix mil and pudding.
Add to cream cheese.
Pour onto crust. Sprinkle remaining crumbs on top.
Refrigerate until ready to eat.

title: cinnamon "s's"
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Add eggs; beat until fluffy.
Stir in flour and baking powder to make pliable dough. Roll into 3-inch ropes and shape into "S's".
Roll in cinnamon and sugar mixture. Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until firm but not brown.

title: baked potato soup
directions: Bake potatoes until tender. Cool, peel and chop into small pieces. Melt butter in large pan and stir in flour. Slowly whisk in milk and over medium heat, bring to almost boiling. Add potatoes, onion and bacon. Stir in cheese and sour cream. Heat through until cheese is melted and soup is hot.

title: cheese mexican cornbread
directions: Mix flour and cornmeal.
Mix remaining ingredients and add to dry mixture.
Mix together and pour into greased muffin tins. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: apple rings
directions: Roll out dough 1/4-inch thick.
Spread 2 cups chopped raw apples over dough and roll up like a jelly roll.
Cut into 1-inch rounds and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour this sauce over all and bake in a 400° oven for 40 minutes.

title: pain perdu (french toast)(means "lost bread" in new orleans)
directions: In a flat dish, combine eggs, salt and milk.
Soak bread in mixture, turning once to
moisten both sides.
On griddle or in a large skillet, melt butter or margarine on medium heat.
Brown bread slices on both sides.
Serve sprinkled with confectioners sugar sprinkled on top, jam, jelly or syrup (optional).
I add cinnamon to mix.

title: swedish poppy seed cake
directions: Put all ingredients in mixing bowl; mix for 3 minutes.
Pour into a greased 12-cup Bundt pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: white clam sauce with linguine
directions: This is simple and takes so little time you can make it while the linguine cooks (about 10 minutes).
Heat the olive oil and saute the garlic and onion until gold, not brown.
Add the parsley, the pepper and the juice of the clams.

title: shrimp etouffee
directions: Saute onion, celery and bell pepper in oleo until onion is tender.
Add soup and water.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.
Add seasonings and shrimp; simmer 10 minutes more.
Add green onion tops and simmer 5 more minutes.
Serve over rice.
Will serve 4 to 6 people.

title: just for kids: buckey's bran muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease muffin tin.
Combine sifted flour, baking powder and salt.
In separate mixing bowl, cream the shortening and sugar.
Add egg and beat well.
Stir in milk and bran.
Sift in the flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir, just until moistened.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cubanos(cuban sandwiches)
directions: Cut rolls open and spread top with mayo.
Layer ham, cheese, pork and top with dill pickles.
Close sandwiches.
Spread top and bottom of rolls with margarine.
Heat griddle to 300°.
Grill sandwiches on both sides until brown.
Cut in half.
Serve and enjoy!
Yields 4 sandwiches.

title: braised string beans(greek:  fassoulakia yahni)
directions: Saute onion and garlic in olive oil.
Add tomato paste and fresh tomato.
Simmer until sauce is slightly thickened.
Add string beans, seasoning and enough water to cover.
Cook until beans are tender.

title: temptation spice cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, nutmeg, cloves and cinnamon.
Add next 3 ingredients and beat 2 minutes, starting slowly and scraping sides of bowl.
Increase speed as needed.
Add eggs and beat 2 minutes more.
Batter will fit 2 (9-inch) layer pans or tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until tester is clean.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Peel, slice and cook potatoes.
(Potatoes will not turn dark if you slice them in salted water.)
Mash potatoes with electric beaters (don't scrape beater off as these have strings from the potatoes on them). Mix rest of ingredients into potatoes and pour into a long baking dish.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Place cooked, drained broccoli in 2-quart baking dish.
Mix well the mayonnaise and soup; pour over broccoli.
Melt margarine and toss bread cubes until covered.
Pour over casserole and bake at 350° until bubbly and cubes are brown.

title: cream cheese glaze
directions: In a small bowl beat cream cheese, powdered sugar, milk and vanilla until smooth.

title: bulkogi (korea)
directions: Slice steak across the grain in very thin slices, no more than 1/4-inch thick.
In a small bowl, combine rest of ingredients, except scallions, to make marinade; mix well.
Pour marinade over steak, coating well.
Let stand in refrigerator, covered, about 2 hours.

title: onion rings
directions: Deep fry in oil until golden brown.
Salt to desired taste. Store briefly in 350° oven.

title: lone star ribs and barbecue sauce
directions: Season both sides
of ribs with mixture of ingredients. Place ribs on grill
or any type of covered smoker or barbecue pit. Keep away from
direct
heat so the smoke does the cooking.
Cook very slowly
for
to
2 hours or until meat comes away from
the bone.
During the final 15 minutes, baste both sides of the
meat with barbecue sauce (in sauce section of this cookbook). Cut ribs into serving portions.
Serves 4.

title: no crust egg custard
directions: Combine first six ingredients and pour into buttered pie pan. Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: orange raisin cake
directions: In a large bowl, cream the butter with sugar.
Add eggs.
Beat. Place orange juice in a cup.
Fill with milk until it measures 1 cup.
Add milk, orange juice and rind to mixture.
Beat until smooth.
In another bowl, blend flour, baking powder, salt and raisins.
Add gradually to butter mixture.
Beat until smooth. Pour in a greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar (optional).

title: joe terry's moist oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
May add raisins or nuts, if desired.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: fried chicken in oven
directions: Melt margarine in Pyrex dish.
Salt and pepper chicken.
Roll chicken in Bisquick.
Place in dish.
Leave uncovered.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: creamy cheese tacos
directions: Saute the onion and garlic in margarine, then add the chilies, Ro-Tel, Milnot and Velveeta.
Cook on low heat until cheese is melted.
Prepare ground beef and taco seasoning package according to package directions; set aside.

title: strawberry pie(shoney's)
directions: Bake pie crust.
Cook 7-Up, red food coloring, cornstarch and sugar until it forms a thick syrup.
Cool this mixture.
Pour over strawberries that have been placed in the baked crust.
Chill and add whipped cream or Cool Whip on top.

title: aunt jeanettes taco salad
directions: Cut up lettuce and tomatoes.
Cook hamburger and drain.
Let it cool, then add to lettuce and cheese.
Just before serving, add Catalina dressing and crushed Doritos, then eat it.

title: diet eclair
directions: In a 9 x 13

glass pan, place a layer of graham crackers along the bottom of the pan. In a mixing bowl, beat the milk and dry pudding until smooth. Add the cool-whip to the pudding and milk and beat. Spread the pudding mixture over the graham crackers. Place another layer of graham crackers on top. Take lid off frosting and melt in microwave for 1 minute. Pour over to top and chill.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare pastry.
In a large bowl, beat eggs slightly.
Add remaining ingredients and blend well.
Pour into pastry lined pie pan.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 350° and bake 45 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool.
Serve plain or with whipped cream.

title: orange julius
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender container.
Cover and blend until smooth, about 30 seconds.
Serve immediately.

title: amish molasses cookies
directions: Cream first four ingredients.
Dissolve soda in hot water. Add to creamy mixture.
Add vanilla and flour.
Make small balls and bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° for 8-10 minutes. I use "Pampered Chef" large scoop and get 10 dozen large cookies.
Put grease on bottom of glass, dip in bowl of sugar and flatten cookies on cookie sheet before you bake them.
Don't overbake. Great cookies.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat butter at medium speed; gradually add sugars, mixing well.
Add egg and vanilla, mixing well.
Combine flour with soda, salt and spices.
Gradually add to butter mixture.
Stir in oats and raisins.
Drop by tablespoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool slightly in pan and remove to wire rack to continue cooling.
(Add nuts with raisins.)

title: peanut butter frosting
directions: Stir together in saucepan over low heat the milk, peanut butter and butter until well blended. Remove from heat. Add salt and vanilla. Gradually stir in sugar; beat until smooth and creamy. If too stiff to spread easily, beat in few drops of milk. Frosts tops and sides of two 8 or 9-inch layers.

title: rafferty's potato soup
directions: In large saucepan, cook potatoes and onion in enough water to cover on medium heat until tender. Add cubes of cream cheese. Remove from heat and stir until cheese is melted. Add soups, butter and spices. Serve hot. Top with shredded cheese, bacon bits or green onion.

title: family meat loaf
directions: In bowl mix thoroughly 1/2 cup soup, beef, bread crumbs, onion, Worcestershire, egg and pepper.
Shape into 8 x 4 loaf and place in a baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours or until done.
Pour 1/2 cup soup over top.

title: lollipops
directions: In medium saucepan combine sugar, syrup and 1/2 cup water. Cook over medium heat without stirring, until candy thermometer registers 300° or until small amount of mixture forms hard, brittle threads when dropped into cold water.
Remove from heat.

title: collin and gregory's chocolate-peanut butter bars
directions: In a large bowl, beat together butter, peanut butter and brown sugar until well combined.
Beat in egg, water and vanilla.

title: meat loaf for ten
directions: Combine ingredients in order given.
Mix well.
Press into greased loaf pans and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: frozen fruit punch
directions: Dissolve jello in boilig water; add remaining ingredients.
Mix and freeze.
Makes about 3 (1/2 gallon cartons; use empty milk cartons).
When serving, add 2 quarts ginger ale for each 1/2 gallon frozen punch.
Stir until slushy.

title: pig eaten good cake
directions: Combine in a large bowl, except oranges.
Add oranges last. Bake at 350° in an oblong pan for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: canned spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook tomatoes, onions, peppers and garlic; run through sieve into very large stock pot.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 1 1/2 hours or until desired consistency is reached.
Place in jars and cover with hot lids; process in hot water bath.
Process pints for 5 minutes and quarts for 10 minutes.
Cooked ground beef can be added when jars are opened.
Makes 19 pints.

title: banana chocolate chip muffins
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together until well combined.
Add bananas, butter and vanilla; beat until combined.
In another bowl, combine flour, baking soda, powder and salt.
Add to banana mixture; blend until just moistened.
Stir in chocolate chips and spoon into greased or paper lined muffin tins.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until golden (more cook in less time).
Makes approximately 24 regular sized muffins.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Bring water, butter and dried onion to a boil.
Add package of broccoli.
Bring to a boil and add 1 1/2 cups Minute rice.
Set aside for 5 minutes.
Add soup and Cheez Whiz.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: ambrosia
directions: Fold mayo into yogurt.
Fold in the rest of the ingredients. Cover.
Chill 2 hours.
Makes 6 servings.

title: ragout of beef
directions: Wipe meat with a cold damp cloth and cut into small cubes. Sprinkle with salt and pepper; roll in flour.
Melt margarine in a large saucepan.
Add meat and brown it well.
Stir in 1 tablespoon flour.
Add 1 cup boiling water.
Bring to boiling point, stirring constantly.
Add carrot and onion.
Cover tightly and let simmer 1 hour.
Add Worcestershire sauce and serve hot. Excellent over baked potato.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs lengthwise in half.
Remove yolks; mash.
Add other ingredients.
Place mixture back into egg halves.
Top with paprika.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all together.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: old fashioned tomato soup
directions: In saucepan, combine the first 6 ingredients.
Cover and simmer 1 hour.
Heat milk or cream in top of double boiler over simmering water.
Add to the tomato mixture just before serving. Makes about 1 1/2 quarts or about 8 servings.

title: tijuana tort
directions: Brown ground beef with chopped onion and salt.
Add tomato sauce, taco seasoning, oregano, diced green chilies and stewed tomatoes.
In baking dish, place layers of meat, tortilla shells and cheese.
Again, layer meat, tortilla shells and grated cheese until all ingredients are in baking dish.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Saute ground beef and onion together.
Drain.
Combine with mixed vegetables and the diluted soup.
Place in a large casserole dish.
Cover with mashed potatoes and sprinkle cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until the potatoes start to brown and the cheese is melted.

title: carl reiner's cookies
directions: Blend all; put small "dollops" on cookie sheet and bake at 350° until slightly brown on edge.

title: angel biscuits
directions: In a bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water.
Put flour, sugar, soda, baking powder and salt in separate bowl.
Cut in shortening. Add buttermilk and yeast mixture.
Mix well.
(Does not have to be kneaded.)
Dough can be stored in a covered plastic bowl in the refrigerator for 1 week.
Roll out and cut in shapes or drop balls on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: butternut squash and sour cream
directions: Melt butter in frying pan.
Add squash and 1/2 cup water.
Put a lid on frying pan and let simmer.
When squash is tender, mash with fork until smooth.
Add salt, pepper and dill weed.
Slowly add sour cream until thickness you want.
May add onion flakes.

title: buckeye candy
directions: Mix peanut butter, margarine and sugar like dough. Form with hands the mixture into buckeye balls. Chill until hard.

title: creamy cheddar spread
directions: In bowl, beat cream cheese until smooth.
Gradually beat in beer or milk.
Add Cheddar cheese and red pepper, beating until well blended.
Chill 1 hour.
Serve as a spread on Wheat 'n Bran Triscuits wafers.
Garnish with parsley.

title: new orleans po boys
directions: Mix together and simmer on stove until hot.
Serve on po boy buns.
A tasty way to use leftovers.

title: orange gingerbread muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, orange peel, baking soda and spices; set aside.
In a small bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Add to flour mixture; don't beat or overmix.
Combine only until moistened.
Spray 12 muffin cups with nonstick spray.
Fill 3/4 full.
Place muffin pan in center of oven and bake until toothpick comes out clean, 15 minutes.
Invert muffins on wire rack and cool.
Serves 12.
Contains 182 calories, 7 gm fat and 187 mg sodium.

title: texas caviar
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve with Scoops.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add remaining ingredients. Chill until thick enough to stir, then
pour into 8-inch glass dish.
Makes 12 portions.

title: steak in foil with mushrooms
directions: Center steak on heavy aluminum foil.
Saute mushrooms in a small amount of butter.
Sprinkle over meat.
Add remaining ingredients; seal carefully.
Bake at 450° for 1 1/2 hours or until tender.
Yields 4 to 5 servings.

title: kohl's coffee cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Flour and grease an 8-inch square pan.
Put batter in pan and bake at 350° until cake tests done and is brown.

title: hawaiian casserole
directions: Combine meat, onion and salt.
Form into meatballs the size of walnuts.
Brown on all sides in hot skillet.
Stir in catsup, brown sugar, vinegar and mustard.
Bring to a boil.
In a greased 2-quart casserole, combine beans and pineapple.
Arrange meatballs on top and pour sauce over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Serves 6.

title: feta cheese spread
directions: Place cream cheese, Feta cheese, scallions and oregano in mixing bowl.
Mix 30 seconds on low speed; scrape the bowl, then mix on medium-high 1 minute.
Layer each wedge with cucumbers, tomatoes and cheese spread on top.
Makes 2 1/4 cups cheese spread.

title: yummy potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes in the skins; cool.
Peel; shred into a 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Heat 1 stick margarine and soups.
Add cheese, sour cream and onion.
Stir mixture into potatoes.
Mix 2 tablespoons melted margarine and corn flakes; sprinkle on top. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes before serving.
Yields 10 to 15 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt margarine and mix with dressing mix.
Cover bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan with chopped chicken.
Mix milk, sour cream and soups.
Pour over chicken.
Top with dressing and pat lightly into soups.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until bubbly.

title: peach cream pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Cut butter into small pieces and dot pie shell with butter.
Cover with peaches.
Combine sugar, flour and nutmeg.
Stir in half and half or cream.
Pour over peaches.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes.
Chill before serving.

title: good and easy chicken
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Mix sherry, soups and butter well.
Put
small amount in bottom of pan.
Spread the uncooked rice
in bottom of pan.
Spread the uncooked rice in pan
and spoon
sauce
over it.
Lay chicken pieces on top of rice and pour any remaining sauce over the chicken.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix peanut butter, brown sugar and flour.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Put flour on your hands and roll a spoonful into a small ball.
Roll in white sugar.

title: velvet pudding(pudim de veludo)
directions: To Make The Caramel:
Put 3/4 cup sugar into a pudding pan; sprinkle sugar with 2 tablespoons water.
Place over medium heat; when sugar begins to brown, stir constantly until reaching an evenly brown caramel color.
With a spatula, spread caramel evenly on bottom and sides of pudding pan and put aside to set.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Add sugar and oil to eggs.
Mix well and add zucchini.
Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into two 5x9 inch loaf pans that have been greased.
Bake at 325 degrees for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: one pan ground beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and chopped onion.
Drain fat.
Add tomato juice and noodles.
Simmer 8 to 10 minutes until noodles are tender.
Stir in sour cream or yogurt and simmer until warm.

title: classic cake-like brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt chocolate in top of double boiler over simmering water.
Remove and cool to room temperature.

title: beer muffins
directions: In a large bowl, combine Bisquick and sugar. Mix well. Gradually add beer and stir until well incorporated. Divide batter equally into well-greased 12 count muffin tin. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes or until muffins are large and puffy and lightly browned on top. Makes 12 muffins.

title: strawberry bread (cake)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine dry ingredients.
Combine beaten eggs and oil. Blend the dry ingredients and egg mixture until just moistened. Fold in strawberries and nuts.
Bake in 2 greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pans or 1 large pan.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes. Check for doneness.
Let cool. Delicious and can be frozen!

title: overnight vegetable salad
directions: Combine cabbage, peas, water chestnuts, onion, celery, apple and salt in a large bowl; toss well.
Combine sour cream, mayo and sugar, stirring until blended.
Spread sour cream mixture over cabbage mixture, sealing edges.
Layer cheese and pecans on top. Cover and chill for 8 hours.
Toss before serving.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Put eggs, butter, sugar, corn syrup and vanilla into blender container.
Cover and blend at medium speed, about 2 minutes, or until very light and fluffy.
Add pecans. Cover and blend at medium speed just until nuts are coarsely chopped.
Pour into pastry crust.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes or until filling is set at edges, but is still lightly soft in center (overbaking will cause filling to curdle).
Cool.
Top with whipped cream, if desired.
Makes 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: creole chicken and sausage jambalaya
directions: Heat oil in medium to large Dutch oven.
Place flour, salt, black and cayenne pepper in small paper bag.
Shake chicken in bag.
Fry in oil until brown.
Add sausage and brown.
Saute onion, bell pepper and celery while chicken and sausage continue to cook.
Add tomato sauce and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Bring to a boil and simmer 5 minutes.
Add rice.
Bring to a boil for 1 minute. Stir.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: honey macaroonies
directions: In large bowl, stir first 4 ingredients together (oats, coconut, walnuts and flour).
In heavy saucepan, combine brown sugar, butter and honey.
Bring to boiling, stirring frequently. Pour over dry ingredients.
Blend well.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Drain pineapple; heat juice and add jello and cream cheese. Stir until dissolved.
Cool a few minutes and add Coke.
Put in refrigerator.
When it begins to congeal, add pineapple and nuts. Place in mold or Pyrex dish.

title: sausage and cheese balls
directions: Mix all together and form into 1-inch balls.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Put in toothpicks to serve.

title: ham delight
directions: Combine ingredients and spread on rolls.
Heat oven to 325° and bake until cheese starts to melt.

title: shrimp stew
directions: Fry meat until crisp.
Drain and crumble. Fry onions in grease. Add flour and brown with onions.
Add tomato juice, catsup, corn, butter, salt, pepper, hot sauce and shrimp. Cook on low heat until shrimp are done. Serve over rice.

title: chili con queso
directions: Put all ingredients in chafing dish, pot, etc. and heat until cheese is melted.
Keep warm to serve.
Serve with Doritos, cheese flavor or plain.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Mix together 1 c. sugar, egg, flour, oil, milk and baking powder. In a 9
x 9 inch baking dish, place the rhubarb and dash of nutmeg. Pour batter over rhubarb. Bake at 350°F. for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: easy bread dressing
directions: Combine butter, onion, celery, salt, pepper, seasoning and cream of chicken soup.
Stir into bread crumbs.
Add enough very hot water or broth to moisten; stir well.
Let set for 20 minutes. Pour into greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Add additional water or broth, if needed.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: nacho cheese dip
directions: Melt cheese, 1/2 at a time, with 1/4 cup milk.
Cook ground beef and sausage; drain well.
Put cheese and meat together in crock-pot on low; stir often.
Boil juice out of green chiles and tomatoes and add to cheese mixture.

title: grand marnier mousse
directions: Beat eggs with salt until softly peaked.
Gradually add 1/4 cup sugar until meringue is stiff and shiny.
Whip cream until stiff, then beat in rest of sugar.
Gently blend in Grand Marnier. Fold in egg whites and turn into 1-quart mold or spoon into individual dessert dishes.
Freeze until firm.
Remove to refrigerator for 15 minutes before serving.
Top with candied flowers or serve with warm raspberry sauce.

title: mom's salmon stew
directions: Cube potatoes and boil until done.
Drain off most of the water.
Add the salmon and corn; let boil.
Add in the remaining ingredients and salt and pepper to taste.
Bring to a boil and serve hot.

title: wampus bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add onion and potatoes, then the milk.
Mix well.
Drop by a large spoon into very hot grease. Brown and serve hot.
(I have a very small ice cream scoop which I dip into cold water between scooping out dough; works nicely.)

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Wash and slice tomatoes. Batter tomatoes with corn meal. Fry in hot oil, browning on each side. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: swiss vegetables medley
directions: Combine vegetables, soup, 1/2 cheese, sour cream, pepper, pimento and 1/2 fried onions.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes (uncovered).
Top with remaining cheese and onions and bake for 5 minutes longer.

title: hilda's dip
directions: Brown meat, onions, and garlic, and drain grease.
Add the remaining ingredients.

title: kugel mackie
directions: Mix all ingredients, except noodles, in electric mixer.
Mix ingredients in order listed.
Fold in noodles.
Place in large greased Pyrex baking dish.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes and carrots in boiling water until tender; drain.
Saute bacon until crisp; drain and crumble.
Saute onion and celery in 2 tablespoons of bacon fat.
Combine cooked vegetables, bacon, salt, pepper, milk and cream.
Simmer for 30 minutes; do not boil.
Garnish with shredded Cheddar cheese and parsley.
Makes about 2 quarts.

title: artichoke surprise
directions: Cook rice in chicken broth with enough water to make 2 cups of liquid. Combine liquid from artichokes with mayonnaise and curry. Set aside. Stir remaining ingredients into hot rice. Add curry-mayo dressing. Blend well. Cover and bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Serves 4.

title: pecan squares
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Into large bowl, add cake mix, 1 egg and 1/3 cup oil, mix with fork until crumbly.
Press in pan and bake for 20 minutes.
In small saucepan, heat 4 eggs, syrup, sugar and butter until dissolved.
Stir in pecans, pour over baked cake.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add remaining ingredients and mix together well. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes and then 300° oven for 45 minutes.

title: upside-down ham loaf
directions: Melt butter in bottom of a greased loaf pan or casserole. Sprinkle with brown sugar. Stud pineapple slices with whole cloves and arrange on top of sugar. Combine ham and remaining ingredients. Pack mixture in pan on top of pineapple. Bake, covered, in moderate oven at 375° about 30 minutes. Turn out upside down on a hot platter. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: hot dog kraut casserole
directions: Boil hot dogs.
Cut pepper, onion and celery in large pieces. Put in saucepan with a little water and cook until tender; drain. Bring tomato juice and Sweet 'N Low to boil and set aside.
Put drained kraut in bottom of casserole dish.
Layer hot dogs, pepper, onion and celery mixture.
Pour tomato juice over layers and cook 20 minutes in a 350° oven.
No fat; very low in calories.

title: lazy day lasagna
directions: Cook noodles in boiling salted water following package directions. Drain when done. While noodles are cooking, brown ground beef and pour off grease.
Combine beef, sauce and oregano. In greased 9 x 13-inch pan, alternate layers of noodles, cottage cheese, Mozzarella and sauce mixture, making sure there is sauce on top layer.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Mix jello as directed.
Let chill.
Then add pineapple, mayonnaise and cottage cheese.
Let set until firm.

title: banana pie
directions: Layer ingredients in order.
Top with Cool Whip and chill. "Ideal recipe for diabetics."

title: pineapple coleslaw
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and toss with mayo type salad dressing to suit.

title: tiger cookies
directions: Stir together flour, soda, salt, sugar and crushed Kellogg's Frosted Flakes; set aside.
Stir together margarine or butter (softened), vanilla and eggs.
Add to flour mixture.
Mixture will be stiff and seem dry.
Keep mixing until everything is moist. Add chocolate chips and mix well.
Roll into balls and flatten. Cook at 350° until just barely light brown.
Do not overcook!

title: jiffy shrimp skillet
directions: Place soup in skillet and pour boiling water over.
Cover; bring to boiling.
Stir in rice, shrimp, celery, green pepper and seasonings.
Cover and bring to boil.
Cook 10 minutes.
Just before serving, add almonds and olives.
Serves 4.

title: harvest popcorn
directions: Heat
oven
Mix
margarine, dill weed, lemon pepper,
Worcestershire sauce, garlic powder, onion powder and salt.
Toss
with
remaining ingredients.
Line large 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch baking pan with aluminum foil extending beyond edges of	pan to keep popcorn in pan.
Spread popcorn mixture in	pan. Bake 6 to 8 minutes, stirring once.
Cool completely and store in airtight container.

title: play dough
directions: Mix salt and flour, then add oil, cream of tartar, water and food coloring.
Mix and stir in large pan over medium heat until it feels like mashed potatoes.
Store in bowl for longer use. Keeps up to 2 months.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water; add dash of sugar.
Add scalded milk, margarine, salt and sugar.
Mix until margarine is melted.
Add beaten eggs; mix.
Add 3 cups flour and mix until batter is smooth. Add yeast mixture.
Add just enough flour to make a sticky dough, about 3 cups.
Use remaining 1 cup of flour on floured surface. Knead until it's all gone.
Let dough rise 1 hour.
Divide into 2 parts.
Roll dough out.
Cover entire surface with melted margarine.
Sprinkle generously with sugar and cinnamon.
Crumble brown sugar and sprinkle over dough.
Add raisins, if desired. Roll and cut into slices about 1 1/4 inches thick.
Place close together on a greased cookie sheet.
Repeat with second section of dough.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Frost, if desired.

title: chicken dressing casserole
directions: Cook chicken and remove bones.
Reserve 1/2 cup broth.
Cut chicken into bite-sized pieces.
Combine soups, milk and broth. Heat thoroughly.
Combine stuffing mix and butter.
Spread 1/2 of stuffing in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer chicken over this. Then pour soups over chicken and top with remaining stuffing. Bake, uncovered, for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix and pour in unbaked pie shell and cook until golden brown at 350° for about 35 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: tak pioneer compote
directions: Place all ingredients into a pot; fill with water, just so you can see the water level.
Cook on low heat about 20 minutes.

title: delicious chicken breasts
directions: Cut chicken breasts in two and place in 9 x 13-inch pan. Place a slice of cheese over each 1/2 breast.
Mix soup with wine and pour over chicken.
Smother chicken with crumbs.
Melt butter and drizzle over the top of the crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, for 2 hours at 325°.
Serves 12.

title: special chicken and rice
directions: Prepare rice as directed on package.
Keep warm.
Meanwhile, cook green pepper and onions in heated oil in covered skillet over low heat until tender, but not browned.
Blend cornstarch with a small amount of chicken stock.
Add remaining stock and soy sauce. Gently stir chicken and stock into vegetables.
Cook and stir just until sauce is clear and thickened.
Add tomatoes and cook just until heated.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook the broccoli in boiling salted water until tender.
Drain and arrange in greased 11 1/2 x 7 1/2-inch baking dish.
Place chicken on top of broccoli.
Pour the mixed soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder on the chicken.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.

title: can't leave it alone
directions: Mix flour, butter and chopped nuts together.
Pat in bottom of 9 x 15-inch pan.
Bake at 375° until light brown.
Cool.

title: oven fried potatoes
directions: Wash and scrub potatoes.
Pat dry with paper towels.
Don't peel.
Cut into strips. Spray potatoes with oil to coat all sides. Place in baking dish and bake at 450°, uncovered for 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.
Turn frequently.
Sprinkle with paprika or chili powder to taste.

title: tapioca pudding
directions: Beat egg whites until they form peaks.
Add 1/2 of the sugar and beat.
Mix milk, sugar, egg yolks and tapioca.
Cook and stir until it comes to a full boil.
Cool and add vanilla, almond and pineapple.
Fold in egg whites.
Serves 6.

title: goose liver pate
directions: Lightly saute the livers
in butter so they are still pink inside.
Add herbs, sherry, brandy, honey, salt and pepper and simmer for 2 minutes.
Finely puree the mixture, one cupful at a time, in a food processor or blender.
Pack into an earthenware jar and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Serve cold on small pieces of toasted rye bread.

title: cold spaghetti
directions: Break spaghetti.
Cook and rinse well.
Mix all ingredients well and refrigerate.

title: maple pumpkin cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine crumbs, sugar and margarine. Press firmly on bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
In large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Add pumpkin, eggs, 1/4 cup maple syrup, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Mix well.
Pour into prepared crust. Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes (center will be slightly soft).
Cool. Chill 3 to 4 hours.
Garnish each slice with remaining maple syrup and chopped pecans.
Refrigerate any leftovers.
This cheesecake also freezes well.

title: party lemonade
directions: In pitcher, stir sugar and hot water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir vigorously with a wooden spoon and pour into tall glasses.
May add a drop of red food coloring to make pink lemonade.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil.
Add eggs and beat well.
Combine all dry ingredients (flour, salt, powder, soda and cinnamon) and stir into sugar mixture.
Add nuts, grated carrots and pineapple.
Beat well.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
May be iced when cooled with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: candied yams
directions: Peel potatoes.
Slice.
Place in baking dish.
Add water, sugar, nutmeg and butter.
Bake until potatoes are cooked with low juice.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Drain oranges well.
Beat eggs.
Add oranges and dry ingredients, sifted together.
Beat 4 minutes with electric beater on slow speed so some flakes of orange are showing.
Pour batter into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Boil chickens until tender.
Debone.
Add soups, poppy seed, salt and sour cream.
Mix well.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Put package of cracker crumbs on top, then pour stick of melted butter over all.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix well and pour into greased oblong pan.
Bake at 350° until cake tests done.

title: savory corn bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°, then grease a 2-quart casserole dish.
In large bowl, combine milk and egg yolks.
Blend well.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
Add flour, corn meal, baking powder and pepper to milk and egg yolk.
Beat until smooth. Stir in green peppers, corn and crumbled bacon.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Roll chicken pieces in flour, coating well.
Brown chicken in oil on all sides.
Drain excess oil from skillet. Add remaining ingredients and cover.
Simmer 30 to 40 minutes or until chicken is fork-tender.
Serve over hot pasta.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Peel and cut potatoes into thin slices.
Cook and stir onion in margarine in 2-quart saucepan until onion is tender.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until mixture is bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in milk and 1 1/2 cups of the cheese.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir for 1 minute.
Place potatoes in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Pour cheese sauce over potatoes.
Cook, uncovered, in 325°
oven for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: holiday fruit cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Mix in the rest of ingredients.
Add fruit last.

title: cream cheese pinches
directions: Beat cream cheese at medium speed of an electric mixer until smooth; add 1 egg, 1/4 cup sugar and vanilla, stirring well.
Set aside.
Combine water and shortening in a saucepan; heat until very warm (120° to 130°).

title: gingerbread
directions: In a large mixing bowl, mix sugar, oil and syrup.
Add beaten eggs; mix well.
Add soda mixture, flour and spices, stirring constantly.
Add boiling water, beating until smooth.
Pour into greased baking pan.
Bake until toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: roast fresh ham
directions: Score the top of the ham and season with salt and pepper.
Put on a rack in a shallow roasting pan.
Roast in a 325° oven for 40 to 45 minutes per pound or until the meat reaches 185° on the meat thermometer.
About 1 1/4 hours before the meat is done, spread with a mix of 1 cup light brown sugar, 1 teaspoon dry mustard and 2 tablespoons vinegar.

title: cheese squares
directions: Cream together butter and
brown
sugar.
Add
flour and nuts, mix with hands to make
crumb
mixture.
Reserve
one cup for topping.
Press remainder into bottom of 8-inch square pan. Bake at 350° for 12 to
minutes
until
light brown.
Cool. Blend together granulated sugar
and cream cheese until smooth. Add milk.
Add
egg, lemon
juice
and
vanilla.
Beat
well. Spread over baked crust.
Sprinkle with reserved crumb mixture. Cut into squares after baking for
25 minutes at 350°.
Freezes well.

title: poached salmon with cucumber sauce
directions: Stir together yogurt, scallions, cucumber, lemon juice and dill.
Refrigerate.

title: "play dough" for children
directions: Mix well in a pan and then heat on stove on medium until thick.
Stir constantly.
Thickens quickly.
Form dough into a ball with wooden spoon.
Drop onto wax paper to cool.
Once it has cooled, knead until smooth.
Play Dough is ready.
Pan will clean easily if soaked in cold water.

title: chocolate chip pound cake
directions: Sift together cake mix and chocolate pudding.
Make well in center of dry mixture and add all other ingredients except chocolate chips.
Beat well, then stir in chocolate chips with spatula.
Pour batter in tube pan and bake 55 minutes or one hour at 350°.
Cool on wire rack.

title: peach sauce
directions: Put in a covered blender container at low speed. Blend together all ingredients until smooth.

title: fruit salad dressing
directions: Pour cold water in medium saucepan.
Sprinkle gelatin over water; let stand for 5 minutes to soften.
Add vinegar, sugar, honey, celery seed, salt, pepper and dry mustard.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until gelatin and sugar dissolve.
Cool to room temperature.
Store in covered container in refrigerator.

title: neiman-marcus brownies
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together and pat into 9 x 13 pan. Set aside.

title: cherry cream freeze
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and mix well.
Gently fold in whipped cream and turn into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Corner will fall. Freeze.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Mix in blender.
Two more eggs and 1/2 cup milk makes another pie.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in 9-inch pie pan.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Drain all vegetables and put in a large bowl.
Combine vinegar and sugar in saucepan; heat until dissolved.
Cool.
Pour over salad.
Toss only a few times.

title: cheese bacon quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Bake pie shell for 8 to 10 minutes. Reduce oven to 350°.
Crumble bacon and put in pie shell.
Add cream and salt to beaten eggs.
Sprinkle cheese over bacon.
Add egg mixture. Dot with butter.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: cherry cheesecake
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat the cream cheese and sugar until smooth. Fold in whipped topping; spoon into crust. Top with pie filling. Refrigerate until serving. Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix all together and serve.

title: rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add sugar, shortening, egg, salt and 1/2 of flour.
Beat at low speed with mixer until smooth. Stir in remaining flour.
Place dough in a greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled. Punch dough down.
Knead briefly.
Shape.
Let rise again until doubled.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant into small bite-size pieces.
This will take about 2 months.
Keep the trunk!
You'll need something to store the pieces in.
Add enough brown gravy to cover.
Cook over open fire for about 3 weeks at 500°.
This will serve about 2700 people.
If more are expected, add 2 rabbits.
Use care though, most folks do not like to find hare in their stew.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add flour and potato chips. Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Drop by teaspoonfuls.
Cool.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: walnut bars
directions: Mix together shortening, salt, brown sugar and 1 cup of flour. Pat into greased pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 325°.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour on top of first layer.
Bake 25 minutes.

title: chinese noodle clusters
directions: Melt chocolate chips and heat to room temperature.
Stir in noodles and peanuts.
Drop on wax paper in bite size clusters. (You can also use butterscotch chips for a change.)
Makes 2 to 3 dozen.

title: rice pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a buttered pan; put some butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: laura's famous cheese ball
directions: In a large bowl, combine semi-softened cheeses; add onion, pepper, pimento, bacon bits and lemon juice.
Blend well and form into a ball.
Roll ball in dried parsley or finely chopped walnuts.
Refrigerate for a few hours to let flavors mingle. Serve with snack crackers.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: lite microwave seafood enchiladas
directions: Stir
together	the
soup, onion, hot sauce, nutmeg and dash of	black pepper.
