In another bowl, put 1/2 soup mix with broccoli (thawed and drained), seafood (example: small shrimp, scallops, crabmeat,
your
choice)
and
cup cheese.
Mix. Soften tortillas,	covered with a damp paper towel, in microwave for
30 to 60 seconds.
Place 1/3 cup of mixture in each tortilla.	Roll, seam
side	down, in 12 x 7-inch oil sprayed pan. Stir
milk
into rest of soup mix.
Pour over enchiladas. Microwave	on
High
12 to 14 minutes, covered. Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Let sit 10 minutes and serve.

title: taco salad
directions: In a large bowl, tear up 1 head of lettuce; add tomatoes and beans.
Add Doritos and drained, browned hamburger.
Mix with dressing.
Serve with a bowl of nacho cheese Doritos.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Fry hamburger.
Cook noodles, drain.
Mix all together.
Pour in a casserole pan.
Top with Mozzarella cheese. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: "surprise" spaghetti
directions: You turn the knob on the stove on.
You stir it.
Then it's ready.

title: strawberry cheesecake pie
directions: Beat together cream cheese, sugar and extract until smooth. Fold in whipped cream and pour into crumb crust. Chill several hours. Clean strawberries and place in a ring on top of chilled pie. Brush strawberries with melted jelly. Yield: 6 servings.

title: featherlight rolls
directions: Add shortening to milk while milk is still warm.
When milk has cooled, dissolve yeast in water and add to milk.
Add sugar, salt, eggs and flour; beat well.
Let rest in bowl about 20 minutes.
Knead dough for a minute or two.
Fill greased muffin pans 2/3 full or make out rolls.
Let rise until double in bulk. Bake in hot oven at 425° for 20 minutes.
Brush with butter after removing from oven.
Makes about 36 rolls.
Only one rising is needed for this recipe.

title: sugar free banana cream pie
directions: Prepare pudding with milk. Slice one banana into the bottom of the crust. Slice other banana into the prepared pudding. Pour pudding into the crust. Chill and enjoy.

title: b~l~t dip
directions: Cook, cool and crumble bacon.
Combine all ingredients; refrigerate for at least 6 hours.
Serve on crispy garlic toast or crackers.

title: carrot cake muffin treats
directions: Combine the flour, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg and ginger in a bowl.
Add the remaining ingredients and stir to blend.
Spoon into oiled muffin tins or paper cups.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: tequila sunrise(alcoholic drink)
directions: Slowly add grenadine to tequila and orange juice.
Garnish with lemon peel or lime wedge.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Heat the olive oil in a large skillet, season the chicken with salt and pepper, then fry, skin-side down for 5 minutes or until lightly browned.
Turn and brown other side.
Set chicken aside.
Add onions to pan and cook for 5 minutes.
Add garlic, mushrooms and peppers.
Cook another 3 - 4 minutes or until onions are golden.
Mix in tomatoes paste and cook 1 - 2 minutes, add wine.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly, add the tomatoes, breaking them down with a wooden spoon.
Sprinkle in the rosemary and oregano and return chicken to the pan.
Season with salt and pepper, cover and simmer 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Check chicken to see if tender - if not cook another 10 minutes. Transfer with a slotted spoon to serving plate.
If sauce is to liquidly boil uncovered for 5 minutes.
Season to taste.
Pour over chicken.
Serve immediately.

title: green rice casserole
directions: Cook rice.
Boil together celery, onions, margarine and broccoli for 5 minutes.

title: sicilian supper
directions: Brown meat; add onion.
Cook until tender.
Add tomato paste, water, salt and pepper.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Heat milk and cream cheese; blend well.
Stir in 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese, garlic salt, green pepper and noodles.

title: golden chiffon cake
directions: In a small bowl sift together cake flour, sugar, baking powder, and salt; Make a well in the center. Add cooking oil, egg yolks, water, lemon peel, and vanilla. Beat mixture at high speed with electric mixer about 5 minutes or until satin smooth. Wash beaters. Make sure they are completely dry before next step.

title: shrimp and okra stew of the southeastern tribes
directions: Leave the small okra pods whole, but slice the larger ones in two crosswise.
Place the okra, tomatoes, bay leaf, peppercorns and water in a large, heavy kettle and simmer, covered, for 20 minutes or until the tomatoes have broken up and the okra is tender.
Add the shrimp and simmer 10 minutes more.
Stir in the gumbo file and salt and simmer for about 10 minutes.
Serve hot in soup bowls.

title: baked avocado
directions: Empty all the inside of the avocado halves and put these creamy insides in a bowl.
Combine all the other ingredients and mix well. Preheat the oven to 350°.
Fill the avocado shells with mixture.
Bake avocado for 15 minutes.
May be served hot or cold.

title: cheesy hash browns(great dish for sunday brunch)
directions: Place frozen potatoes in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour 1/2 of the margarine over potatoes.
Mix all other ingredients (except the other 1/2 margarine) and pour over potatoes.
Top with remaining melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown rice, onion, pepper and celery in oil.
Stir in chili powder and salt.
Pour in can of tomatoes and water.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Turn on low heat until done.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Open crescent rolls and arrange on 11 x 14-inch cookie sheet. Seal ends of crescent rolls (roll out flat).
Bake until done. Cool.
Mix cream cheese, soup mix and mayonnaise.
Spread over crescent crust, add fresh vegetable pieces, cut and serve.

title: strawberry-pineapple delight
directions: Dissolve jello in water; add strawberries, then pineapple juice and then pineapple.
Place 2/3 of mixture in large dish (approximately 13 x 9 1/2 x 2-inches) and set in refrigerator until firm, approximately 30 minutes.
When set, cover with sour cream and remaining jello mixture on top.
Chill until set.

title: red beans and rice(from new orleans cajun)
directions: Sort beans and rinse well.
Cover with tap water and soak overnight.
Drain and put into large pot.
Add the hot water and the bone, onion, green rareripe, garlic, bay leaf, cayenne and salt.
Mix, bring to boil.
Cover and reduce heat to a simmer. Simmer until tender, about 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
(Add water, if necessary to keep from sticking or burning.)
Stif often.
Add sausage pieces, mix, simmer for 15 to 20 minutes, until cooked, uncovered.
Thick gravy will form.
Serve over hot cooked rice.

title: brownie pie
directions: Mix chocolate and margarine.
Add other ingredients and pour into pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: easy chicken and rice
directions: Mix in a 13 x 9-inch pan the rice, milk and soups.
Place chicken breasts on top with small pat of butter on top.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour to 1 1/4 hours until bubbly.

title: fat free marshmallow treats
directions: Premeasure ingredients.
Melt marshmallows over low heat until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Add Molly McButter sprinkles.
Mix well.
Add cereal and raisins.
Stir in quickly until well coated. Press mixture evenly into a 13 x 9-inch pan coated with cooking spray.
Cut into squares.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large bowl.
Add eggs and oil. Stir until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not beat.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, nuts and bananas.
Spoon batter into well-greased and floured 9-inch cake pans. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until cake tests done. Cool in pans for 10 minutes. Remove from pans.
Frost when cool.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Mix sugars and shortening together.
Add 2 tablespoons water and eggs.
Dissolve soda in 1/4 cup hot water.
Add to mix.
Add cut up dates.
Sift together flour and cinnamon.
Mix all together.
Add chopped walnuts.
Roll in wax paper and refrigerate for 1 hour or overnight.
Cut in slices and bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Arrange chicken in bottom of baking dish, sprinkle rice over chicken.
Mix the 3 soups and water together, pour over chicken and rice.
Cover with foil and bake in 325° oven approximately 1 hour or until chicken is done.
This recipe can be changed by adding 1 cup diced celery and 1 cup chopped onion.

title: lottie lane cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 375°.

title: cutout cookies
directions: Cream together the butter, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.

Mix well. Sift together the flour and cream of tartar. Stir flour mixture and baking soda into creamed butter mixture. Chill before rolling. Roll thinly on pastry cloth. Cut with cutters and bake at 375° for 6 minutes.
Sprinkle with colored sugar before baking or decorate with icing after cool.

title: basic waldorf salad
directions: Sprinkle apples with lemon juice to keep color bright. Combine apples, celery and walnuts.
Blend mayonnaise and cream. Add to apple mixture.
Toss; chill thoroughly.
Serve on crisp lettuce.
Yields 6 servings.

title: impossible macaroni and cheese pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a 10 x 1 1/2-inch pie plate.

title: pumpkin gobs
directions: Beat
all
ingredients	except	flour.	After mixed add flour. Drop
by tablespoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: sauerkraut cake
directions: In a large bowl, cream the oleo and sugar until light.
Beat eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla. Sift flour, baking powder, soda, salt and cocoa.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with water, beating well. Stir in kraut.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Cool in pan and frost.

title: quick pizza dip
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spread cream cheese on bottom of 9-inch pie plate.
Top with 1 cup Mozzarella cheese, pizza sauce and remaining Mozzarella cheese.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes or until mixture is thoroughly heated and cheese is melted.
Serve with assorted crackers and breadsticks.

title: fresh peach cobbler
directions: In glass baking dish 10 x 6 x 2-inch stir together 2/3 c. sugar, tapioca,1/4 tsp. salt and the cinnamon.
Fold in peaches, dot with butter.
Mix together the flour, baking powder, 1/3 c. sugar and 1/2 tsp. salt; add shortening, egg and milk.
Beat only until smooth (about 1/2 minute).
Spoon evenly over peaches, spreading with spatula.

title: potato salad
directions: Peel cooled potatoes and cube into a large bowl.
Add eggs as you cut them into small pieces.
Mix remaining ingredients; sprinkle with paprika.
Chill.

title: absolutely zippy chicken
directions: Combine salt, pepper and paprika; rub over chicken pieces. Place chicken in a single layer in an un-greased baking dish. Combine Worcestershire sauce and lemon juice; drizzle over chicken. Cut the margarine into small pats and place two pats on each piece of chicken.
Cover dish with aluminum foil.
Bake in a 500-degree oven 15 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 350 degrees and bake 1 hour longer.
If crisp chicken is desired, do not add soup.
If you use the soup, combine soup with 1/2 soup can of water.
Fifteen minutes before the end of baking time, pour some mixture over chicken, and continue baking for the remaining 15 minutes.
Yield: 4 - 5 Servings.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Break pretzels into small pieces; pour melted butter over pretzels.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350° in large Pyrex baking dish. Cool.
Mix cream cheese with sugar.
Add Cool Whip; pour over pretzels.
Dissolve strawberry jello in boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries; mix well.
Pour over cream cheese mixture.
Chill until set.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients; mix well. Pour into pie shell and bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix together flour, salt and brown sugar.
Cut in 1 cup shortening.
Add vinegar and milk.
Mix until coarse and forms a ball.
Makes 2 (10-inch) pie crusts.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown beef with onion and bell pepper.
Add water and rice. Season to taste with chili powder.
Simmer over low heat until rice is done and water is absorbed.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown beef and onions, drain, add taco seasoning. Stir, add all remaining ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes or more. Serve with Taco Chips in bottom of bowls or with Tortillas or Corn Bread on the side.
Top with toppings of your choice.
This makes a huge amount but it can be frozen or just do one of each ingredient.

title: bourbon balls
directions: Mix together wafer crumbs, powdered sugar, cocoa, walnuts, corn syrup and bourbon.
Mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in granulated or powdered sugar.
Store in container with tight fitting lid.
The longer stored, the better.

title: cheese strata
directions: Lightly butter bread both sides; cut each slice into 8 pieces. Alternate layers of cheese and bread, beginning and ending with bread in a 9 x 13-inch buttered dish.
Beat the next 6 ingredients together; pour over bread and cheese.
Allow to stand refrigerated overnight, covered.
Cover baking dish; place in pan of water. Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
May also use (or replace chilies) with ham, shrimp, chicken or mushrooms.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cheesy hash browns
directions: Mix hash browns, cream of chicken soup, sour cream, cheese, onions, salt, pepper and 1/2 cup melted butter.
Spread mixture into 13 x 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Combine remaining melted butter and crushed corn flakes and top mixture evenly.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yields 8 servings.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix in pan, sugar, cocoa, milk and butter.
Bring mixture to a boil, then add remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on waxed paper or greased cookie sheet.
Refrigerate.

title: crisp oven-fried chicken
directions: Combine corn flake crumbs and seasonings.
Beat egg and vegetable oil in a small bowl.
Dip chicken breasts in beaten egg and dredge in crumb mixture.
Place in baking sheet lined with aluminum foil for easy clean-up.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Mix all together and freeze.
Freeze leftovers.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
press into 9 x 12 pan.
Bake at 400° for 6 minutes.
Don't Overbake.
Cream together cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread over pretzel mixture.
Prepare jello in 2 c. boiling water.
Chill until slightly set.
Add strawberries and pour over cheese mixture.
Chill.

title: delicious delight
directions: Blend together flour and butter; then add pecans.
Press mixture into a 13 x 9-inch pan for crust and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: pasta fazool
directions: Saute onion, celery and garlic in margarine until tender.
Add broth and boil 15 minutes.
Add beans, parsley, salt, pepper and a little Hunt's sauce; mix well.
Mix in cooked and drained ditalini and serve hot.

title: pheasant with sautéed apples
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper in a plastic bag.
Add 2 or 3 pheasant pieces at a time and shake to coat.
Brown pheasant lightly in butter or margarine.
Add wine.
Cover and simmer about 35 to 55 minutes, or until tender.
Remove pheasant to warm platter.
Beat cream with egg yolks.
Slowly stir into pan drippings.
Cook and stir over medium heat just until sauce is smooth and thickened.
Do not boil.
Pour sauce over pheasant. Garnish platter with sauteed apples.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put everything, except onion rings, in a covered 2-quart dish and microwave on High for 8 minutes.
Stir and microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Stir and microwave on High 4 minutes more.
Stir in 2 tablespoons butter and put onion rings on top.
Then microwave at High for 1 minute, uncovered.

title: smoked salmon log
directions: Drain and flake salmon, removing any skin and bones.
Combine salmon with next 6 ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Chill several hours.
Combine pecans and parsley.
Shape salmon mixture into an 8 x 12-inch log and roll in nut mixture.
Chill well; serve with your favorite crackers.
This is best when made a day or two ahead of time and kept tightly covered.

title: apple butter bars
directions: Sift flour, soda, salt and sugar in mixing bowl.
Mix in uncooked oats; add melted butter.
Mix well.
Press 1/2 of the mixture into a 12 x 18 x 2-inch ungreased pan.
Spread with the apple butter, then cover with the remaining batter.
Pat lightly. Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes or until lightly brown.
Cool in pan and cut into bars.

title: betty's creamy potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes until soft.
Chop egg into small pieces.
Mix all ingredients together while still warm.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in greased casserole dish at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: pickled beets
directions: Mix all ingredients in a Dutch oven pot (or larger); cook slowly on low for about 1 hour.
Cool and enjoy.
(Remove pickling spice before storing or serving).
Makes a great vegetable dish for a buffet or covered dish supper.
Will keep in refrigerator for several weeks.

title: turkey divan
directions: Blend butter and flour in saucepan.
Add chicken or turkey stock and stir until thick.
Add nutmeg.
Blend in whipped cream, sherry and Worcestershire sauce.
Lay broccoli spears in bottom of shallow dish; cover with turkey slices and pour sauce over it. Sprinkle with grated cheese and put under the broiler until heated thoroughly and brown.

title: chicken gumbo
directions: Cook onion, celery and pepper in oleo until clear, then add other ingredients.
Simmer 30 minutes in large pot.
Can be served over rice.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: fruit salad
directions: Into large container with seal, peel oranges; cut into bite-size pieces toward the center core.
Squeeze core for juice into bowl, being careful not to drop seeds.
Quarter and peel apples; cut out core, then into bite-size pieces.
Cut peeled bananas into bite-size pieces.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring well.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.

title: mindy's baked ziti
directions: Cook ziti, drain.
Cook meat with a little bit of the sauce. Spoon off fat.
Add meat to Ricotta.
Add together egg, Parmesan cheese, salt, pepper, parsley and 1/2 the Mozzarella.
Mix.
Add this to meat-cheese mixture.
Now add ziti and mix well.
Add 1/2 of the sauce, a little at a time, mixing gently.
Put some sauce in the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Put the ziti mixture in dish and cover with remaining sauce.
Now sprinkle the remaining Mozzarella cheese on top.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 20 to 40 minutes, until bubbling.

title: eileen's cheese cake
directions: Cream together 1 cup sugar and cream cheese.
Add eggs (mix well after each), 1 teaspoon vanilla and salt.
Bake in spring-form pan at 325° for 50 to 53 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes. Top with sour cream, 2 tablespoons sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla, stirred together.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: drunk chicken
directions: Pour half of the beer or soda out of can, place can inside chicken.
Rub chicken down with salt, pepper and garlic salt. Place on grill and cook until done.
Makes a really moist chicken. You can also do this with turkey.

title: homemade bread
directions: Mix 1 1/2 cups of warm water, yeast and sugar; set aside and let rise until bubbly.
In a large bowl, mix the yeast mixture and the flour.
Mix well.
Add oil, salt and 8 cups water.
Knead for 20 minutes.
Let rise 6 hours, covered.
Knead again.
Grease 6 pans, fill pans 1/2 full.
Let rise to edge of pans. Beat 1 egg and brush over top of loaves.
Bake 1 hour at 450°.

title: baked chicken breasts supreme
directions: In a large bowl, combine first eight ingredients.
Place chicken in mixture and turn to coat.
Cover and marinate overnight in the refrigerator.
Remove chicken from marinade; coat each piece with crumbs and arrange on a shallow baking pan.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes or until juices run clear.

title: yellow rice
directions: Chop onion and garlic and saute in oil; remove from oil.
Cool oil slightly and brown chicken in oil.
Wash rice until water is clear and place into a turkey roaster.
Add 3 pints of very hot water, salt, tomatoes, onions, garlic and food coloring; stir. Place chicken on top and pour oil over it.
Cover.
Start cooking at 500° for 15 minutes; lower to 350° and cook for 30 to 45 minutes.
Garnish with peas and pimento and heat slightly.

title: spice tea mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add 2 tablespoons to 1 cup boiling water.

title: strawberries in the snow
directions: Mix and refrigerate 1 hour.
Make into shape of strawberry and roll in red sugar.
Green leaves are slivered almonds dipped in food coloring.
Add water to green coloring.

title: surprise coconut-sour cream cake
directions: Mix these items together.
Cover and refrigerate at least overnight.

title: dream bars
directions: Place margarine and flour in blender (food processor) with steel blade.
Place crust ingredients in the bowl and process on high speed until combined.
Pat mix into bottom 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until golden.
Set aside to cool. Meanwhile, add nuts to coarsely chop; set aside.
Then add eggs to empty bowl process on high speed, adding brown sugar gradually. Then add flour, baking powder, salt and vanilla just until combined.
Then fold in walnuts, coconut and semi-sweet chocolate. Pour over crust.
Bake 350° for 25 minutes longer.
Makes 30 bars.

title: beef roast
directions: Put beef in crock-pot.
Cover with V-8 tomato juice.
Sprinkle dry onion soup mix over beef (if large roast, you may want to use 2 packages of onion soup mix). Put the crock-pot on high for 7 to 8 hours, cook until tender.
With the tomato juice you may want to thicken this as you would for gravy by adding flour.
Tomato Juice Gravy good with mashed potatoes or rice.

title: potatoes au gratin
directions: Boil and grate potatoes.
Add mustard, salt, pepper, milk and cheese.
Place grated potatoes in casserole and pour hot cheese over all.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chinese style quick steamed fish
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Rub fish inside and out and let sit 20 minutes to 1 hour.
Lay fish in shallow dish.
Stuff cavity with the next 5 ingredients.
Cover with plastic wrap and microwave on High for 12 minutes or until opaque and glazed.
Sprinkle with chopped green onions and serve.
Serves 4 people.

title: roasted garlic
directions: Heat the butter, peanut oil and olive oil in a casserole over medium heat.
Add peeled cloves, side by side, and make sure they are well coated.
Bake for 20 minutes, basting from time to time. Add salt and pepper.

title: chopstick tuna
directions: Combine soup and water/milk. Add 1 cup of chow mein noodles, tuna, celery, cashews, onion and pepper. Toss lightly to mix well. Spread in ungreased baking dish. Sprinkle remaining noodles over top. Bake in a 375° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until heated through. Remove from oven and immediately garnish with drained mandarin orange sections. Serve hot.

title: easy shrimp dip
directions: Combine dry Good Seasons mix, sour cream and shrimp. Refrigerate at least 2 hours to allow flavors to blend.
Serve with large Fritos chips.

title: sweet and sour chicken or shrimp with rice
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice, and cut pineapple into smaller chunks.
To pineapple juice, add vinegar, soy sauce and enough water to make 1 1/2 cups plus 1 tablespoon liquid.
Into oleo in skillet, put the bell pepper, garlic, carrots, green onions, mushrooms and water chestnuts; add liquid and stir in rice, pineapple and chicken or shrimp.
Bring mixture to a simmer, cover and cook for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes, then fluff mixture with a fork.

title: easy chicken breasts
directions: Salt
chicken
to
taste.
Sprinkle
with
garlic salt, onion salt or whatever spices you wish.
Place chicken breasts in baking dish; pour over condensed cream of chicken and cream of
celery soup.
Spread
to
each
corner of dish; mix well. Bake at
400° for 10 to 20 minutes.
Lower oven to 300°.
Bake about
1 hour and 30 minutes or more.
(If time permits, lower oven
to
The slower you bake chicken, the more tender and moist it will be.

title: dottie's town meeting brown bread
directions: Sift baking soda with flours. Add cornmeal. Mix all dry ingredients, pressing out any lumps. Add molasses, milk and raisins. Stir well. Pour into 2 pint-sized cans (well-greased). Cover with 4 thicknesses of waxed paper; tie or tape securely. Place on rack in kettle with 2 to 3-inches of water. Cover and steam 1 hour.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and sour cream together with electric mixer until well blended. Add Provance seasoning (or any other dried herbs you like). Refrigerate until serving time.

title: breakfast drink
directions: Blend all ingredients in a blender and drink!

title: microwave tiger butter candy
directions: In 2-quart bowl, place white chocolate.
Microwave on Medium for 5 to 8 minutes, until stirred smooth.
Stir in peanut butter. Spread mixture on wax paper coated cookie sheet.
In 1-quart casserole dish place semi-sweet chips.
Microwave on Medium for 2 to 4 minutes until melted.
Drizzle over peanut butter layer; with knife or small spatula, swirl mixtures.
Refrigerate until firm; break into pieces.

title: can opener salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl.
Chill overnight.
Yields 10 servings.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Beat sugar, oil and eggs well. In separate bowl, combine flour, cocoa, salt and soda then add to sugar mixture.
Add buttermilk, water and vanilla and mix well. Bake in 9x13 pan or in jelly roll pan at 350° for 25-40 minutes.
Frost while hot.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook celery and onions in bacon fat until done.
Cook and drain carrots and potatoes, then mix everything together.
Add the milk last.
Simmer and eat.

title: spinach, chicken and noodle salad
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
Rinse well in cold water and drain again. Combine oil and seasonings and toss together with other items. Cover and refrigerate until ready to eat.

title: cranberry-filled wreaths(coffeecake)
directions: Spray 2 cookie sheets with a nonstick cooking spray.
Place cranberry sauce in a fine strainer or sieve.
Stir to break up; set aside to drain thoroughly.
Combine contents of the box and yeast packet from the roll mix with oats and 1/4 cup of sugar; mix well.
Stir in hot water, egg and margarine until dough pulls away from bowl.
Knead on lightly floured surface 5 minutes or until smooth.
Divide dough in half.
On prepared cookie sheets, press each half into 12 x 8-inch rectangles.
Top each with half of the drained cranberry sauce. 1/4 cup nuts and 1 tablespoon of sugar to within 1 inch of edge.
Roll up, starting from the long side, pinching seams and ends to seal.
Bring ends together to form a ring.
With kitchen shears, cut through ring almost to center at 2-inch intervals.
Cover loosely with plastic wrap.
Let rise 30 minutes or until nearly doubled.
Heat oven to 350°.
Uncover dough; bake 23 to 28 minutes or until golden.
Cool on wire rack before frosting.
Makes 2 coffee rings.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and butter together; add eggs and pecans. Fill shell.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°, then reduce temperature to 350° and bake for 35 minutes longer.

title: banana bread
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 hour in greased loaf pan.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: crustless quiche
directions: Combine all ingredients and blend with a spoon.
Pour into 9-inch quiche pan or pie plate.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top.
Bake at 325° for about 40 minutes.

title: french onion soup
directions: Saute onions in butter and oil.
Cover and cook for 20 minutes more on low heat.
Remove cover and add remaining ingredients except for bread and cheese.
Cover again and simmer for another 20 minutes.

title: crawfish fettucini
directions: Using a big pot, saute onions, celery and bell peppers in margarine.
Mix flour with a little water and add to onion mixture.
Cover and cook on low heat for 15 minutes.
Add parsley, garlic, crawfish, half of the Velveeta cheese, relish, salt and pepper.
Cook for 30 minutes.
Cook fettucini according to package directions.
Add fettucini.
Pour into a large, greased casserole. Top with remaining Velveeta cheese and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or microwave just until it is heated and cheese is melted.

title: broiled parmesan potatoes
directions: Stir together butter and spices. Place potato slices in a single layer on the unheated rack of a broiler pan.
Brush butter over both sides of potato slices.
Broil about 5-inches from the heat for 8 to 9 minutes or until potatoes begin to brown.
Turn potatoes with wide spatula.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Broil for 4 to 6 more minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: walnut clusters
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
In a bowl, with electric mixer at medium speed, beat butter with sugar until creamy.
Next, beat in egg, vanilla, then chocolate, then flour mixture.
Fold in walnuts.
Drop mixture by heaping teaspoonfuls 1-inch apart onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake just 10 minutes, no longer.
Cool.
Store in container with loose fitting cover.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen.

title: chicken stuffed peppers
directions: Cut tops of green peppers; remove seeds and membrane.
Saute onion in small amount of tomato liquid.
Add tomatoes, rice or barley, Tabasco, pepper, chicken and 1/2 of the cheese.
Stand peppers upright in an 8-inch square baking dish.
Stuff with tomato-rice filling.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 23 to 30 minutes or until hot.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Return to oven to melt cheese.

title: tater tot pie
directions: Brown
ground
beef, onion and pepper. Drain meat.
Put in bottom
of	ovenware dish.	Place Cheddar cheese soup, then onion soup,
then
mushroom
soup
on top of meat. Stick Tater Tots on top.
Bake	at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until Tots are brown and mixture bubbly.

title: congo squares
directions: Melt shortening in large saucepan.
Pour in brown sugar and let cool a little.
Beat in one egg at a time.
Add in flour mixture of dry ingredients, nuts and chips.
Spread into greased 2 x 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.
Don't overcook.

title: link log
directions: Grind or mash links which have been browned in oil.
Put into bowl, add the other ingredients.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Blend together the next 4 ingredients.
Add Cool Whip.
Judge texture.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Thaw and drain broccoli.
Mix first 6 ingredients.
Stir in Jiffy mix.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.

title: fruitcake for diabetics
directions: Pour orange juice and sugar substitute over chopped cranberries or cherries.
Let stand 1 hour.
Add raisins, pecans, pineapple and orange rind to cranberry mixture.
Add melted margarine.
Sift and measure flour.
Add soda, salt, allspice, cinnamon and nutmeg to flour.
Sift again.
Add dry ingredients to fruit mixture.
Stir until thoroughly mixed.
Pour mixture into 16 nonstick baking cups.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes until light brown.

title: one-step supper rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large mixing bowl, combine sour cream and egg yolks.
Add pancake mix (measure by lightly spooning into cup and leveling off) and blend until dry ingredients are well moistened.
Fill greased muffin cups one-half full.
May sprinkle with poppy or sesame seed, if desired.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serve warm.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together 3 times.
Set aside.
Combine sugar and cocoa; mix well. Beat egg yolks in large bowl of electric mixer.
Beat in water, vanilla and sugar mixture at medium speed.
Beat in flour mixture. Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form; stir 1/4 of chocolate batter gently into whites.
Fold egg whites into remaining batter. Pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan and bake for 25 to 30 minutes, or until a wooden pick inserted in center
comes out clean.

title: seven-layer salad
directions: Place in oblong 9 x 13-inch pan in order listed.
Mix 2 cups mayonnaise with 1 tablespoon sugar.
Spread over salad.
(This seals the moisture in.)
Refrigerate overnight.
Before serving, spread with 1/2 cup grated cheese.

title: classic beef stew
directions: In a Dutch oven, brown beef half at a time in the oil; drain. Return all meat to pan. Add onion, tomatoes, broth, tapioca, garlic, parsley, salt, pepper and bay leaf. Bring to a boil. Remove from heat. Cover and bake at 350° for 90 minutes. Stir in carrots, potatoes and celery. Bake, covered, for 60 minutes longer or until meat and vegetables are tender. Remove bay leaf before serving.

title: biscuits
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and shortening. Add milk. Roll out, cut and bake at 400° until brown.

title: surprise cookies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and roll into small balls.
Dip into confectioners sugar.
Place on cookie sheet.
Flatten.
Bake in preheated 350°
oven for 10 minutes.

title: knox blox
directions: In medium bowl, sprinkle gelatine over cold juice and let stand 1 minute.
Add hot juice and stir until gelatine is completely dissolved.
Pour into an 8 or 9-inch baking pan. Chill until firm.
To serve, cut into 1-inch squares.
Makes about 6 dozen blox.

title: christmas pickles
directions: Drain pickles and cut into strips.
Place back in jar and add ingredients.
Place in refrigerator, shaking often to dissolve sugar.
May be used over and over for more pickles by adding 1 1/2 teaspoons vinegar, 3/4 cup sugar, 1 tablespoon horseradish, celery seed and onion.

title: bread
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening.
Add hot water, salt, eggs and 3 cups flour.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water and add to creamed mixture and beat real good.
Add remaining 3 cups flour.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Make out next morning and place in greased loaf pan.
Cover with cloth.
Let rise until double in bulk (takes about 2 hours at room temperature).
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes 2 to 3 loaves.

title: chicken and bisquick dumplings
directions: Wash and boil chicken or chicken breasts until tender.
Use enough water to cover chicken.
When done, pour broth off and set aside 6 cups.
Season broth with milk, butter, salt and pepper to taste.
Have broth boiling; mix Bisquick with enough milk to pick up enough for a dumpling.
Pinch off dumplings from spoon the size desired.
Drop dumplings in boiling broth.
Press dumplings down in broth.
Do not stir.
Keep heat on medium to prevent scorching. Dip each dumpling in flour to thicken broth.
Tear chicken off bone and add to dumplings when done.

title: santa fe rice
directions: In a sauce pan bring the water to a boil and stir in the rice, beans, salsa.
Cover with lid and remove from heat.
Let stand 5-10 minutes.
Yield 4 servings.

title: never-fail dumplings
directions: Mix flour, salt and shortening.
Add water and eggs, making a soft dough.
Divide into 2 parts.
Roll out into thin sheets and let dry for 15 minutes.
Cut into small strips and drop in broth. Simmer or cook until done.
Use more salt, if you like.

title: butter crunch snack
directions: Mix cake, oleo and 1 egg together; spread in a 9 x 13-inch glass pan, then whip the cream cheese (room temperature), 2 eggs and confectioners sugar; beat.
Spread on top of first layer. (May have to use hands.)
Cook 25 to 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: low-fat zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Add applesauce.
Stir in vanilla and zucchini.
Sift dry ingredients together and mix well.
Add nuts. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves (equals 32 servings).

title: corn chowder
directions: Combine potatoes, celery, onions, corn juice and water, cooking until celery is done.
Add remaining ingredients, corn, bacon, mushroom soup, milk and crackers heating slowly.
Don't let it boil.
Serve with Queen Of Muffins.
Good stuff!

title: apple cake
directions: Bake in a 350° oven for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: poor man's lobster
directions: Cut haddock into 1-inch pieces.
Add salt, seafood seasoning and celery seed to water and vinegar.
Boil.
Add frozen fish; simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Drain and serve with melted butter.

title: crescent chicken squares
directions: Blend cheese and margarine until creamy.
Add chicken, salt, pepper, milk and chives to cheese.
Spread dough into 4 rectangles, sealing perforations. Spoon 1/2 cup of cheese mixture into center of each rectangle.
Pull 4 corners of dough to center and seal edges. Brush tops with melted margarine and sprinkle with bread crumbs. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: black-eyed peas
directions: Put all ingredients together in a pot and cook slowly until tender, about 3 hours.

title: breakfast treats
directions: Blend together the cream cheese, sugar, egg yolk, vanilla and softened margarine.
Spread on bread (crusts trimmed); roll up as jelly roll.
Cut in thirds or halves, as desired.
Dip in melted butter.
Roll in 1 cup sugar mixed with 4 teaspoons cinnamon. Freeze on cookie sheet.
Wrap airtight.
When ready to use, bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes (depending on frozen state).

title: lazy day lasagne
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Combine spaghetti sauce and meat; simmer about 15 to 20 minutes.
Combine oregano, Ricotta cheese, Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese.
In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, layer ingredients as follows:
1/2 cup sauce, 1/2 uncooked noodles, 1/2 of cheese mixture and 1 cup of sauce.
Repeat this layer, then add final layer of noodles and top with remaining sauce.
Cover and bake at 375° for about 50 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Cook in a double boiler until thick.
Cool and pour over fruit mixture.

title: cream cheese cake(crummy salad)
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water; let it cool.
Crush graham crackers very fine; add the margarine and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with 1/2 of crumb mixture. Mix cream cheese, 1 cup sugar and 2 teaspoons vanilla.
Mix until smooth and creamy.
Add the jello to this mix.
Whip milk and add jello and cheese mixture.
Mix well.
Pour over crushed crackers and add crackers over the top.
Chill for 12 hours or overnight.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix well.
Put into ungreased pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: shrimp macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
In a large bowl, toss cooked macaroni with remaining ingredients.
Cover and chill before serving.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: clam dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Heat in oven for 15 minutes or until slightly browned.

title: gumbo
directions: Toppings:

To dress up cooked vegetables, sprinkle with toasted sesame seed, toasted chopped nuts, canned French fried onions, slightly crushed seasoned croutons, snipped fresh herbs, chopped hard-boiled eggs and crumbled cooked bacon.

title: kool-aid punch
directions: Add sugar to water in saucepan; bring to a boil to make syrup. Add syrup to Kool-Aid; mix well.
Add pineapple juice; chill. Add ginger ale just before serving.
Yields 40 cups.

title: best banana cake(or, what to do with leftover bananas....)
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add slightly beaten eggs.
Add baking soda to the yogurt.
Add that combination to the previous one; beat well.
Add flour and salt alternately with bananas and vanilla.
Pour into oblong glass greased pan.
Add a handful of chocolate chips and mix slightly with a knife.
Chips will settle to bottom if mixed in too much.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar. Bake at 350° for at least 45 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: easy shrimp dip
directions: Thaw shrimp following package directions.
Drain well.
Set aside.
In a bowl, combine remaining ingredients. Beat until smooth. Fold in shrimp. Cover and refrigerate until chilled. Serve with crackers.

title: hot dip
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add tomatoes and green chilies. Mix all ingredients together and slow cook in a slow cooker for about 30 minutes.
Serve with chips.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, 1/4 cup sugar and margarine; press into 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: fudge
directions: Cook sugar and milk 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients. Stir until chocolate and Marshmallow Creme
melts.

title: jalapeno jelly(canning recipe)
directions: In food processor or blender, blend peppers and half of the vinegar until smooth.
In a 6 to 8-quart saucepan, combine pepper mixture, remaining vinegar, sugar and butter or oil.
Over high heat, bring mixture to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Stir in liquid pectin.
Return to a full rolling boil and boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly. Remove from heat.
Stir in food coloring.
Immediately fill hot half pint jars with jelly, leaving 1/4-inch headspace.
Wipe jar tops and threads clean.
Place hot lids on jars and screw bands on firmly.
Process in boiling water canner for 5 minutes.
Yield:
7 half-pint jars.

title: chewy crisps
directions: Blend all ingredients thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork dipped in water.
Bake in moderate oven at 325° for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Cool 1 minute before removing from baking sheet.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: company peas
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Mix all ingredients together.
Place in casserole dish. Bake in a 300° oven for 30 minutes.

title: stuffed noodles(simple)
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Add sausage (cut in long slices) with remaining ingredients.
Pour in baking dish.
Sprinkle shredded cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: banana punch(serves 50)
directions: Heat sugar in water and cool.
Add juices.
Smash bananas; add and mix well.
Freeze until needed in 2-pound containers.
About 15 to 20 minutes before serving time, place frozen mixture in punch bowl.
At serving time, chop up bananas and add that and ginger ale.
It is best served as a slushy consistency (can be stretched with more ginger ale if necessary).

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix oatmeal and tomato sauce in a small dish and set aside. Mix ground turkey, onion, green pepper, egg and salt.
Now combine all ingredients. Cook in a loaf pan at 350° for 45 minutes. Remove from oven and spread ketchup on top.
Bake 10
minutes more.
Yields 12 servings.
Preparation time is 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: chocolate covered pretzels
directions: Melt bark in small pan.
Remove from heat.
Dip pretzels and remove with a fork.
Place on wax paper to dry.

title: onion rings
directions: Mix together.
Dip onions (sliced) into mixture and cook in hot oil, a few at a time.
Then drain on paper towel.

title: apple nut bread
directions: In large bowl with wooden spoon, mix ingredients in order given.
Place in greased and floured loaf pans.
Makes 2 (8 1/2 x 4-inch) loaves.
Bake approximately 1 hour at 375°.

title: vegetable, beef and biscuit casserole
directions: In a 10-inch skillet over medium heat, brown the ground beef, breaking it up.
Drain any fat through a colander lined with paper towels or a coffee filter.
Stir in soups, water, vegetables and Worcestershire sauce.
Spoon into a 3-quart baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: mock lobster dip
directions: Over low heat combine soup and cheese.
Use eggbeater or whisk until smooth.
Add clams, few drops of Worcestershire sauce and few minced onion flakes. Serve warm.

title: egg custard
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, butter and vanilla; beat.
Pour in unbaked pie crust.
Bake for 10 minutes at 450°, then reduce heat to 325° and bake for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: seafood dip
directions: Mix and heat until bubbly.
Serve with crackers or vegetables.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken; take out bones and skin.
Cut up and place in 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Combine 1 can cream of chicken soup and condensed milk.
Pour over chicken.
Mix stuffing mix, water and margarine.
Pour on top of chicken and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: raisin oatmeal cookies
directions: Simmer raisins in water over low heat until plump (20 to 30 minutes).
Drain raisin water into measuring cup and add water to make 1/2 cup.
Mix shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in raisin-water.
Stir in flour, baking powder, soda, salt and spices; add rolled oats, nuts and raisins.
Drop onto ungreased cookie sheet and bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding as it says on box, then add remaining ingredients. When putting vanilla wafers and bananas in, put one layer down, then pour some mixture on it, then put another layer.

title: slaw
directions: Chop all vegetables as desired.
Add oil, salt and celery seed.
Mix sugar, water and vinegar.
Add and mix thoroughly. Will keep for weeks in the refrigerator.

title: meatballs in tomato sauce
directions: Pan-fry bacon.
Remove.
Combine beef, seasoning and portion of onion.
Shape into balls.
Brown in bacon grease.
Add rest of onions and tomatoes.
Cover and cook for 15 minutes over low heat. Thicken gravy with a little bit of flour and water.

title: glazed meat loaf
directions: Pour milk over crumbs.
Add ground beef and salt and pepper. Stir in carrot, onion and eggs.
Mix.
Pack in loaf pan.

title: chicken casserole supreme
directions: Cook chicken and remove meat from bones.
Cube meat and mix with the sour cream and mushroom soup; pour into a casserole dish. Mix together the melted margarine, chicken broth and stuffing mix. Put on top of the chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: orange julius
directions: Put first 4 ingredients in blender; process until creamy.
Add cubes, one at a time.
Process until crushed.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Press crescent rolls into a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking sheet to form a crust.
Bake in a 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: broccoli and stuffing
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: steak and gravy
directions: Roll steak in flour; sprinkle with salt and pepper and place in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Mix onion soup with water and coffee. Pour over steak.
Bake at 350° until gravy thickens or until steak is tender.

title: spanish rice
directions: Adds color and vitamins.
Can reheat in microwave.

title: easy rice pilaf
directions: Melt margarine in a small saucepan (nonstick).
Brown rice and Rosa Marina.
Add boiling water slowly.
Add bouillon cubes. Cover and simmer on low until all liquid is absorbed.
This mixes well with small pieces of meat (hamburg, beef or chicken) or add fresh vegetables for crunch.

title: knock your socks off salsa
directions: Chop everything that isn't already liquid or dust; bring it to a full boil, then can it.
Makes 9 to 10 quarts.

title: sauerkraut casserole
directions: Peel potatoes. Cut in fourths and then in halves.
Cook for 5 minutes after they come to a boil.
Saute onion in butter.
Rinse sauerkraut and put in roaster sprayed with Pam.
Mix in brown sugar and onion.
Brown kielbasa after cutting in small pieces. Add to sauerkraut and mix gently.
Stir in potatoes.
Bake at 350° covered for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake an additional 15 minutes.
Watch while baking.
Add water if needed.
This will serve 15 to 25 people.

title: mallow whipped sweet potatoes
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, butter, salt and spices, beat until smooth (add a little orange juice) Stir in 1 c. marshmallows. Place in baking dish and top with remaining marshmallows.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20 mins.

title: fried potato cakes(fritters)
directions: Beat the eggs and add other ingredients.
Mix thoroughly. Drop from spoon into hot fat.
Brown well on both sides.
Serves 4.

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix together and refrigerate for 4 days.
Mix each day and add small amount of water.
On fourth day, form into pound rolls and wrap in foil (shiny side in).
Place in low pan and add 1/2-inch water in pan and bake for 90 minutes at 325°.
Keep refrigerated.

title: squash patties
directions: Cook squash and drain well.
Mash squash.
Combine squash and egg.
Stir well.
Add flour, cornmeal, sugar and onion to squash. Stir until blended.
Drop squash mixture by heaping tablespoonfuls into hot oil.
Cook until golden brown.
Drain well on paper towels.

title: apricot cake
directions: Mix 1 cup apricot nectar, Crisco oil, lemon cake mix and lemon Jell-O.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: after church stew
directions: Put beef cubes in roast pan.
Add salt, pepper, vegetables, tomato soup and water.
Bake at 300° for 3 hours.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Add sugar to softened cheese.
Add peanut butter.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into large pie shell.
Chill before serving.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Steam chicken in salted water until tender.
Debone and cut up.
Saute onion in small amount of oil until clear.
Add soups, tomatoes, cumin, salt and pepper.
Simmer about 20 minutes. Remove from heat and add sour cream.
Heat tortillas in about 1/4-inch oil (just a second or two) on each side.
They should not be crisp.
Drain on paper towel.
Put a small amount of meat, Monterey Jack and a little sauce.
Roll tortillas.
Place in 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Continue until all tortillas are rolled. Pour remaining sauce over top.
Cover with Cheddar cheese and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: finger lickin' smoked chicken
directions: Sprinkle chickens with seasoned pepper and leave at room temperature for 1 hour.
Melt margarine with Worcestershire, Tabasco, lemon juice and garlic salt; add 7-Up.
Cook chickens on charcoal grill with mesquite charcoal.
Turn often and baste with margarine-7-Up mixture several times.
When chicken is done (about 60 minutes), baste once more.
It keeps chicken moist.

title: cranberry freeze
directions: Soften cream cheese and mix in sugar and mayonnaise.
Stir in cranberry sauce, crushed pineapple and walnuts.
Fold in Cool Whip and food coloring.
Pour into a lightly greased loaf pan.
Freeze until firm.
Let stand 10 to 15 minutes before serving.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: mexicorn(lo-fat and easy)
directions: Take juice from corn and put in skillet.
Saute peppers and onion in juice.
You may need to add more water.
When peppers and onions are done, add corn and simmer until corn is heated.

title: aunt bill's brown candy
directions: Pour 1 pint of sugar into a heavy iron skillet and place it over a low fire.
Begin stirring with a wooden spoon and keep the sugar moving so that it will not scorch at all.
It will take almost 30 minutes to completely melt the sugar, and at no time let it smoke or cook so fast that it turns dark.
It should be about the color of light brown sugar syrup.
As soon as you have the sugar started to heat in the skillet, pour the remaining 2 pints of sugar and the cream or milk into a deep, heavy kettle.
Set it over low heat to cook along slowly while you are melting the sugar in the skillet.

title: wilted leaf lettuce
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Save 3 tablespoons grease in skillet and combine with vinegar, water, sugar and salt.
Heat to boiling and stir 2 minutes.
Combine lettuce, onion and crumbled bacon. Pour hot liquid over greens and mix.
Garnish with chopped hard-cooked eggs.

title: peanut butter fudge(microwave)
directions: Put sugar, peanut butter, margarine and milk in glass bowl. Microwave on High for 2 minutes.
(If weather is damp 2 1/2 minutes.)
Remove and stir until all is mixed together.
Add vanilla and nuts and pour in greased pan (8 x 8-inches).
Chill for 20 minutes in the freezer.

title: taco soup
directions: Cook hamburger and drain.
Combine all ingredients and heat through.
Pour over taco chips in individual bowls.
Add grated cheddar cheese and a dab of sour cream to top.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes if skin is tough, but otherwise just scrub and rinse them.
Cut potatoes into thin slices, but not all the way through.
Lay a handle of a wooden spoon beside potato and this will prevent the knife from cutting all the way through.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onions and green peppers in butter.
Cook rice; mix with onion, pepper and butter.
Cook broccoli.
In a dish, make a layer of rice mixture and broccoli.
Mix soup and milk together.
Pour over top.
Put Cheez Whiz on top.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: blueberry cheese cake
directions: Mix together flour, butter or margarine and pecans.
Mix in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Press out to sides of pan, covering all of the bottom.
Bake at 425° for 12 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix Cool Whip, cream cheese and sugar together and spread over cooled crust. Place in refrigerator for 2 hours to chill.
Spread 1 can blueberry pie filling over chilled cream cheese mixture.

title: lettuce salad
directions: Chop and toss lettuce and cauliflower.
Mix mayonnaise, onion and sugar; pour over lettuce mixture.
Sprinkle cheese on top, then bacon.
Let stand.
Mix and toss just before serving.

title: coca-cola ham
directions: Place trimmed ham inside of brown paper grocery sack which you have placed in large baking pan.
Pour Coke over ham inside of sack.
Fold and staple sack closed.
Bake at 350° until done, according to how many pounds your ham is.

title: tasty sweet pickles
directions: Drain all liquid out of jar.
Cut pickles into slices.
Put back into the jar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Seal jar.
Keep out of the refrigerator for 24 hours. Turn upside down often.
Put back into the refrigerator.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook frozen broccoli with a little water.
Cook onion in College Inn.
Melt butter; add Bisquick and make a paste.
Add this paste to College Inn.
Stir well.
Add broccoli, pepper and half and half.
Heat and serve.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Thaw broccoli to breakage stage.
Mix with all other ingredients.
Melt oleo in pan in oven.
Add mixture to the pan. Cook in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry rhubarb pie
directions: Sprinkle 2 tablespoons flour on bottom of 9-inch crust.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix rice, cheese, broccoli and soup together.
Put into casserole dish and put French fried onions on top.
Cook at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Add next 5 and mix.
Add flour and mix.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: pineapple chicken
directions: Dredge chicken in flour, salt and pepper coating.
Brown in hot oil and drain.
Combine pineapple juice, brown sugar and soy sauce.
Pour over browned chicken. Cover and simmer for 45 minutes. Add pineapple chunks and cook another 5 minutes.

title: sugared nuts
directions: Put water, cinnamon and sugar in iron skillet until hot.
Add nuts and cook until dry and sugary.
Be sure to stir constantly. Pour on cookie sheet and break apart the pecans.
Let dry completely before storing.

title: old fashioned raisin bars
directions: Combine raisins and water and bring to boil.
Add shortening or oil and cool.
To mixture stir in sugar and slightly beaten egg.
Sift together and add flour, salt, baking soda, cinnamon, nutmeg, allspice and cloves to mixture.
Stir in chopped walnuts. Pour into greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake in 375° oven for 12 minutes or done.
When cool dust with confectioners sugar or frost.

title: quick skillet
directions: Brown beef and onion in oil.
Drain.
Stir in water and next 5 ingredients.
Add macaroni; mix well.
Bring mixture to boil, then reduce heat to low.
Simmer, uncovered, 15 to 20 minutes, stirring occasionally until macaroni is tender.
Garnish with minced parsley, if desired.
Makes 5 servings.

title: pickled mushrooms
directions: Combine all ingredients, except onions and mushrooms.
Add them, then cover and store in refrigerator 8 hours.
Drain just before serving.

title: fat cake
directions: Bake cake in 11 x 13-inch pan at 350° for time specified on box.
Cool about 20 minutes.
Mix cream cheese, Dream Whip, pudding and milk until thick.
Spread on top of cooled cake. Spread crushed pineapple on top of cream cheese mixture.
Top with Cool Whip and crushed nuts.

title: broccoli pierre
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place uncooked broccoli in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Mix onion, soup, sour cream and Parmesan cheese.
Spread over broccoli.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake for 35 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown meat with onion and green chilies in Dutch oven.
Drain off excess oil.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil, then simmer 30 minutes.
Makes 10 servings.
Add bread and a salad to make a quick, filling and warm meal on a cold day!

title: toting casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a 3-quart baking dish; cook and drain noodles.
Melt butter, saute meat, stir in tomato sauce and flour; simmer 10 minutes.
Combine cottage cheese, sour cream, salt, onion, green pepper and olives.
Put half the noodles in baking dish.
Spread on all the cottage cheese mixture.
Top with remaining noodles and cover with ground meat mixture.
Bake for 30 minutes; let stand about 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 10.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown hamburger and bacon; drain grease off and add onion. Brown until golden.
Add rest of ingredients; pour into 2 1/2-quart casserole or crock-pot.
Cook in crock-pot 2 hours or in casserole in 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Mix beaten egg with milk, persimmon pulp and vanilla.
Stir liquid mixture into dry ingredients.
Add melted shortening.
Pour into a well-greased baking dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 minutes.

title: banana surprise
directions: Mix well first 5 ingredients.
Add the dry ingredients and mix well.
Add nuts and raisins.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until tester comes out clean.
Bake in 10-inch greased tube pan. Cool 20 minutes and turn out on plate and dust with powdered sugar.

title: grilled snacks
directions: Spread crackers with peanut butter; scatter marshmallows on top.
Place low under broiler to heat and brown lightly.
Serve at once.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes.
When done, slice in half lengthwise while still hot.
Scoop out potato from skin.
Combine potato insides in a large bowl with desired amounts of remaining ingredients.
Stuff potato skins with potato mixture.
Thirty minutes before serving, reheat in oven at 350°.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Cook potatoes and carrots in the juices from the canned vegetables until tender. Saute the hamburger with the onions and garlic, drain well. Place the hamburger into the pot with the potatoes and carrots, add the tomato sauce and vegetables. Add worcestershire sauce, cilantro, and bay leaf. (Can also add rosemary, thyme, or other herbs to taste.) Let soup simmer for about an hour. It ends up being more of a stew than a soup. Great with cornbread.

title: caramel pie
directions: Place sugar
in a heavy skillet and caramelize over low heat. (Cook
until
melted
and
of
a rich brown color.	The caramelized sugar
will
harden
and be a rich brown color and looks almost
like	it
would never dissolve, but it does when added
to
the milk, flour and egg mixture.) Combine milk, egg yolks
and flour; stir in caramelized sugar.
Cook over medium heat
until mixture thickens, stirring constantly.	Add margarine. Cool
and top with meringue.
Bake at 325° for about 15 or 20 minutes to brown the meringue.

title: italian zucchini
directions: Cook the zucchini in boiling, salted water until tender. Drain.
In saucepan, saute the onion and celery in butter until soft.
Combine all the ingredients and mix well.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Transfer to a lightly buttered casserole and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat first 7 ingredients together, then add remaining dry ingredients and mix together.
It's best to beat by hand.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken elegance
directions: Cover chicken with water.
Put in generous amounts of onions, celery, carrots, parsley, salt and pepper.
Let simmer until tender, about 45 minutes.
Reserve 1 1/2 cups of broth.
Mix chicken, cut in bite size pieces, mushroom soup and sour cream; put into casserole bottom.
Heat broth and butter; add to stuffing and mix until moist.
Spread on top of chicken.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Combine shortening, onion, pepper, celery and drained mushrooms in a skillet.
Cook until limp.
Add rest of ingredients (including mushroom liquid), except shrimp.
Cover and simmer slowly for 30 minutes.
Add raw shrimp.
Return to boil and simmer.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sausage and mushroom casserole
directions: The night before:
Sprinkle roast heavily with garlic salt and black pepper.
Roll in flour.
Wrap in tinfoil; refrigerate overnight.

title: lemon squares i
directions: Beat egg whites until soft mounds are formed.
Add the powdered sugar gradually.
Beat until stiff; set aside.
Cream butter and sugar well.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt; add alternately with lemon juice, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Add lemon rind and pecans.
Gently fold in beaten egg whites and pour into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Frost while still warm; sprinkle with chopped pecans.

title: apple salad
directions: Cut up apples in bowl.
Add diced cheese.
Add pineapple and nuts.
Place pineapple juice in saucepan.
Beat egg up, then add sugar and cornstarch or flour.
Add to juice and cook until it boils.
Let cool.
Pour over apples and serve.

title: ed's barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Use a wire whisk to mix well.
Use funnel to pour back into catsup bottles.
Keeps well. Yummy!

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix in order listed, all dry ingredients a little at a time. Add eggs one at a time.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Use 3 greased loaf pans.

title: brown sugar pumpkin pie
directions: Combine pumpkin, brown sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and allspice. Add eggs and mix well.
Gradually add evaporated milk; blend thoroughly.
Pour into pie shell and bake in a 425° oven for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 35 to 45 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: graham cracker torte
directions: Whip cream, sugar and rum together.
Arrange 9 crackers in a square.
Spread with a thin layer of cream and top with slices of banana.
Repeat layering 4 times.
Top with another layer of graham crackers.
Frost with remaining cream and decorate with nuts and cherries.

title: pudding cake(very easy and very good.)
directions: Pour prepared cherry pie filling into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread evenly.
Spread crushed pineapple.
Sift yellow cake mix over the cherries and the pineapple.
Put pats of butter evenly over the top.
Sprinkle the nuts on the mixture and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: homemade bread
directions: Crumble yeast into small bowl.
Add lukewarm water and 1 teaspoon sugar.
Set in warm place until it becomes light and spongy (about 15 minutes).
Combine Spry, 2 tablespoons sugar and 1 teaspoon salt in a large bowl.
Add scalded milk and water. Stir until Spry is melted.
Cool until lukewarm.
Add yeast mixture.
Add flour gradually, making a stiff dough.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix ingredients together until stiff.
Bake at 325° until brown.

title: cannoli dip
directions: Cut wonton squares into thirds.
Heat butter-flavored Crisco (shortening); brown wontons and drain on paper towels.
Mix cheese, powdered sugar, vanilla, chocolate chips, nuts and dash of green food coloring (for a pistachio effect) to create dip. Sprinkle powdered sugar on wontons.

title: country chicken and potato bake
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Cut unpeeled potatoes into 1 1/2-inch chunks.
Finely chop onion.
In large roasting pan, toss potatoes and onion with chicken, salt, pepper and rosemary.
Arrange the chicken pieces skin side up.
Bake uncovered one hour or until potatoes are tender and browned and juices run clear when chicken is pierced, basting with pan drippings occasionally.
Serves 8.

title: english muffin bread
directions: Mix together 3 cups of flour, yeast, sugar, salt and baking soda.
Heat milk and water to warm; add to dry ingredients.
Mix well with an electric mixer.
Stir in the remaining flour.
Oil 2 bread pans; sprinkle with cornmeal.
Divide mixture into the 2 pans; let rise 45 minutes.
(Cover loosely while rising.)
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: baker's frosting
directions: Boil water and sugar one minute. Set aside to cool.
Beat powdered sugar, cornstarch and egg whites with water and sugar mixtures. Add shortening and flavoring.
Beat until creamy. Will keep a week or two in a covered container in the refrigerator.

title: date-nut bread
directions: Mix dates, sugar, butter and water.
Let cool.
Add other ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: orange cream shake
directions: Put half of ice cream and half of orange juice in blender. Add 3 ice cubes and blend 1 minute at high speed until mixture is smooth and creamy.
Pour mixture into a large mug.
Repeat with remaining ingredients.
Garnish with orange slices, if desired.

title: 3-bean hamburger bake
directions: *Do not drain canned beans.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa; beat eggs.
Add all ingredients to cocoa mixture.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell and cook at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Let stand a few hours or overnight.
Serve with rye bread.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Brown beef in small amount of fat.
Mix all ingredients and pour into pastry shell.
Spread cheese topping over filling.

title: sally lunn muffins
directions: Cream shortening and
sugar.
Combine eggs and milk and add to mixture.
Add baking
powder
and salt to flour and add to mixture.
"Pam" muffins
pans
and pour batter in.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Stir sugar and cornstarch together in saucepan. Blend in pineapple.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
While hot, pour over fruit. Refrigerate, uncovered, until mixture cools.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together. Drop by teaspoon full on ungreased cookie sheets. Criss-cross each with a fork. Bake at 350 degrees for 8-12 minutes.

title: smoky salmon dip
directions: Mix thoroughly and chill.
Cover with minced parsley and nuts if desired.
Serve with crackers.

title: sailboater's sea breeze
directions: Because on a boat, it's not always easy to keep fruit juices for cocktails..........

title: dollys
directions: Melt butter in 8-inch square pan.
In layers, add the following:
graham cracker crumbs, coconut, chocolate morsels and nuts.
Cover all with condensed milk.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Cool for 15 minutes in refrigerator.
Cut up into small squares.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix rice and soups in baking dish (approximately 10 x 13-inch).
Wash out each soup can with 1/3 cup water and add.
Put chicken, which has been dipped in oil or melted margarine, on top of rice.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: squash casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat with onions and garlic salt.
Layer in casserole dish in this order: hamburger meat, squash, both soups, cheese and cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate sundae cookies
directions: Sift together first 3 ingredients; set aside.
Add brown sugar to shortening.
Blend in egg.
Stir in half the dry ingredients. Add cherry juice and 2 tablespoons milk; stir in remaining dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Blend in chocolate, walnuts and cherries. Drop by rounded teaspoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cut marshmallows in half and place on hot cookies.

title: party mix
directions: Combine the Corn Chex, Rice Chex, pretzels and nuts together in a large roasting pan. Combine and mix well the oil, brown sugar, Worcestershire sauce and garlic salt. Pour over the cereal, pretzel and nuts mixture and toss to coat. Bake at 250° for 1 1/2 hours, stirring frequently.

title: oven barbecued hawaiian chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a small bowl combine crushed pineapple with juice, chili sauce, apricot preserves, brown sugar, soy sauce and cornstarch.
Mix well.
Remove skin and fat from chicken except wings.
Arrange chicken in 15 1/2 or 10 1/2-inch roasting pan lined with foil.
Spoon pineapple mixture over chicken.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes, basting occasionally with pan drippings until juice runs clear when chicken is pierced.
Cut pineapple into quarters, then into eight 3/4-inch slices.

title: million dollar pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar thoroughly.
Add eggs, one at a time, alternating with flour, milk and flavoring.
Bake at 325° for about 90 minutes or longer in a tube pan.
Makes 1.

title: southern yam pineapple casserole
directions: Beat all together, except marshmallows.
In a buttered baking dish, place 1/2 mixture.
Top with 1/2 marshmallows, then add remaining mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry nut bread
directions: Cream the butter, sugar, vanilla and lemon extract until fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each.
Sift flour, salt, cream of tartar and soda.
Combine jam and sour cream.
Add jam mixture alternately with dry ingredients.
Stir in nuts.
Divide among 5 greased and floured 4 1/2 x 2 3/4-inch pans. Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: beets and eggs
directions: Cook beet juice, allspice, vinegar, and water till hot. Place eggs and beets in a large jar and pour hot liquid over them. Refrigerate a day before serving.

title: crispy baked fish fillets
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.
Wash and dry fillets and cut into serving pieces.
Season, dip in oil and coat with cornflake crumbs.
Arrange in a single layer in a lightly oiled shallow-baking dish.
Bake 10 minutes without turning or basting. Yield:
4 servings.
Approximately 260 calories per serving.
No taste of cornflakes.

title: sour cream coconut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Beat well for 3 minutes.
Bake at 350° in 9 x 13 x 2 pan for 30 to 35 minutes or until done in middle.

title: cherry "dump" cake
directions: Layer the ingredients in an oblong Pyrex dish in the order given, pouring the melted oleo over the cake mix.
Bake in 325° oven for 30 to 45 minutes or until brown.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Brown pork chops in skillet.
In oblong baking dish, mix water with onion soup mix and add mushroom soup and rice.
Place pork chops on top.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 400°.

title: mexican fiesta dip
directions: Combine sour cream and taco seasoning mix - set aside. Spread refried beans into dish then spoon sour cream mixture over beans.
Layer with remaining ingredients.
Serve with chips.
Can be prepared without lettuce & tomato if desired.

title: apricot cream cheese cookies
directions: Combine margarine, sugar and softened cream cheese, mixing until well blended.
Blend in eggs, lemon juice and rind.
Add combined dry ingredients; mix well.
Chill for several hours. Shape level tablespoons of dough into balls.
Place on greased cookies sheet; flatten slightly, indent centers and fill with preserve.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
When cool, sprinkle with confectioners sugar, if desired.
Yields 6 dozen.

title: english crumpets
directions: Add flour to lukewarm milk.
Beat until smooth.
Add salt, butter and yeast.
Beat well.
Let rise until double.
Place greased muffin rings on hot griddle (1/2 fill with dough); cook until batter sets, then turn.
Makes 24 Crumpets.

title: easy lemon pie
directions: In a mixing bowl combine all ingredients, saving 1/2 of the Cool Whip.
Beat until smooth.
Spread remaining Cool Whip on top of pies.
Refrigerate before serving.
Pies are good frozen, too.

title: vinegar and oil dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cover tightly and shake well.
Makes 3 cups dressing.

title: peach crisp
directions: 1. Drain peaches.
Arrange peach slices in an ungreased 8-inch square pan; set aside.

title: kukune lubia sabz(string bean casserole)
directions: Cook string beans.
Saute the onions and the meat in butter for 20 minutes.
Add the string beans to the meat mixture.
Cook slightly.
Add half the spices and sugar to the meat mixture. Beat the eggs slightly and add the rest of the spices and the sugar to the eggs.
Mix well.
Pour the beaten eggs over the meat and string bean mixture.
Add the lemon juice and mix well. Grease the bottom of a 10-inch pie pan.
Pour the mixture in the pan and cook in a 325° preheated oven for 45 minutes.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: cookie pizza
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix sugar, margarine, vanilla and egg. Stir in flour, baking soda and chocolate chips.
Dough will be stiff.
Spread or pat dough in an ungreased 12-inch pizza pan or cookie sheet.
Bake about 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Let it cool.
Just before serving, spread on whipped topping. Sprinkle with walnuts, coconut and candies.
Cut into wedges. Refrigerate any remaining cookie.

title: pesto torte("to pie for")
directions: In food processor, blend basil leaves, garlic and pine nuts until a paste is formed.
While the processor is running, add the oil.
Add Parmesan cheese last and do not overblend.
Remove from processor.
In Kitchen Aid, beat butter and cream cheese until light and fluffy (5 minutes).
Push down sides from line to line. Line a mold pan or empty 5 pound cottage cheese or sour cream container with Saran Wrap (film), overhang the sides.
Carefully put in 1/3 of butter mixture, then 1/2 of Pesto, etc., until both are gone.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Can be made 4 days ahead.

title: french onion soup
directions: Saute onions in butter and oil for 20 minutes.
Add flour, salt, pepper, sugar and broth.
Simmer for 20 minutes or longer. Cut bread into wedges.
Sprinkle garlic, paprika and oregano on. Put under broiler 1 to 2 minutes until brown.
Fill bowl with soup, add bread and top with cheese.
Put under broiler or in microwave 30 seconds to one minute.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Peel apples and quarters. Roll each quarter in roll, starting at the little end. Place in greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Place extra apples between the rolls. Melt margarine in microwave and add sugar and cinnamon; mix. Spoon over the apple rolls. Pour Sprite around edges and around extra apples. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Serve with vanilla ice cream.

title: cheese and macaroni loaf
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Add remaining ingredients and place in greased baking dish.

title: tomato basil corn muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 475 degrees. Grease muffin tins. Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Fill each section in muffin tin about 2/3 full.
Bake for about 15 to 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
This should make about 18 muffins.

title: basil vinaigrette dressing
directions: In jar with lid combine all ingredients.
Shake well.
Store refrigerated.

title: anne's cheese spread for fish
directions: Broil fish (steaks take 10 minutes per inch and 5 minutes on each side).
Mix topping.
Spread on top of broiled fish.
Broil until brown and bubbly.

title: low-fat cheese cake
directions: Combine milk with gelatin in a 4-cup microwave bowl.
Beat in egg whites, food coloring and sugar.
Cook in microwave, uncovered, 3 to 3 1/2 minutes.
Stir after each minute.
Continue until mixture is thickened and creamy.
Put cottage cheese and vanilla in blender.
Blend until smooth.
Add custard mix and blend.
Pour into crust.
Refrigerate for three hours or overnight.

title: ham and cheese potato bake
directions: Mix hash browns, ham, 1/2 cup cheese and onion.
In another bowl, combine sour cream, soups and pepper.
Add to potato mix. Mix well.
Put in a 3 quart greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for approximately an hour or until potatoes are tender.

title: chicken squares
directions: Mix together and pour into buttered 9 inch pan and bake 350 degrees for 55 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onions until tender.
Warm canned ingredients together in large Dutch oven, then add Velveeta cheese and cook until cheese is melted.
Add hamburger and onions; stir together.
Cut tortillas in pieces; place in large casserole dish, enough to cover bottom.
Layer with hamburger mixture.
Repeat layers until all is used.
Bake at 350° until warm through.
This makes a lot and freezes well.

title: granola
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour; turn over and watch closely.
Allow baked mixture to cool completely, then crumble.
Add nuts and chips.
Store in covered container in refrigerator.

title: spiced black beans
directions: Soak beans overnight. Drain. Rinse. Stud the onion with cloves.
Place all ingredients in a large Dutch oven and bring to a boil. Reduce to simmer and cook until tender, about 1 1/2 hours. Remove onion, carrot, celery and cilantro. Serve on rice.

title: pickle roll-ups
directions: Mix together with electric mixer the ingredients, with exception of beef, until smooth and spreadable.
Separate beef slices and spread a little cheese mixture between 2 slices. Spread a thin layer of cheese mix on top piece of beef and put a dill spear on one end and roll up beef around pickle.
Cut each one into 3 pieces.

title: cranberry-orange pineapple punch
directions: Mix cranberry juice and the orange-pineapple juice together. Add Sprite or 7-Up to taste just before serving.

title: zucchini nut bread(1 loaf)
directions: In a mixing bowl, stir together flour, cinnamon, baking soda, salt, nutmeg and baking powder; set aside.
In another bowl, beat together sugar, zucchini and egg.
Add oil and lemon peel; mix well.
Stir flour mixture into zucchini mixture.
Gently fold in chopped nuts. Turn batter into greased 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until wooden pick inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove from pan; cool thoroughly on a rack.
Freezes well.

title: strawberry cheese pie
directions: In large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into pastry shell.
Chill 3 hours or until set. Top with strawberries and glaze.
Ready to eat.

title: garlic dills
directions: Bring to boil and pour on cucumbers that have been put in a jar with 1 bay leaf, dill and a pinch of alum.

title: erin's chicken
directions: Saute 1/2 strips of cut up chicken 3 to 5 minutes with onion. Add white wine and sour cream.
Heat.
Add grapes; heat 3 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine fruit into a bowl; mix.
Add lemon yogurt and lemon juice until fruit is covered.
Add nutmeg.
You may serve immediately or chill for 30 minutes.

title: dirt
directions: Put cookies through blender to make crumbs.
Put crumbs 1-inch deep in container (new flowerpot with a liner makes a cute dessert centerpiece).
Make pudding as directed.
Beat cream cheese and fold in pudding.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Put mixture on top of 1-inch crumbs.
Put rest of crumbs on top.

title: beef lentil soup
directions: Cook washed lentils in the 10 cups water for 1 hour.
Add seasonings and other ingredients.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Serve hot with fresh rolls or Italian bread.

title: grape-nut pudding
