directions: Place in saucepan the water, tapioca, brown sugar, salt and raisins.
Cook until transparent (about 10 minutes).
Take from stove and add grape-nuts, walnuts and vanilla.
Pour into 4 individual dessert dishes to cool.
Serve with whipped cream or Kool Whip.

title: bacon blue cheese dip
directions: Combine Blue cheese, cream cheese, wine and onion.
Beat until fluffy.
Stir in sour cream.
Chill.
To serve, stir in bacon and serve with assorted crackers.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Mix milk, sugar, butter, vanilla and nuts together.
Roll into small balls and let stand for a while.
Melt paraffin wax and chocolate in small pan.
Dip balls into and coat well.
Make sure wax and chocolate are not too hot.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and pour into greased casserole. Mix brown sugar, flour, 1/2 stick oleo and nuts.
Pour over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Lightly grease 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Place ripe bananas in large mixing bowl; mash slightly with a fork.
Add oil, sugar and eggs.
Using electric mixer, beat together until smooth.
Sift all dry ingredients into banana mixture; stir until well combined.
Fold in the vanilla and chopped walnuts.
Pour batter into baking pan.
Bake 60 minutes or until skewer inserted in center comes out clean.

title: turkey parmesan
directions: On waxed paper, mix flour, salt and pepper.
On another sheet of waxed paper mix bread crumbs and Locatelli cheese.
In pie plate with fork, beat egg and 2 tablespoons water.
Coat turkey cutlets with flour mixture, egg mixture then crumbs.

title: pepperoni rolls
directions: Mix dough and put in greased bowl to rise.
(I let it rise 3 times.)
Divide into balls about the size of golf balls.
Put spoon of pizza sauce on cutting board and press ball of dough to make it flat.
Put spoon of sauce on it and pepperoni and cheese, if you want, and roll up.
Put side by side on greased cookie sheet.
After pan is full, brush top with pizza sauce.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Brush with oleo and let cool.
Makes about 200 rolls.

title: potato casserole
directions: Spread margarine in bottom of large, oblong baking dish. Place frozen potatoes in dish.
Mix onion, soup and sour cream with potatoes, then mix in 1/2 of bag of cheese.
Sprinkle the remaining cheese on top of potato mixture and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: apple cinnamon salad
directions: Add 1/2 cup boiling water to cinnamon candies.
Stir to dissolve and add 1 1/2 cups boiling water to Jell-O.
Stir to dissolve.
Add candies.
Add ice cubes and stir until dissolved and add apples and celery.
Chill until firm.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large casserole dish.

title: mincemeat cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Beat butter, sugar and egg and add dry ingredients.
Stir in fruit mixture and nuts.
Bake on a lightly greased cookie sheet at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Combine and blend all ingredients until smooth.
Grease and flour a Bundt-type pan and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: panic mousse(when you need a fast dessert)
directions: Scald milk.
Do not boil.
Put egg and all other ingredients into blender.
Pour scalded milk over ingredients in blender and blend on High for 1 full minute.
Chill for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix peanut butter, powdered sugar, Rice Krispies, margarine and vanilla all together.
Form a ball.

title: grandma's buttermilk cake
directions: Beat egg whites; add 3/4 cup sugar and vanilla.
Set aside. Cream butter and sugar; cream well.
Add egg yolks one at a time. Beat well.
Fold in flour and soda, alternating with buttermilk. Cream in egg whites.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
This recipe can be frozen for later use.

title: pepper steak
directions: Spray skillet with Pam cooking spray.
Saute onion and stir in steak strips.
Simmer for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Stir in Worcestershire sauce and tomato sauce.
Add just enough water to sauce.
Thirty minutes before serving, add pepper.
Serve over rice.

title: zucchini pancakes("less oily and starchy")
directions: Combine ingredients.
Heat 2 tablespoons vegetable oil in a heavy skillet.
For each pancake, drop one heaping tablespoon of mixture into oil.
Fry 3 to 5 minutes on each side or until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Add oil when necessary.
Makes 6 to 8 plump pancakes.
Top with low-fat yogurt, flavored with mint and garlic or some prefer with salsa.

title: ultimate turtle cheesecake
directions: Mix crumbs, 1/2 cup of the pecans and butter; press onto bottom and 2-inches up side of 9-inch spring-form pan. Place caramels and milk in small microwavable bowl. Microwave on High 3 minutes or until caramels are completely melted, stirring after each minute. Pour 1/2 of the caramel mixture into crust. Refrigerate 10 minutes. Cover and reserve remaining caramel mixture in refrigerator for later use.

title: johnny margetti
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and garlic.
Add mushrooms and simmer. Cook macaroni and drain.
Add rest of ingredients and pour into 9 x 12-inch pan and top with more grated cheese.
Bake until brown and bubbly.

title: brown betty
directions: Toss crumbs and butter together.
Place bread crumbs on bottom of buttered baking dish.
Spread half of apples over bread crumbs. Sprinkle with sugar and spices and moisten with lemon juice and rind.
Repeat and pour on hot water.
Cover with remaining crumbs.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Layer crushed Ritz crackers in a casserole.
Drain one can of asparagus and place over crumbs.
Pour 1 can of cream of mushroom soup over asparagus.
Top with crackers.
Dot with butter.
Bake 30 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown ground beef, onion, salt and pepper.
Add chili powder, Ro-Tel tomatoes, tomatoes, green beans and corn.

title: black magic cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put dry ingredients together in large bowl.
Add eggs and liquids.
Mix until batter is smooth (batter will be thin).
Pour into well-greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.
(Can also be baked in two 8-inch pans for same amount of time.)

title: hominy casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients except bread crumbs and spoon into a 2 1/2-quart casserole. Sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Combine the egg, milk and salt. Add enough flour to make stiff dough (about 1 cup). Roll very thin on floured surface.
Let stand 20 minutes. Roll up loosely and slice 1/4-inch wide.
Unroll. Spread out and let dry 2 hours.
Drop into boiling soup or boiling salt water and cook, uncovered, about 10 minutes.
Makes 3 cups cooked noodles.

title: fruit-topped cheese pie
directions: Beat cream cheese and sugar until creamy; mix in Cool Whip and spoon into crust.
Add pie filling around edge of pie.
Chill at least 3 hours.
Garnish with additional whipped topping, if desired.

title: cheese sauce
directions: In a pot, melt butter.
Stir in flour; cook for a few minutes. Remove from heat.
Add milk; return to heat and stir until smooth.
Add salt, paprika and cheese.
Stir until cheese is melted.

title: knoxville world's fair chili
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients in a 4 quart pot.
Heat to boiling, stirring.
Lower temperature to simmer.
Cook, stirring occasionally, for 2 to 4 hours.
Serve over Fritos with cheese, lettuce, tomatoes and sour cream.

title: shrimp in hot sauce
directions: Heat wok.
Add butter and melt over medium heat.
When butter begins to sizzle, add shrimp.
Stir-fry about 5 minutes until shrimp are firm and pink.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir until bubbly hot. Serve over rice or with toast.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: aunt ann's sugar cookies
directions: Mix margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Add salt, vanilla, egg, cream of tartar, soda and baking powder.
Mix well.
Add flour and mix well.
Refrigerate at least two hours.
Make small balls about the size of walnuts.
Flatten on cookie sheet with bottom of glass that has been dipped in sugar often.
Do not grease or oil cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet at once.
Frost if desired.
Cookies freeze well in plastic bag.

title: rice broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in margarine for 5 minutes.
Add all other ingredients, stir over heat until cheese is melted.
Bake in casserole dish at 350° for 1 hour on center rack of oven.

title: swiss and chicken casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients, except walnuts. Spoon into 3-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with walnuts.
Bake 35 minutes.

title: cinnamon cake
directions: Mix together first 7 ingredients.
Combine cinnamon and sugar and add.
Pour into greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Sprinkle powdered sugar on top.

title: golden punch
directions: Combine juice, sugar and water in large bowl.
Let stand 30 minutes.
When ready to serve, add ginger ale.
Yields 32 to 40 servings.

title: robbie's blackberry cobbler
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening. Add milk and form dough.
Roll out dough approximately 1/4 inch thick.
Place 3 cups blackberries over dough and roll up like jelly roll.
Melt 1 stick butter in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cut dough into 1 1/2-inch slices and place in pan.
Dissolve the 2 cups of sugar in 2 cups water.
Pour over dough slices in pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours or until golden brown on top.

title: fish in horseradish(fisk i pepperrot)
directions: Make a sauce of sour cream, horseradish, salt, pepper and sugar.
Add fish and mix gently.
Serve salad cold on lettuce, garnished with egg and tomato wedges.

title: creamed onions and mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.

Slice onions and put in an 8-inch square baking dish. Slice mushrooms and spread over onions. Spread cream of celery soup over the mushrooms. Sprinkle with pepper. Top with bread crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake 30 minutes. Easy to make using a food processor.

title: date and nut bread(serves 20)
directions: Pour boiling water over chopped dates. Add baking soda and let cool. Cream butter, sugar, salt and eggs. Beat and mix with cooled dates, flour, vanilla and nuts. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix; put into pie shells (2).
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 325°.

title: microwave tyrolean fish fillets
directions: In 2-quart oblong glass baking dish, combine onion and butter. Microwave on High 3 to 4 minutes or until tender.
Stir in soup, wine, cheese, lemon juice and parsley.
Arrange fish in soup mixture.
Spoon over fish. Sprinkle with bread crumbs and paprika. Microwave, uncovered, on High 12 to 14 minutes or until fish flakes, turning dish once halfway through cooking.
Let stand 2 minutes before serving.
Makes 4 servings.

title: icebox chocolate pie
directions: Spray pie pan with Pam.
Mix first 3 ingredients.
Put this mixture in pie pan.
Take your hand and smooth it out.
Put it in oven and cook for 10 minutes at 350°. Let crust cool completely.
Next, mix cream cheese, powdered white sugar and Cool Whip.
Mix well and spread on top of crust.
Next, mix pudding and pie mix and milk.
Mix well and put on top of cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip mixture in crust.
Then add Cool Whip on top of this and put in freezer for awhile.
Take out and serve.

title: bean salad
directions: Mix together vegetables.
Combine vinegar, oil and sugar. Stir together.
Pour over vegetables.
Mix and refrigerate overnight (24 hours).
Drain.
Serve cold.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Mix ground beef, Kraft Old English cheese and marinara sauce. Stuff shells with sauce and pour remaining sauce over shells in baking dish.
Grate Mozzarella and Cheddar cheese over top.
Bake about 15 minutes at 350°.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs until light and fluffy.
Beat in vanilla and bananas.
Add flour mixture (flour, baking soda and salt) and beat until blended.
Add water.
Beat to blend.
Stir in cinnamon.
Add raisins and walnuts, if desired. Turn into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.
Turn on rack to cool.
Makes 1 loaf, 18 slices.

title: chocolate cookies
directions: Melt butter with cocoa or chocolate.
Add sugar, flour, nuts, baking powder, vanilla and eggs.
Mix well and chill for 1 hour. Roll into small balls and roll in powdered sugar.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 12 to 15 minutes at 325°.

title: german potato salad
directions: Put sliced potatoes and sliced onions in alternate layers in bowl.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste.
Pour over all 1/2 cup boiling water and fold lightly.
Try not to mash your potatoes.
Fry out the diced bacon and pour over the top (if too much grease, add just enough for taste).

title: glorious taco mess
directions: Put all in a large crock-pot and simmer for 2 hours.
It can be cooked all day in a crock-pot on low.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs in large bowl.
Add oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla. Combine dry ingredients. Add to egg mixture.
Blend well. Add nuts.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tomato soup
directions: Cook tomatoes until
soft;
run under sieve (strainer). Cook onions and celery
in
oleo until soft.
Add all ingredients after putting tomatoes through the sieve (strainer).
Add 12 to 14 tablespoons
of cornstarch to boiling tomatoes (mix a little water
to cornstarch) before adding to tomatoes.
Cook 15 minutes on low setting.
Jar and seal.

title: cape cod lobster newburg
directions: Cut lobster into bite size pieces; toss in flour.
Saute in butter for 3 minutes.
Add wine; cook for 1 minute.
Add cream, salt and pepper.
Add egg yolks and stir.
Cook just under boiling point until thick.
If allowed to bubble, Newburg may break.
Serve on golden brown toast.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: Cook vegetables until tender in water.
Mix flour and 1/2 cup milk and stir into the potatoes.
Stir until smooth.
Add remaining milk and cheese and heat until thick.

title: nuts and bolts
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Melt butter and Worcestershire sauce together; add seasonings.
Pour over remaining ingredients and stir every 15 minutes for 1 hour.
Turn out on paper towel to cool completely before storing.
Makes about 1 gallon.

title: iced tea punch
directions: Place tea in glass or earthenware tea pot.
Add boiling water; cover and steep 5 minutes.
Strain tea into punch bowl or pitcher. Add sugar; stir until dissolved.
Add orange and lemon juices. Chill.
Add club soda.
Place crushed ice into punch bowl or pitcher.
Yields 10 punch cup servings.

title: grandmother's pecan pie
directions: Combine sugar and corn syrup in small saucepan; bring to boil. Beat eggs at medium speed of electric mixer until blended. Gradually add hot sugar mixture to eggs, beating constantly.
Stir in butter, vanilla and pecans.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: coconut drop cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Mix in egg, vanilla and salt.
Add flour in 4 parts, mixing well after each addition.
Stir in coconut.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheet. Flatten with floured bottom of a glass.
Sprinkle with coconut, if desired.
Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 4 1/2 dozen.

title: molasses sugar cookies
directions: Melt shortening in a 3 quart saucepan over low heat.
Remove from heat; let cool.
Add sugar, molasses and egg.
Mix well. Sift together flour, soda, cloves, ginger and cinnamon.
Add to first mixture.
Mix well and chill.
Form into 1-inch balls and roll in granulated sugar.
Place on well greased cookie sheet. Mash each cookie with glass bottom dipped in sugar.
Bake in 375° oven 8 to 10 minutes.
Delicious warm or anytime.

title: rice and mushroom casserole
directions: Saute onions and mushrooms in butter.
Add consomme and water. Add rice and stir.
Season.
Bake in greased casserole, covered, in moderate oven at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: sour cream bars
directions: Mix together with hands the following ingredients:
yellow cake mix, margarine, 1 egg and pecans.
Mix until it is a dough. In a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan, press dough until level. Sprinkle chocolate chips over dough.
With a mixer mix cream cheese, 2 eggs and sugar together until smooth.
Pour over top of mixture.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat the eggs.
Add the sugar, oil, nutmeg, cinnamon and salt. Mix well and add the pumpkin, water and baking soda.
Mix well and add the flour, vanilla and nuts (optional).
Grease and flour 3 tall 1 pound coffee cans.
Fill 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Makes 3 loaves.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Put frosting in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, egg and powdered sugar together and spread over frosting.
Mix cake mix according to directions on box and pour over cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Take out of oven and let set 3 minutes.
Loosen edges with a knife and turn upside-down and leave for five minutes before removing from pan.
Should be stored in refrigerator.

title: favorite meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients except for 1/2 cup of tomato sauce or puree.
In a 13 x 9-inch baking pan, shape into a loaf.
Pour the 1/2 cup of tomato sauce or puree over top of loaf until covered.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour or until done. Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Serve with horseradish. Yields 8 servings.

title: pear pie
directions: Combine flour, sugar and coconut.
Add oleo.
Stir and set aside.
Put 1 cup pears in pie shell.
Top with coconut mixture. Repeat layers until mixture is gone.
Cover pie with aluminum foil.
Bake for 10 minutes at 450°.
Remove foil and reduce heat to 350°.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: chile pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease a 10-inch pie pan or casserole dish.
Cut chiles open and line pie pan, allowing top of chile to come to top edge of pan.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: To potatoes, add sugar, salt and flour; put into greased oven dish. Slightly beat eggs; add to milk. Add bourbon if wanted. If not, add 1 teaspoon grated orange rind and enough juice to taste. Pour this over potatoes; dot with butter. Bake 1 hour at 300° or until set. Serve hot or cold.

title: baked chicken parmesan
directions: In a paper bag, place seasonings, cheese, parsley and crumbs; coat chicken by shaking a few pieces at a time in the bag.

title: reese's cups
directions: Mix butter, peanut butter, graham cracker crumbs and powdered sugar well.
May have to stir for a while to mix thoroughly.
Pack in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Heat chocolate chips with small amount of water (can microwave).
Spread over peanut butter mixture.
Chill and cut into squares.

title: baked acorn squash
directions: Bake acorn squash in 350° oven until semi-tender.
Fill with remaining ingredients and return to oven to cook until squash is tender.
Yield: 3 servings.
Calories: 175.
Diabetic exchanges: 1 starch, 1 fruit and 1 fat.

title: potatoes rosemary
directions: Saute onions and garlic until tender.
Stir in potatoes, seasoned salt, pepper and lemon rind.
Spoon half of mixture in lightly greased 1-1/2 qt.
baking dish.
Sprinkle half of the cheese.
Repeat with remaining potato mixture and cheese.
Stir together bread crumbs, butter and Rosemary.
Sprinkle over top. Bake covered at 400 degrees for 40 minutes.
Uncover and bake another 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: beef-rice italiano(yield: 4 servings)
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients in large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat until meat is browned and vegetables are tender, stirring to crumble meat.
Drain well; return mixture to pan.
Add Italian seasoning, tomatoes, and broth; bring to a boil.
Stir in rice.
Cover and remove for heat.
Lets stand 15 minutes.
Stir well before serving.

title: baked chicken
directions: Place chicken pieces in single layer in baking dish.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Top each piece with 1/4 strip of bacon.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
(Add 10 minutes for bone-in.)
Mix water, soup, sour cream, mushrooms and seasoning. Heat to boiling.
Remove covering from chicken and pour hot mixture over the top.
Return to oven and bake 20 minutes (uncovered). Remove chicken pieces to serving dish (20 minutes).
Remove chicken.
Make sauce or gravy from drippings.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients throughly.
Best if put in blender.

title: rhubarb upside-down cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Arrange rhubarb in an 8-inch baking dish.
Combine sugar, flour, orange peel and cinnamon.
Sprinkle on top of rhubarb.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Brown chicken in a little oil and butter in Dutch oven.
In a casserole, put the rice, broth and seasoning mix.
Lay chicken on top. Cover and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: grandma's sugar cookies
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
together making firm dough.
Roll out and cut with cookie cutter.
Bake in hot 450° oven for 6 to 8 minutes.
Sprinkled with colored sugar looks nice.

title: peanut brittle
directions: This recipe for peanut brittle is very crunchy, not hard like most.
The reason is the amount of butter used.
This candy will not make if raining.
Cook sugar, syrup and water over high heat, stirring constantly until it threads, about 10 to 12 minutes. Sometimes a little longer just until it threads real good.
Add oleo and raw peanuts; continue to cook, stirring constantly until mixture turns darker in color and the peanuts start to crack, about 10 minutes.
Sometimes peanuts will not crack.
At once put in 1 heaping teaspoon soda and stir well.
Pour onto buttered cookie sheets while still foaming, spread thin.
Let cool and break into pieces.

title: egg and sausage casserole
directions: Mix together in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Place all ingredients (except tofu and lemon juice) into mixing bowl and gently mix together.

title: strawberry ice cream
directions: Scald 2 cups milk.
Add sugar and other ingredients (including rest of milk).
Chill.
Pour into churn.
Finish filling with milk and churn.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat sugar and oil.
Add eggs.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Pour into
2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes to 1 hour.

title: weekend punch
directions: Combine in punch bowl.
Draw off enough to fill ice cube tray and freeze.
Refrigerate bowl until well chilled.
Before serving, add 25 ounces chilled ginger ale or Sprite.
Float ice cubes in punch bowl.

title: lasagna casserole
directions: First:
Brown and drain sausage and ground meat.
Add next 6 ingredients and simmer.

title: zucchini and tomato bake
directions: Place zucchini in a 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with 1/2 each of soy sauce, garlic salt, salt and pepper.
Layer tomatoes and onion over zucchini; sprinkle with remaining seasonings.
Top with cheese; dot with margarine.
Cover and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: trudy's fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk in 3-quart saucepan. Bring to full rolling boil, stirring constantly. Continue boiling 5 minutes over medium heat until candy thermometer reaches 234°. Remove from heat. Stir in chocolate pieces until melted. Add Marshmallow Creme, nuts and vanilla. Beat with wooden spoon until well blended. Cool. Cut into squares. (Makes 3 pounds.)

title: corn pudding
directions: Bake for 1/2 hour, covered.
Uncover and brown.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Boil, drain and mash squash.
Mix all ingredients together and put in large 3-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Garnish with paprika and/or parsley.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Cook to soft ball stage.
Add 28 caramels and stir until melted.
Good on yellow cake.

title: mushroom potatoes
directions: Peel and slice enough potatoes to fill 3/4 of a casserole dish; add chopped onion (and/or any other spices to your taste) and penny size (sliced) Polish sausage or beef hot dogs.
Pour 1/4 c. water in dish and cover with Saran Wrap.
Microwave on high for 10 minutes.
Drain off water and pour diluted (with milk) cream of mushroom soup over and mix in.
Bake in oven 1/2 hour at 400°. Cream of celery soup can also be used.

title: little lunch pizzas
directions: Toast English muffin halves on medium toaster setting.
Put muffin halves on cookie sheet.

Top each muffin half with 1 tablespoon pizza sauce, 1 tablespoon shredded Cheddar cheese, 1 tablespoon shredded Mozzarella cheese and pepperoni (if desired). Bake in oven about 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: frankentizers
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook, uncovered.
Cut up hot dogs to bite size pieces and simmer in sauce for 1/2 to 1 hour.
Little sausages may also be used.

title: quick lemon crisps
directions: Combine all ingredients, stirring mixture well. Shape dough into 1-inch balls; place 2-inches apart on ungreased baking sheets. Bake at 350° for 9 minutes or until edges are golden. Makes 4 dozen.

title: gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Drain pineapple; use juice and add enough water to juice to make 1 cup of liquid.
Add vinegar and salt.
Add to jello.
Chill until partially set.
Add pineapple, carrots and nuts.
Chill to set.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix everything adding enough flour to make a soft dough. Roll out on a floured board and cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: picadillo(spicy meat hash)
directions: Saute garlic, onion and pepper in oil for 5 minutes, then add meat and stir until cooked through (approximately 5 minutes). Add the rest of the ingredients and cook for 3 minutes. Use mixture in tortilla shells, empanadas, omelets or just serve with rice. Makes 7 cups. Will fill approximately 12 shells.

title: sour cream rhubarb pie
directions: Place rhubarb in unbaked pie shell.
Pour mixture over rhubarb and bake in a 450° oven for 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: refrigerator dough for cinnamon rolls
directions: In large bowl, combine flour, 1/4 cup sugar, salt and lemon rind.
Cut butter into flour mixture with pastry blender.
Measure warm water into small bowl.
Sprinkle yeast in, stir until dissolved.
Beat eggs with milk; add dissolved yeast and egg mixture to flour mixture. Mix until thoroughly combined. Cover tightly and refrigerate overnight.
Divide dough in half.
Roll half on a well-floured board into an 18 x 12-inch rectangle. Combine sugar with cinnamon; sprinkle half of mixture over dough. Roll up tightly beginning at long side.
Cut roll into 1-inch slices.
Place, cut side up on a greased baking sheet.
Flatten with palm of hand.
Repeat with remaining dough and sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes or until done.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Flatten each chicken breast.
Spread breast on a sheet of wax paper and cover with another sheet.
Using a mallet or edge of saucer, pound each breast until flat, about 1/4-inch thick.
Do not tear chicken.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Top each with a slice of ham.
Cut cheese into 4 bars.
Place a bar of cheese at one short end of each ham.
Fold long edges of cutlet over ends of bar of cheese, then starting at short end of cutlet, roll up, jelly roll style.
To hold each chicken roll together, fasten with string and wooden toothpicks.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Mix all together well and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Test center with toothpick.

title: teresa's dressing
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake in oven at 400° for 1 hour or until hog dogs rise to top and mixture has thickened.

title: bean dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl (except Monterey Jack cheese). Spread in casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese and bake for 20 minutes at 300°.
Serve warm with taco chips.

title: lacey-edged okra cornbread
directions: Mix with enough cold water to make a fairly thin consistency. Fry in hot Crisco, pouring enough batter to make about 3 1/2-inch patties.
Cook until brown on both sides. Serve while hot.

title: sweet and sour chicken or pork
directions: In a crock-pot, mix sauce ingredients in the order given. Carefully stir in meat.
Cook on low at least 5 hours.
Serve over rice.
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: homemade salami(almost like hickory farms)
directions: Mix with hands.
Divide into 3 rolls.
Wrap in Saran Wrap and refrigerate 24 hours.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Wipe with paper towel for excess oil after baked.
Cool and refrigerate.
Enjoy.

title: broccoli-raisin salad
directions: Clean and pare broccoli; blanch and emerse in ice water.
Add bacon, onion and raisins.
Mix together sugar, vinegar and mayonnaise.
Pour over salad and chill.
Red onion can be used for color.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Combine crumbs, sugar and margarine; spread onto bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Combine cream cheese
and sugar mix at medium speed on electric mixer until well blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Blend in chocolate pieces and vanilla and pour over crust.
Bake at 450°
for 10 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 250°
and continue baking for 35 minutes.
Loosen cake from rim of pan; cool before removing rim of pan.
Chill.
Top with 6 ounce package almond brickle chips before baking (optional).
Omit chocolate pieces and top with almond brickle chips before baking (optional).

title: lollie's pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs, then add remaining ingredients.
For chocolate lovers, stir in 1/2 cup chocolate chips.
Pour into uncooked crust.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes until middle is set.

title: hobo dinners
directions: On a large piece of foil (heavy duty), stack patty, onion slices, carrot slices and potatoes.
Season with salt and pepper. Place about 1 to 2 tablespoons butter (in pats) on top of vegetables.
Fold the foil making a package, making sure it is closed as not to leak.
It is best to cook right on charcoal,15 minutes on one side and turn for 12 minutes on other side.
Check for doneness of meat.
This can be cooked in conventional oven at 375 degrees for about 40 minutes.
Makes about four dinners.
Great for campouts.

title: no drink christmas boil
directions: To use:
Put in 1 quart water and simmer.
Do not drink.
This is only to make house smell good.

title: luke's b.b.q. ribs
directions: In roasting pan, place vegetables in bottom of pan and place rack over vegetables. Add enough water to the dry ingredients to make a thin paste. Brush ribs on both sides with paste to cover thickly, place in roasting pan, bake at 300 degrees for 3-4 hours.

title: chicken tenders
directions: Cut chicken into strips about 1 1/2 to 2-inches wide, coat them with the flour seasoned with salt and pepper.
Brown the chicken in a little oil on both sides, remove from pan.
Put chicken back in pan.
Let this cook about 35 minutes.
Mix enough cornstarch and water to thicken the broth that chicken was cooked in.
Take chicken out to thicken, after it is thickened as in gravy, put chicken back into pan to heat.
Serve over rice. Serves 4.

title: garden fresh pizza
directions: Melt oleo in 10-inch nonstick skillet.
Add onion, mushrooms, squash, garlic salt and pepper.
Cook over medium heat 15 to 20 minutes.
Whip eggs; pour over squash mixture and cook over medium heat until eggs are set.
Do not stir.
Layer pepperoni, Cheddar cheese, hot cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Cook about 5 minutes until cheeses are melted.
Serve at once.
Sausage or ground beef may be substituted for pepperoni.

title: biscuit nugget chicken bake
directions: Heat first 6 ingredients until hot and bubbling.
Pour mixture into 8 or 9-inch baking dish.
Separate biscuits and cut into fourths.
Combine last 4 ingredients in a bag.
Shake a few biscuits at a time in the bag.
Arrange over hot mixture. Sprinkle remaining coating over top.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 18 minutes or until biscuits are golden brown.
To reheat, cover loosely with foil.

title: french dressing
directions: In blender, chop onion first; add remaining ingredients. Blend 3 minutes.

title: cranberry peach cobbler
directions: Combine pie filling and cranberry sauce.
Spoon mixture into lightly greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Set aside.
Combine cake mix, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Cut in butter with a pastry blender until mixture is crumbly.
Stir in pecans.
Sprinkle crumb mixture evenly over fruit mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden and bubbly.
Serve with vanilla ice cream, if desired.

title: pizza pancakes
directions: In a large bowl, combine the biscuit mix and the Italian seasoning. Combine eggs and milk; stir into dry ingredients just until moistened. Fold in the cheese, pepperoni, tomatoes and green peppers. Pour batter by 1/4 cupfuls onto a lightly greased hot griddle. Turn when bubbles form on top. Cook until the second side is golden brown. Serve with pizza sauce. Yields 14 pancakes.

title: cloverleaf rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over shortening.
When melted, add cold water and salt.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Add eggs, sugar and flour; mix well.
Put into large greased bowl.
Cover with wax paper and towel.
Refrigerate.
Put rolls into greased muffin tin and let rise for 2 1/2 to 3 hours before baking.
Bake to golden brown at 375°.
This dough will keep for up to 6 weeks in the refrigerator.

title: watergate salad
directions: Combine dry pudding with Cool Whip.
Add remaining ingredients (drain all juices).
Chill until firm.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: bacon chicken breasts
directions: Wrap each chicken breast with strip of bacon.
Line casserole dish with chipped beef and pour mixture of sour cream and mushroom soup over chicken.
Bake at 300° for 3 hours or bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tortilla pinwheels
directions: Spread tortillas with other mixed creamy ingredients.
Roll them the long way and chill for 8 hours at least.
Slice crossways with string or serrated knife.

title: orange cookies
directions: Mix everything.
Drop cookies.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: orange muffins
directions: Cut orange in small pieces and place in blender and puree. Place orange juice, orange puree, egg, oil and raisins in bowl. Sift dry ingredients.
Pour orange mixture over dry mixture and stir.
Put in muffin pans.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Shell the eggs and cut in half lengthwise.
Carefully remove the yolks and mash them in a bowl.
Add the remaining ingredients, including enough mayonnaise to keep it all together.
Carefully spoon back into the hard-boiled egg whites.
Serve on a bed of lettuce.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Boil peppers until tender.
Mix other ingredients and stuff peppers.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yields 6 servings.

title: chicken divan
directions: Boil chicken (use two whole breasts).
Remove meat from bones and cut into bite-size pieces and put into casserole dish.
Cook package frozen broccoli or fresh broccoli.
Drain and spread over chicken pieces.
Spread one half can or more cream of celery soup mixed with a little milk (I use the whole can) over chicken.
Put some American cheese over this.
Top with chicken Stove Top stuffing.
Bake in 350°
oven for one half hour or longer, if needed.

title: buttermilk dressing
directions: Put all ingredients into blender and blend, or place in jar and shake well.
Store in refrigerator.
Shake well before using. Great on tossed salads.

title: low-fat manicotti
directions: Cook manicotti and drain. Stir mushrooms and spaghetti sauce together. Spread 1/4 of the sauce in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil until tender. Drain. Run cold water over them. When cool, peel and cut into thin slices.

title: red lobster rolls
directions: Mix first three ingredients and drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet and bake at 350° until brown.
Mix last three ingredients together and brush over rolls while hot.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Wash tomatoes and cut into 3/4-inch slices.
Dip slices into egg and then into bread crumbs.
Melt butter in a large skillet. Add tomato slices.
Cook until golden brown, turning once.
Season to taste.

title: chicken-noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles and drain; add chicken, peas, soup, herbs and seasonings; mix well.
Put in 350° oven until reheated through.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together
butter, sugar and brown sugar; add eggs and vanilla.
Mix together flour, oatmeal, salt, baking powder and baking
soda.
After
the
first
ingredients are mixed together, add
chocolate chips, Hershey bar and nuts.
Drop by spoon on cookie sheet.
Bake for 6 minutes at 400°.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a small bowl, combine flour, Wheatena and baking soda.
In a large bowl, beat butter, date sugar and honey until light and fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla; beat until fluffy.
Add flour mixture; stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake approximately 10 to 12 minutes; makes 5 dozen 2 1/2-inch cookies.

title: easy blueberry cobbler
directions: Place blueberries in a 10x6x2 inch baking dish and sprinkle with lemon juice. combine flour, sugar, and egg; stir until mixture resembles coarse meal. Spread over blueberries. Drizzle melted butter over topping. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Serve warm. Serves 6.

title: sour cream potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes, celery and onion in water in covered pan until tender; do not drain.
Press through sieve or mash well.
Add milk, bouillon cubes and margarine.
Mix sour cream with flour until smooth.
Add to soup and cook, stirring constantly, until thickened and bouillon cubes are dissolved.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: lasagna #1
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Simmer in Ragu sauce for 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Cook noodles in salted water until tender.
Rinse in cool water.
In a 13 x 9-inch pan, place layer of noodles, then meat and sauce, then cheeses.
Continue layers until pan is full or ingredients are used up. Bake in a 350° oven until browning and bubbly, approximately 30 minutes.

title: savory chuck roast
directions: In bowl, combine flour, brown sugar, salt, pepper and dry mustard.
Stir in catsup, water, Worcestershire sauce and vinegar. Place roast in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Pour catsup mixture over roast.
Cook covered at medium (350°) oven for 45 minutes. Give dish half a turn.
Add onion and green pepper, cover and cook for 30 to 45 minutes longer or until tender, turning dish halfway once.
Skim fat from pan juices and serve with roast.
Serves 6.

title: overnight dinner rolls
directions: Mix yeast and warm water.
Add eggs, sugar, warm water, oil, salt and flour.
Cover overnight.
Next morning divide into 3 sections and roll in circles.
Cut like pie into 8ths.
Roll into crescent shape.
Raise on greased cookie sheet until church is out.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine instant pudding and 1 1/2 cups of milk.
Follow box directions.
Add condensed milk and Cool Whip to pudding.
Layer vanilla wafers, sliced bananas and pudding mixture.
Refrigerate. This makes a large pudding.

title: pizza fundue
directions: Mix sauce and cheese in saucepan; heat over medium heat, stirring frequently.
Cut muffins or bread into cubes.
Dip cubes into heated sauce and eat.

title: taffy crunch corn
directions: Measure popcorn in large pan.
In saucepan, melt margarine. Stir in brown sugar, syrups and vanilla.
Bring to boil and boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Pour over corn.
Bake at 250° in 2 large baking pans for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and stir. Repeat 3 more times or until crisp.

title: black forest cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, combine flour, sugar, cocoa and salt; mix well.
Add egg and margarine; mix well.
Spread into lightly greased 9-inch square baking pan.
Top evenly with cherries.
In bowl, combine 1 cup coconut and 3/4 cup condensed milk.
Spread over cherries.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until coconut is lightly browned.

title: german pancakes
directions: Beat egg.
Mix flour and sugar with egg.
Add salt and milk and mix well.
Pour mixture in hot skillet with small amount of melted butter or margarine.
Flip pancake when top appears dry. Remove from skillet when browned.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar mixture and enjoy.

title: chocolate roll
directions: Place mashed potatoes in a bowl with sugar, coconut and vanilla.
Stir until well blended; will be stiff.
Shape into a roll of 2 inches round.
Spread melted chocolate over roll. Chill; slice thin.
Makes 3 dozen pieces.

title: sweet and sour spareribs
directions: Marinate ribs in 2 tablespoons soy sauce, 1 tablespoon brown sugar, salt, cornstarch, ginger and 1 tablespoon soy sauce.
Let stand 10 to 15 minutes.
Brown ribs.
Remove excess fat.
Add vinegar, water and 3 tablespoons brown sugar.
Cover pan.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer slowly until tender, about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix together graham cracker crumbs and margarine; firmly press into bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
In large mixing bowl, mix together butter, powdered sugar and eggs.
Mix 15 minutes.
Spread mixture over graham cracker crumbs.
Place sliced bananas over mixture; spread pineapple over bananas, then spread Cool Whip over that. Top with nuts and cherries.
Refrigerate overnight.
Cut into squares.

title: san antonio style chicken wings
directions: Cut wings in half at joints; discard wing tops.
Combine 1/3 cup of picante sauce, catsup, honey and cumin.
Pour over chicken. Place in refrigerator; marinate at least 1 hour, turning once. Drain chicken, reserving marinade.
Place on rack or foil-lined broiler pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Brush chicken with reserved marinade.
Turn and bake, brushing generously with marinade every 10 minutes, until tender, about 30 minutes.
Place 6 inches from heat in preheated broiler.
Broil 2 to 3 minutes or until sauce looks dry.
Spoon sour cream into small clear glass bowl.
Top with remaining 2/3 cup picante sauce.
Serve with chicken.
Makes 24 appetizers.

title: ice cream
directions: Mix and freeze in an electric ice cream freezer. Add regular milk if recipe does not fill to the fill line on freezer canister.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Break bread in small pieces.
Mix all ingredients together. Put in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: the dish
directions: Brown sausage and drain grease.
In buttered casserole, place potatoes, onion and season with salt and pepper. Add corn, then soup.
Place meat on top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: potato puff balls
directions: Blend potatoes, egg yolks, parsley, onion, salt and pepper. Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Fold into potato mixture. Spoon into 12 well-greased muffin tins.
Brush top with melted butter.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes until golden brown.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant into small bite size pieces (this should take about 2 months).
Add enough brown gravy to cover.
Cook over fire about 4 weeks at 365°.
This will serve 3,000 people.
If more are expected, 2 rabbits may be added, but do this only if necessary as most people do not like to find hare in their stew.

title: spiced carrot strips
directions: Cut carrots into julienne strips, place in saucepan and cover with water.
Cook until tender, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Drain. Combine butter, sugar, salt and cinnamon; pour over carrots and toss to coat.
Serve immediately.
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix ingredients, saving eggs and milk to be stirred in last. Preheat oven to 400° if baking cornsticks or muffins or 375° if pan baking.
Bake until lightly browned.
(Best if baked in iron skillet.)

title: spicy fire-house chili(8 to 10 servings)
directions: Cook both ground and diced beef in a 5-quart saucepan, stirring often until meat browns lightly.
Drain excess fat.
Add onions, pepper, garlic, chili powder and chili peppers with liquid.
Cook until onions are soft.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, water and Worcestershire sauce.
Reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes.
Add kidney beans and heat 10 minutes more.

title: peanut butter coffee cake
directions: Mix 1/2 cup brown sugar, flour, 1/4 cup peanut butter and butter together until crumbly.
Set aside.
Cream remaining 1/2 cup peanut butter and shortening together.
Beat in rest of brown sugar.
Add eggs in one at a time and beat until fluffy.
Stir together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add alternately with milk to cream mixture.
Beat after each addition.
Spread in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Top with crumbly mixture.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind oranges and cranberries.
Add nuts, celery and sugar. Add 2 cups hot water to dissolve jello.
Add remaining 2 cups cold water.
When jello begins to thicken, add cranberry mixture. Chill until firm.

title: jello pudding pecan pie
directions: Blend pie filling with syrup.
Gradually stir in milk and egg. Then add pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until top is firm and just begins to crack.
Cool at least 3 hours.
Garnish with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: party chicken
directions: Boil the chicken breasts until tender; cool and bone.
Mix chicken soup, mayonnaise, onion and lemon juice; spread over chicken.
Sprinkle with almonds and potato chips.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: pecan teasers
directions: Cook
bacon until crisp; drain and crumble.
Blend with other ingredients,
except
bread.
Remove crusts from bread. Cut each slice into four squares and spread mixture on top of each square. Bake at 350° until lighter brown.

title: cheese cake bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease (using margarine) a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
In a medium bowl, combine flour, walnuts, brown sugar and salt.
Pour in melted butter or margarine and toss with fork. Pat into prepared pan.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: coconut bonbons
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into balls. Chill for 1 hour, then dip in melted chocolate for an added treat.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter together.
Add applesauce, jam and vanilla.
Combine dry ingredients; mix with raisins and nuts. Combine with first ingredients.
Cook in tube pan at 300° for 2 hours.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash and onion until tender.
Drain and mash.
Melt 1/4 stick margarine in casserole and line with bread crumbs.
Combine all ingredients using more bread crumbs.
Sprinkle a few bread crumbs on top.
Put in a hot oven for a short time.
Very flexible recipe.
You can use 2 to 4 cups squash to same quantity of other ingredients.
Freezes well.

title: bavarian cream
directions: Mix gelatine, 1/4 cup of sugar and salt thoroughly in top of double boiler.
Beat egg yolks and milk together.
Cook over boiling water, stirring constantly until gelatine is dissolved, about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.
Beat egg whites until stiff in remaining 1/4 cup of sugar.
Fold gelatine mixture into stiffly beaten egg whites.
Fold whipped cream into gelatine mixture.
Turn into molds.
Unmold on serving platter and garnish.
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: frozen cherry salad
directions: Mix and freeze in a 9 x 13-inch container.
May also be frozen in paper liners in cupcake pan.

title: homemade yeast rolls
directions: In first bowl, mix boiling water, shortening and salt.
In second bowl, mix cold water, sugar and eggs.
In third bowl, dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Mix all three bowls together and add flour until it makes stiff dough.
Spread oil on top of the dough to keep soft.
Cover bowl with wet towel and let rise overnight.
Roll dough and cut out.
Let rise for 2 hours.
Bake at 400° until done.

title: good morning grits
directions: Cook grits according to package directions. Add butter and shredded cheese, stirring until cheese melts. Spoon into serving dish and garnish with cheese cut outs and parsley sprig.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Mix and add crumb mixture for top (if desired).
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: shoe peg corn casserole
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients.
Place in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Top with cracker crumbs.
Drizzle with melted margarine.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: "mexican dip"
directions: Mix together and bake for 20 minutes in 325° oven.

title: low-sugar strawberry pie
directions: Place oats in blender; blend 1 minute until ground.
In bowl, stir oats, flour, sugar and salt.
Combine milk and oil.
Add to flour mixture; stir until moistened.
Form into ball; place ball between 2 squares of wax paper. Roll out; peel off top paper and fit into 9-inch pie pan.
Remove paper.
Prick bottom and sides. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes; cool.

title: garlic crackers
directions: In small bowl, combine all ingredients except crackers.
Pour over crackers; stir occasionally until oil soaks in.

title: nana's christmas salad
directions: 1st Layer:
Mix jello as directed on box.
Add pineapple (drain juice and set aside).
Add bananas (sliced) and marshmallows.
Mix all together and let set.

title: abbott family pickles
directions: Wash and cut cucumbers into sticks, enough to fill 6 pint jars.
Pour boiling water over them and let stand 4 to 5 hours. Drain and pack solidly in jars.
Boil solution of remaining ingredients.
Boil 5 minutes.
Pour hot over cucumbers in jars. Place covers on jars and process 5 minutes in boiling water.

title: pear salad
directions: Heat juice of pears and pineapple.
Add lemon juice and sugar.
Add Knox gelatine that has been dissolved in 1/4 cup cold water.
Cut up pears; add pineapple and chill in 13 x 9 x 2 pan.

title: potato soup
directions: Cover potatoes, carrot and onion with enough water to cover well.
Add bouillon cubes and cook about 10 minutes or until done. Do not drain.

title: snowball cake
directions: Dissolve jello in 4 tablespoons cold water.
Add a cup of boiling water; let cool.
Add pineapple, sugar, juice and salt. Put in the refrigerator until cold.
Add 1/2 cup of Cool Whip and pinch off brown crust of cake and break into bite-sized pieces. Line long pan or dish with cake pieces.
Pour 1/2 of mixture over first layer.
Make another layer and pour rest of mixture over cake.
Pour the remaining Cool Whip over the cake.
Sprinkle with coconut.

title: lush lime cooler
directions: Blend sherbet, limeade and vanilla ice cream until smooth, about 1 1/2 minutes.
Add milk; blend 30 seconds.
Pour into chilled glasses.
Top each with scoop of sherbet or vanilla. Serve immediately.
Yield:
5 cups.

title: oven stew
directions: Place in roasting pan, meat first.
Add other ingredients as listed.
Cover and bake in 325° oven for 3 to 4 hours.
Can also be prepared in a crock-pot.

title: squash pickles
directions: Combine all ingredients, except squash.
Bring to boil.
Add squash and bring to full boil.
Put in hot sterilized jars and seal.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes in casserole dish. Serve with savory crackers or small rye bread rounds.

title: five hour stew
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a roaster.
Cover.
Cook for 5 hours at 250°.
Never lift lid.

title: linda anne's fruit salad
directions: *Bananas, apples (green), grapes, strawberries, etc. may be used.

title: spiced pears, peaches and apples
directions: Combine sugar, water, vinegar, cinnamon and whole cloves. Heat to boiling.
Into syrup, drop enough fruit to fill one jar. Cook covered just until tender.
Pack in hot sterilized jar; add hot syrup to 1/2-inch from top.
Seal.
Makes enough syrup for 6 pints.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger with chopped onion; drain.
Pour into Prego sauce and mix.
Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Pour a little bit of sauce in baking dish.
Layer noodles and sauce, ending with sauce.
Top with Cheddar cheese, then Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Do not uncover for 15 minutes after taking out of oven!!!

title: bama baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour in casserole and top with bacon.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: Make a dark brown roux with flour and oil.
Add onions, bell pepper and celery.
Remove from heat and stir for 5 minutes. Bring chicken stock to a boil and add roux; stir for 5 minutes. Melt butter and add crawfish, fat, seasonings and green onions. Saute 3 minutes.
Add roux to mixture and cook 20 minutes.
Top with parsley.
Serve over rice.

title: lady lux cookie
directions: Will need dowels to wrap around dough.

title: buttermilk chess pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add flour, eggs, vanilla and salt; beat well.
Then add buttermilk.
Pour in pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Let set for at least 10 minutes before cutting.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Cook soup and cheese in a saucepan (very low heat) until all melted and blended.
Add butter to soup mixture after melted.
Add onion to broth and simmer while cheese and soup are melting.
Line bottom of casserole dish with layer of cut tortillas, next chicken, finally soup.
Repeat layers once more.
You can put tortillas on top for last layer and use grated cheese.
Cook in oven at 350° for 30 minutes until bubbly.

title: chocolate fudge frosting
directions: Melt oleo; add cocoa until boiling.
Put in bowl and alternate sugar and milk, beating constantly.
Frost cooled cake immediately.
The icing hardens fast so you need to work quickly.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt margarine, chocolate chips and peanut butter.
Add corn and rice cereal.
Mix well.
Then coat mixture with powdered sugar.

title: baked chicken and cheese
directions: Layer in baking dish: chicken breasts, sliced cheese, croutons (mixed with butter), soup mixture on top.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° until done, approximately 25 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon in small bowl.
Cut each biscuit into quarters and roll in sugar mixture.
Drop into Bundt pan until pan is full.
Melt butter and pour evenly over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Drop out of pan on serving dish and serve warm. Do not cut; serve by pulling apart pieces.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain and marinate at least overnight in Italian dressing.
Add vegetables and cheese.
Mix with sour cream and seasonings to taste. Refrigerate.
Keeps well up to week or 10 days.
Flavor improves with age.

title: sea scallops with cucumber and tarragon
directions: Dissolve
sugar
and cornstarch in water and set aside. Heat a
wok
over
high
heat.
Pour
in 2 tablespoons of oil around rim.
Stir-fry
the
scallops for 1 minute, adding the vermouth and salt.
Then transfer to a dish.
Add the remaining
oil and heat it.
Add the scallions, cucumbers and tarragon
and
stir-fry them
2 to 3 minutes.
Return the scallops with
their liquid to the wok.
Add the water-sugar-cornstarch mixture.
Stir everything
together
for
seconds
or so, adjusting seasoning to taste.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: meal-in-a-frypan
directions: Brown beef in hot shortening in electric skillet set at 380°. Stir in onion, tomatoes, beans and seasonings.
Cover, reduce heat to 300°; simmer for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally to prevent scorching.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, sugar and baking powder; set aside.
Beat eggs until thick and lemon colored.
Fold in flour mixture.
Add vanilla.
Beat heavy cream until stiff.
Fold into batter.
Bake 1 hour in a greased Bundt pan.

title: chili
directions: Melt fat.
Brown onion lightly.
Add ground beef; cook until moisture is absorbed.
Add remaining ingredients; bring to a boil. Simmer 30 to 40 minutes.
Remove garlic.

title: 3 bean salad(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Combine together all ingredients and let marinate overnight.

title: chicken artichoke spread
directions: Mix well.
bake in buttered baking dish for 20 minutes at 350°
Spread warm on crackers.

title: sour cherry salad
directions: Drain cherries; measure liquid and add water to make 2 cups. Bring to a boil.
Put Jell-O into a 2-quart bowl.
Add sugar. Pour boiling liquid over Jell-O to dissolve.
Refrigerate until consistency of egg whites.
Fold in cherries, nuts and celery. Pour into mold.

title: broccoli with cavatelli
directions: Boil broccoli (section off stems) in salted water in large pot.
Cook.
Shut heat off and put aside.
Save water.

title: popeye's biscuits
directions: Mix biscuit mix, 7-up and sour cream thoroughly.
Knead slightly, roll out and cut.
Coat pan with butter, then coat biscuits.
Bake at 350 degrees about 15 minutes.

title: buffalo wings
directions: Place chicken in large, flat casserole dish. Bake 1 hour at 350° or until chicken is golden brown.
Halfway through cooking time, turn and drain the chicken.
When chicken is golden brown, pour hot sauce over chicken. Bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: beef and cabbage
directions: In a large Dutch oven, saute beef, onions and celery until meat is no longer pink and vegetables are tender-crisp.
Stir frequently to crumble meat.
Arrange cabbage wedges on top of meat mixture.
Blend tomato sauce and seasonings.
Pour over cabbage. Cover, reduce heat and cook over low heat for 45 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese.
Serve over beds of cooked rice.
Serves 4 well.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients 3 minutes.
Put chocolate chips in blender.
Pour in hot mixture, blend 6 seconds.
Add eggs and blend 1 minute.
Fold in whipped cream or Cool Whip.
Serves 10. Can freeze.

title: grandmother's cornbread
directions: Beat egg.
Add buttermilk, stir and add meal.
Stir.
Rub 2 tablespoons of shortening in pan.
Let it get hot before putting bread mixture in.
Cook at 450° until golden brown.

title: batter dipped shrimp
directions: Mix all together.
Dip shrimp in flour, then in dip, then in flour.
Fry until brown.

title: chess cake "lemon bars"
directions: Combine margarine and cake mix.
Add 1 egg (beaten) and mix well.
Put mixture into a large oblong pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: pasta vegetable salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Heat at 350° for 40 minutes until hot.

title: teriyaki sauce
directions: In a pan, blend together the cornstarch, soy sauce, sugar, garlic and fresh or ground ginger. Stir in wine, if used, and the beef broth. Cook, stirring until thickened. Makes about 2 1/2 cups.

title: rolled oatmeal cookies(from inga's article on cookcars)
directions: You need a medium stiff batter.
Roll and bake.
It was all guess work.
There was no temperature setting.
The rolling pin was a great big log, real heavy, and the cookie cutter was a saucer.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, sugar and melted butter; press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: beer chicken
directions: Season chicken.
Brown pieces.
Put into covered casserole. Mix in soup, mushrooms, beer, soy sauce, Worcestershire and almonds.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or in microwave until sauce is bubbly.
Cook wild rice.
Add green onions and water chestnuts. Serve sauce over rice.

title: barbecue biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In mixing bowl, combine chili sauce, milk, parsley, Worcestershire sauce and onion.
Let stand 5 minutes. Stir in Bisquick to make soft dough.
Form dough in ball on floured surface.
Knead 5 times.
Roll to 1/2-inch thickness. Cut into 2-inch rounds. Bake on ungreased baking sheet at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 10 to 12 biscuits.

title: lentil soup
directions: Wash and pick over lentils; place in large pot.
Cover with water; boil 2 minutes.
Drain, rinse and return to pot.
Add 4 cups water and chicken broth or stock.
Boil.
Add chicken, carrots, celery, onion, garlic and bay leaves.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Add tomatoes, oil, basil, parsley and fresh ground pepper to taste. Boil; reduce heat to low, partially covering pot.
Simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.
Remove bay leaves.
Add vinegar.
Serves 8.

title: lost bread
directions: Beat eggs, cinnamon and sugar together.
Dip bread in mixture and fry on buttered griddle.

title: dill pickles
directions: Put 1 to 3 slices of onions in bottom of quart jar, 1 flower and/or stems of dill in bottom.
Cut cucumbers lengthwise and pack in jar on end.
Put 1 to 2 slices onion on top of jar.
Put 1 piece dill on top of jar.

title: russian tea cakes
directions: Mix thoroughly the butter, sugar and vanilla. Work in flour, salt and nuts until dough holds together. Shape dough into 1 inch balls. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10-12 minutes at 400° or until set but not brown. While warm, roll in confectioners sugar. Cool. Roll in sugar again. Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: date-nut balls
directions: Cook dates, sugar and margarine until margarine is absorbed (not long), stirring constantly.
Pour hot mixture over Rice Krispies, mixing well.
Form into small balls about the size of a marble.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Makes about 4 dozen.
These hold together better if done quickly while warm.

title: pumpkin crunch cream pie
directions: Pour milk into mixing bowl.
Add pudding mix.
Beat with wire whisk until well blended (about 1 minute).
Let stand about 5 minutes.
Blend in pumpkin, spice, chocolate chips and 2 cups Cool Whip.
Spoon into pie crust.
Chill 4 hours.
Before serving, garnish with remaining Cool Whip and chocolate chips.
This is best served cold.

title: baked fish
directions: Preheat oven to 350° to 375°.
Place fish in baking dish and pour salad dressing over it.
Sprinkle crushed chips and cheese generously on top.
Bake, uncovered, for 25 minutes.
(Delicious.)

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix all together and freeze overnight.
Crunch and serve crunchy.

title: marinated slaw
directions: Mix together.
Refrigerate.
It will keep in refrigerator for up to two weeks, tightly sealed.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: *Can use self-rising flour and omit baking powder and salt.

title: key lime chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Place ingredients except chicken in food processor or blender.
Cover and process until ingredients are combined.
By hand, blend well.

title: hot chili
directions: Sort and wash beans. Put in Dutch oven.
Cover with water and bring to a boil.
Cover and cook 2 minutes.
Remove from heat. Let stand 1 hour.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 hour or until tender.
Drain beans and set aside.
Combine ground beef, onion, garlic and jalapeno in large Dutch oven.
Cook over medium heat, stirring to crumble meat, until meat is browned.
Drain off drippings.
Add beans and remaining ingredients.
Stir well. Cover and simmer 1 hour.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: easy tamale pie
directions: Combine ground beef, 1/2 cup chopped onion, salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Brown in oil.
Spoon mixture into a medium-size casserole.
Saute 1/4 cup chopped onion and garlic in remaining oil until onion is golden.
Add salt, chili powder, paprika, oregano, 1/4 teaspoon pepper, tomato sauce and drained kidney beans.
Mix thoroughly and spoon over meat mixture.
Combine crushed corn chips and grated cheese; sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: In a mixing bowl, stir together powdered sugar, creamy peanut butter and butter until well combined.
Shape candy into 1-inch balls.
Place the balls on a baking sheet lined with waxed paper. Let the balls stand about 20 minutes or until dry.
Melt the dipping chocolate or coating.
Dip the balls into the melted chocolate.
Let stand until dry.
Store tightly covered in a cool, dry place.
Makes about 30 balls.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat butter, eggs, sugar, salt and syrup together.
Pour pecans in pie shell and pour syrup mixture on top of them.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes, until filling is set.

title: green salad
directions: Mix ingredients except nuts.
Works well in rectangular pan. Top with nuts.
Chill.

title: apple berry salsa and cinnamon chips
directions: Peel, core and slice apples. Coarsely chop apples. Dice strawberries and kiwi. Place fruit in a small bowl. Zest orange to measure 1 teaspoon zest. Juice orange to measure 2 tablespoons juice. Add orange zest, juice, brown sugar and jelly to fruit mixture. Mix gently. Refrigerate until ready to serve. Spoon into serving bowl. Serve with Baked Cinnamon Chips.

title: twinkie delight
directions: Layer all ingredients in Pyrex pan 13-inches long as listed. After Cool
Whip is put on top, sprinkle chopped pecans on top and refrigerate.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Shell eggs and cut in halves.
Put yolks in a bowl and other ingredients.
Mix well and spoon into eggs.
Garnish with paprika.

title: instant hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix in large airtight container. Fill cup to your taste and add hot water.
Add as much chocolate as desired.
Stores all winter.

title: scalloped cabbage
directions: Boil cabbage until tender in water.
While hot drain water and keep to put back into mixture if needed.
With fork work butter into hot cabbage, chopped to a fine texture.
Crumble crackers to fine crumbs.

title: orange no-bake cookie
directions: Mix together in bowl.
Shape into small balls and roll in coconut (small Angel Flake).
Put on wax paper and let set up overnight before storing.
Can be frozen.

title: peanut butter quickies
directions: Combine sugar, flour, salt, milk and margarine in saucepan. Bring to a boil and boil for 3 minutes. Add the rest and mix well. Drop teaspoon size pieces onto wax paper and refrigerate overnight.

title: punch concentrate
directions: Bring to a boil the sugar and water; let cool.
Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Mix all ingredients together; freeze in 3 pints. To each pint, add 1 bottle ginger ale or Sprite.

title: dumplings
directions: Sift flour and salt together; mix in shortening.
Add egg and enough milk to make a soft dough.
Roll out on floured board until thin.
Cut into 1-inch wide by 3-inch long strips.
Drop into 1 quart or more of boiling chicken broth in crisscross pattern. Cook 20 minutes with lid off.
When dumplings are cooked, add 1 tablespoon butter and more milk if desired.
Do not stir.

title: shark swim
directions: Chop up tomatoes and simmer the whole shebang, except the fish. Simmer about 20 minutes to cook vegetables, then add the shark and simmer another 10 minutes to cook it through.

title: low-fat pumpkin bars or bread
directions: In large mixer bowl, beat together pumpkin, sugar, oil and yogurt.
In a medium bowl, combine the flours, baking powder, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add to pumpkin mixture, stirring just until combined.
Stir in the raisins.

title: ham loaf
directions: Bake at 350° for 3 hours.

title: zucchini supreme
directions: Combine all ingredients in a casserole or 9x9 pan except last 1/2 cup Ritz cracker crumbs and grated cheese, adding the eggs last.

title: manicotti
directions: Whisk together eggs and milk.
Add flour and continue to whisk until all of the lumps are gone.
Heat a lightly oiled skillet to medium heat.
Spread 2 tablespoons of mixture on hot skillet like a very thin pancake.
Cook each side until lightly brown. Place crepe on a dish.
Repeat process until all of the batter is done.
Place a piece of wax paper between each crepe. Wrap crepes in foil and set aside.

title: oyster stew
directions: Heat milk with cream in a medium-size saucepan over low heat until bubbles appear around edge (do not boil); stir in salt and paprika.
Heat oysters and juice in butter in a medium-size saucepan until oyster edges begin to curl.
Stir in scalded milk mixture.
Ladle into soup bowls or mugs.

title: my mother's brown sugar cookies
directions: Cream lard and sugar; add eggs, buttermilk and soda.
Sift in flour, baking powder and salt.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet. Bake for 10 minutes at 400°.

title: frijoles rancheros(aka borracho beans)
directions: Boil beans, garlic and salt in water for about 2 hours or until done. Add additional water as needed.

title: mandy's fruit cake(in memory of lee & mandy clemons)
directions: Mix fruit with wine and let stand several hours.
Cream butter and sugar, add egg yolks.
Mix well and add fruit & nuts, mix well.
Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.

title: strawberry bread(2 loaves)
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients; add to the dry ingredients, stirring until well combined.
Spoon mixture into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove from pans and let cool completely on wire racks.

title: homemade picante sauce
directions: You will need seals, lids, jars and gloves.

title: lucile's pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, butter and salt.
Add eggs, then syrup, vanilla and nuts.
Pour in pie shell and bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese, pour into a casserole dish.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350 degrees.
Add cheese and bake 30 minutes longer.

title: banana cake
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and butter.
Then mix in the other ingredients.
Bake at 350° about 40 minutes.

title: quick smoky barbecue sauce
directions: Mix together and seal in jar.
Keep in refrigerator.
Will keep a year.

title: steamed chicken with mushroom sauce
directions: Use skillet with lid.
Wash split chicken breasts thoroughly. Pour olive oil in skillet and make sure bottom is covered with oil by moving oil around skillet.
Let oil get hot, then place chicken breasts in skillet and brown on all sides.
Season with garlic salt and pepper to taste.
Cover skillet and let slow cook on low temperature until chicken is done.
Then prepare soup while chicken is cooking, adding only 1 can water for sauce.
Pour over prepared chicken.

title: curried fruit *
directions: Drain fruit thoroughly.
Arrange peaches, pears and pineapple in flat baking dish.
Place cherries in an attractive pattern. Sprinkle with blanched, slivered almonds all over.
Mix sugar, butter and curry powder.
Sprinkle over fruit.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Combine flour, sugar, cocoa, baking powder, salt and nuts.
Set aside.
Combine oil, eggs and vanilla; add to dry ingredients.
Do not overmix.

title: blueberry-sausage breakfast cake
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, stir together flour, baking powder and baking soda; set aside.
In a large mixer bowl, beat margarine or butter with an electric mixer on medium to high speed until fluffy. Add sugars and beat until combined.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating 1 minute after each addition.
Add flour mixture and sour cream to egg mixture alternately, beating after each addition, just until combined.
Fold in sausage and berries.

title: sparkling golden cooler
directions: Combine sugar and water in saucepan.
Stir over low heat until sugar is dissolved.
Increase heat; bring to boil.
Boil for 3 minutes; cool.
Place orange, lemon and lime juices into blender container with bananas; blend until smooth.
Mix with syrup and pineapple juice.
Freeze in refrigerator trays until firm, about 3 hours.
Scoop frozen crush into large bowl to serve.
Stir in ginger ale.
Serve at once, garnished with fresh strawberries. Yields 20 servings.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Mix gelatin, hot water and juice.
Chill slightly.
Fold in oranges and pineapple.
Congeal.
Top with following:

title: molasses or ginger cookies
directions: Mix well.
Roll in small balls the size of a walnut, then roll in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Saute onion, celery, pepper in butter until tender. Mix in next six ingredients. Make into loaf and bake at 375 degrees one hour or until done.

title: french breakfast puffs
directions: Mix together shortening, sugar and egg.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg.
Stir alternately with milk.
Fill greased muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until light golden brown.

title: raspberry coffee cake
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients until mixture is like fine crumbs. Reserve 1 cup of mixture.
To remaining flour mixture add baking powder, soda, salt, yogurt, vanilla and egg.
Blend well.
Spread batter in 10-inch cake pan, greased and floured.
Carefully spoon jelly over top of cake.
Sprinkle with walnuts.
Sprinkle reserved topping (flour mixture) over nuts.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes or until toothpick in center of cake comes out clean.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix meat, bread crumbs, egg, onion and 1/2 can tomato sauce. Form a loaf.
Place in shallow loaf pan in oven.
Combine 1/2 can tomato sauce, water, mustard, vinegar and brown sugar.
Pour over loaf and bake for 1 1/4 hours at 350°.
Baste occasionally.
Make gravy from drippings.
Serves 6.

title: bacon curls
directions: Trim edges off of bread and cut in half long ways.
Spread cheese spread on bread and roll with bacon.
Secure rolls with a toothpick.
Bake in a double broiler pan for 1 hour on 325 degrees.

title: hot chili and cheese dip
directions: Spread cream cheese in a microwave-safe dish such as a Pyrex pie pan.
Layer chili on top.
(Add chili powder if you like it spicier.)
Heat in oven or microwave.
Cover top with Cheddar or Jack cheese.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Add eggs.
Add syrup, melted butter, vanilla and pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 300° and continue baking for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar until light and fluffy. Beat in egg yolks.
Sift together flour and baking soda; add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in vanilla, coconut and nuts.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold into batter. Turn into 3 greased and floured 9-inch layer pans.
Preheat gas oven to 350°.
Bake 30 minutes or until done.
Fill and frost with icing.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes if skin is tough.
Otherwise, scrub and rinse them.
Cut potatoes in slices but not all the way through.
Use a handle of a spoon to prevent knife from cutting all the way.
Put potatoes in baking dish.
Fan them slightly.
Sprinkle with salt and drizzle with butter; sprinkle with herbs.

title: mexican meat pie
directions: Rub a 9 x 13-inch pan with butter on bottom and sides.
Brown the ground chuck. Add the taco seasoning as directed on package. Layer tortilla shells on bottom.
Put ground chuck on top, then the tomatoes next. Add the cheeses.
Bake, lightly covered, with foil at 350° for 20 minutes.
Uncover and bake 10 more minutes. Let set for a little bit.

title: cheesy appetizer
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Thaw pastry and unfold; place in greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Cook and stir mushrooms, onions and pepper in margarine until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour mixture into pan.
Bake 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Cut into squares.
Makes 24.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar, add egg yolks and sifted dry ingredients, add apples and mix. batter will be stiff. Pour in a 11x14in greased pan.

title: wild rice soup
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Add potato soup, milk, bacon and onion.
Heat through on top of stove or place in crock-pot and simmer 4 hours.
Add sherry, salt and pepper.
Add cheese; heat to melt cheese.
Garnish individual bowls with 1 tablespoon Cheddar, if desired.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix ingredients in a punch bowl with a large block of clear ice to chill.
Juice, if fresh, are not strained, but seeds are removed.
Garnish with slices of fruit, mint sprigs and small amount of maraschino cherries.
Serves 15.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add oil, eggs and pumpkin.
Blend until well mixed.
Divide into 3 parts.
Put in greased and floured coffee cans.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.

title: blueberry torte
directions: Crush crackers into fine crumbs.
Mix in 1/2 cup sugar and melted butter.
Press into bottom of pie pan.
Cream together cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar and eggs.
Pour mixture over crust and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Let cool.
Pour blueberry filling over top and chill.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: family size meat loaf
directions: Wash and chop onion and celery.
Mix all ingredients together until blended well.
Place in a baking dish or pan.
Press together well.
Bake for 1/2 hour at 400°.
Reduce heat to 350°. Bake until done.

title: sauteed oysters
directions: Drain oysters.
Cook on medium heat for 5 to 10 minutes. Drain liquid again.
Then add butter and spices.
Saute for 10 more minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: fresh veggie pizza
directions: Spread rolls flat in a rectangular pan.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and Ranch dressing mix.
Add finely chopped vegetables.
Top with shredded cheese. Slice into squares to serve.

title: poppy seed pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and oleo well.
Add sugar slowly, creaming well. Add 1 egg at a time, beating after each one.
Add 1/2 cup milk. Add flour, remaining milk and poppy seed alternately beating at low speed.
Add salt and flavoring.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours. Ovens may vary, so baking time may vary.
Take from oven.
Let sit on wire rack 5 minutes.
Turn out on cake rack.

title: cowboy beans
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: crawfish casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package instructions.
Saute chopped onion and bell pepper until soft.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes and Pet milk.
Let simmer about 5 minutes.
Add crawfish and simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Mix rice and crawfish mixture and put in casserole dish.
Sprinkle top with shredded Mexican Velveeta.
Cook at 350° for about 15 to 20 minutes or until cheese is melted.
(Good with shrimp, also.)

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Cook almonds over low heat until sugar melts.
Stir constantly, cool and break apart.
Tear all lettuce into bite-sized pieces.
Place greens in plastic bag with celery and green onions.
Add oranges.
Just before serving, add dressing (I use Good Seasons Italian) and shake well to coat.
Add almonds and shake again.

title: chicken & spinach lasagna
directions: Drain spinach again and pat dry on paper towels.
Arrange spinach in bottom of baking dish.
Sprinkle with nutmeg and season to taste.
Arrange diced chicken over the spinach.
Cover with lasagna noodles and spoon the tomato sauce over all.
Bake at 350° until heated throughout.
Serve with salad greens.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix ingredients in 2-quart casserole dish.
Beat egg whites and add to mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: coffee kuchen
directions: Preheat oven to 350° and lightly grease and flour a 9-inch tube pan.
Into a large bowl, sift flour with baking powder, salt, cinnamon, sugars and coffee.
Using pastry blender or 2 knives, cut butter and shortening into flour mixture until it resembles small peas.
Set aside 1 cup for topping.
Combine milk with baking soda and eggs; mix well.
With wooden spoon, stir all at once into flour-fat mixture.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes, or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Let cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and serve warm.

title: tuna crunch casserole
directions: In a one-quart casserole dish, mix ingredients then slice eggs.
