Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top with chips.
Bake 5 minutes longer.

title: saucy chicken and pasta dinner
directions: Heat 1/4 cup margarine in a large skillet on medium-high heat. Cut chicken into 1-inch pieces and add chicken and garlic powder to skillet.
Cook for 4 minutes.

title: clam dip
directions: Cut top off bread.
Spoon out insides.
Mix all other ingredients and put inside bread shell.
Replace the top and wrap in foil.
Bake at 200° for 2 hours.
Serve with bread spooned from the inside of the loaf.

title: seashell macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni; add cheese, cut in small pieces, and add butter, sugar and tomatoes.
Mix well and put in casserole dish and top with cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 400° or until bubbly.
(I use spaghetti sauce.)

title: herb roasted chicken
directions: On wax paper, combine flour, sage and thyme.
Coat chicken with mixture.
In skillet over medium-high heat in margarine, cook chicken until browned on both sides.
Add soup and 1/2 cup water, stirring to loosen browned bits.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4.

title: pudding fruit salad
directions: Whip pineapple juice and pudding mix.
Pour over other ingredients.
Chill overnight or at least 8 hours.

title: fudge
directions: Mix in a heavy 2 quart saucepan, sugar, Pet skimmed milk, marshmallows, butter and salt.
Cook, stirring constantly, over medium heat to a boil. Mixture will be bubbling all over the top. Boil and stir 5 minutes more.
Remove from heat.
Stir in chocolate chips until completely melted.
Add nuts and vanilla. Spread in a buttered 8-inch square pan.
Cool.
Cut into 30 pieces.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix together everything except potatoes and corn flakes.
Add potatoes and mix again.
Top with corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for about an hour.

title: nut roll
directions: Mix all together, reserving 1 cup crushed graham crackers for covering bottom and top of Nut Roll.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Melt caramels with 1/3 cup evaporated milk in a saucepan or microwave.
Mix the oleo, cake mix and rest of milk together. Pour 2/3 of the mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and spread caramel mixture over it.
Roll out rest of the mixture between two sheets of waxed paper and transfer to pan.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes.

title: lady neapolitan
directions: Heat to just melted. Spoon over cake. Chill. Can be made early in the day for p.m. serving.

title: applesauce surprise
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon in applesauce.
Stir in corn flakes. Heat in oven until hot.
When ready to eat, place marshmallows on top until covered.
Set oven on 350°.
Put dish back in until marshmallows melt together.
Quick, easy and very good.

title: marshmallow balls
directions: In saucepan, combine candy, milk and butter.
Cook over medium low heat about 20 to 25 minutes until toffee is melted.
Stir often.
Cool slightly.
Dip marshmallows in toffee mixture.
Roll in cereal.
Dry on wax paper.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: surprise fudge
directions: Put cheese and margarine in glass bowl.
Microwave on High until softened.
Add cocoa, vanilla, xxxx sugar and nuts; mix well.
Pat into a 10 x 15-inch pan.
Chill for 30 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: pecan balls
directions: Cream margarine and 2 tablespoons plus 1 teaspoon sugar well. Add
flour	and pecans.
Roll into small balls and bake 30 to 40 minutes in 300° oven.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: pea salad
directions: Drain peas.
Mix with onion and tomatoes.
Add enough mayonnaise to blend.

title: holiday pumpkin soup(easy and low-fat)
directions: Thoroughly wash and clean 1 pie pumpkin.
Bake pumpkin whole in 325° oven for 2 hours until brown and soft to the touch.
Pick stem off and peel skin away (peels off like paper).
Scoop out seeds.

title: cattie's punch
directions: Chill pineapple juice.
Then put all juices, water and 1/2 gallon of ice cream in a 5-gallon thermos container.
Break up the ice cream and stir well.

title: easy chicken and vegetables in foil
directions: Coat a grill rack with cooking spray.
Preheat the grill. Place each breast into center of an 18 x 12-inch piece of foil. Evenly top with the bell peppers and potatoes.
In small bowl, combine tomato sauce, orange juice, salt, black pepper and red pepper until blended.
Evenly drizzle over the chicken and vegetables.
Bring up 2 long sides of each piece of foil and double fold with a 1-inch wide fold.
Double fold each end to form a packet.
Place packets, seam side up, on the rack and grill for 25 minutes or until vegetables are tender and a thermometer inserted in thickest portion of breast registers 160° and juices run clear.

title: apricot barbecue sauce(for "sasha's favorite meatballs")
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bring to a boil.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine all fruit, except bananas.
Sprinkle dry pudding and Tang over fruit and mix well.
Refrigerate.
When ready to serve, add sliced bananas.

title: best baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a crock-pot.
Cook on low for 4 to 6 hours.

title: steak butter pattie
directions: Mix ingredients together thoroughly.
Roll in wax paper. Freeze.
Use on steak when needed.
Can be cut to appropriate size before freezing if desired.

title: tuna salad
directions: Mix all ingredients; add lettuce last.

title: baked apple pies
directions: Pull biscuits apart and flatten. Put a piece of apple in the biscuit, then fold the biscuit cover. Close edges of biscuit with a fork. Mix 1/4 cup cinnamon and 1/2 cup sugar together. Roll pies in cinnamon and sugar mixture. Melt butter, add 1cup sugar and milk, stir. Put pies in a glass baking pan and pour this mixture over pies. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until brown.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco; add sugar and eggs, beating well.
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with milk; add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into prepared tube pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Combine peanut butter, 3/4 cup margarine and sugar.
Press mixture into 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Melt chocolate morsels with remaining 1/2 cup margarine; pour over mixture in pan. Refrigerate 15 minutes, then cut into bars.
Yield:

title: archibald's polynesian chicken
directions: Combine sauce ingredients and stir over medium heat.
Add chicken breasts.
Cook until sauce thickens.
If chicken is done and sauce isn't thick, cornstarch may be used.

title: forget-it beef stew
directions: Combine all ingredients in a casserole.
Add a slug of soy sauce and Worcestershire sauce.
Bake for 4 hours at 275°.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar and corn syrup.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Next add the roasted peanuts.
Microwave on High 3 to 5 minutes until light brown.
(If raw peanuts are used, add at the beginning of cooking time with the sugar and syrup; also add 1/8 teaspoon of salt.)
Next add the vanilla and butter; cook 1 to 2 minutes.
Next add baking soda; stir until light and foamy.
Pour out on a greased pan.
Refrigerate until firm, 30 minutes to 1 hour.

title: roast chicken legs or wings
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chicken, in saucepan and cook until slightly thickened on top of stove.
Place chicken in roasting pan and baste with sauce.
Roast, uncovered, at 350° for 2 hours, basting and turning occasionally.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook together the first six ingredients.
Remove chicken from broth; skin, bone and cut into chunks.
Heat 2 cups broth and add pearl onions, potatoes and carrots; cook until tender.
Remove vegetables with slotted spoon.
Stir flour and milk into 2 cups broth and bring to boil.
Add cooked vegetables, peas and chicken. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish and cover with pie crusts. Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.
Also freezes well.

title: skillet supper
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions, and set aside. Heat electric skillet to 350° and add ground chuck, onion and pepper.
Cook until meat is brown and vegetables are tender. Drain well.
Spread meat and vegetable mixture evenly in the skillet.
Place egg noodles in center.
Spoon tomato sauce and grated Cheddar cheese on top of mixture.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: spinach cheese rolls
directions: Thaw bread dough following package directions.
Spray 15 muffin cups with nonstick cooking spray; set aside.
Lightly flour a surface and roll out dough to 15 x 9-inch rectangle.
Let dough rest for 5 minutes if it is springy and difficult to roll.
Set up dough so long edge runs parallel to edge of work surface.

title: pudding cones
directions: Mix milk and pudding together in a bowl.
Beat until well blended.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Chill well.
Spoon into ice cream cones and top with nuts or sprinkles.
Now it is ready to eat. Keep any leftovers in the refrigerator.

title: rice krispies treats
directions: Melt margarine in a large pan over medium heat.
Add marshmallows and stir until melted.
Stir in Rice Krispies.
Pour mixture into a well-buttered dish.
Cool completely and cut into squares.

title: strawberry jello delight
directions: Mix jello.
Let stand until it gets thick.
Stir in strawberries.
Mix well, then pour 1/2 in a larger bowl.
Cut cake in half.
Place 1/2 into the biggest bowl.
Cover with 1/2 of the Cool Whip.
Now, place rest of cake on top and pour rest of jello over cake.
Cover with rest of the Cool Whip.
Serves 12 or more.

title: pasta ala toto
directions: Bring all ingredients except capellini to a rapid boil; lower gas and continue to simmer for 45 minutes.
Break capellini; add to boiling ingredients.
Cook another 10 minutes.
Serve immediately.
If desired, flavor with grated cheese.

title: amazing peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix together peanut butter and sugar.
Drop by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes. Should be lightly cracked and brown.
Do not overbake.

title: persimmon cookies
directions: Wash and press fully ripe persimmons through colander.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and pulp.
Add to flour, cinnamon, salt and soda.
Mix well with other ingredients and add nuts.
Drop from teaspoon onto oiled cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned, about 10 minutes.
These can be frozen.

title: five layer dinner
directions: Arrange ingredients in layers in a greased casserole in the order given.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine cooked broccoli, including juice, with rice and mushrooms. Saute onion in margarine.
Add to other ingredients. Combine mushroom soup and cheese in double boiler.
Add garlic salt.
Heat until cheese melts.
Pour this into broccoli mixture and mix.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° until it bubbles.

title: fettucini carbonara
directions: Microwave bacon until crisp; keep to the side.
In frying pan, saute onions in olive oil over medium heat.
Add desired seasonings and garlic.
Add Prosciutto and cook to desired level of crispness.
I usually cook for 1/2 hour and then turn down to low heat.
In a separate pan, fry eggs hard.
Remove and chop; add to onion mixture.
In a bowl, mix cream with Parmesan.
Beat until mixture is of milk shake thickness.

title: molasses sugar cookies(from grandma's molasses)
directions: Mix together shortening, sugar, molasses and egg.
Sift together dry ingredients; blend with shortening mixture.
Roll into balls.
Roll balls in extra sugar.
Place on cookie sheet about 2 inches apart.
Flatten.
Bake about 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.

title: pizza dogs
directions: In a saucepan, combine pizza sauce and pepperoni; heat through.
Stir in the cheese until melted.
Spoon about 2 tablespoons into each bun; top with hot dog.
Serve immediately.

title: pepper steak
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet over medium heat; add steak. Saute until brown.
Add tomatoes, green peppers, mushrooms and onion. Stir in soy sauce, salt, ginger, sugar and pepper.
Cover. Simmer for 30 minutes.
In a small bowl, blend a small amount of pan juices with flour.
Stir into skillet.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Serve over rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together broccoli, cheese, and rice.
Add a can of soup. Bake at 350° until brown on top.

title: tortellini primavera
directions: Cook tortellini as package label directs; drain.
Keep warm.

title: quicker fig preserves
directions: To reduce cooking time, freeze figs (make up preserves when it's cool weather!).
When ready to cook, knock off as much ice from the figs as possible.
Place figs in heavy-bottomed pan and cook very slowly until the figs have begun to melt; increase the temperature gradually until hot.
Add the sugar and cook until as thick as desired, stirring very frequently to prevent scorching. Add the ground ginger, a 1/2 teaspoonful at a time to taste. Bottle in sterilized half-pint jars.
Hot biscuits, here we come!

title: easy rich caramel sauce
directions: Remove label from can; cover the can with warm water and simmer on low heat all day.
(Be sure to keep can covered with the water all the time.)
No, don't punch hole in can.
Very good on Hi Ho crackers, etc.

title: depression soup
directions: Cull and wash beans.
Cover with water and 1 teaspoon salt. Soak 3 hours or overnight.
Drain.
Put beans in heavy pot with 2 quarts water.
Add more as needed.
Add salt pork, sliced sausage or ham pieces.
Season to taste.
Boil slowly about 3 hours or until tender.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat, onions and peppers.
Add mushrooms and olives.
Simmer 45 minutes.
Add salt, pepper and garlic to taste. In large pan, alternate layers of meat mixture, cheese and Ragu. (Save some meat mixture for top layer.)
Put tomato soup on top with meat and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: corn scallop
directions: Add milk to corn.
Add broken up bread.
Bake in 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Top with Ritz cracker crumbs.
Dot with oleo and paprika.
Bake at 300° for 1/2 hour.

title: onion rings
directions: Whip eggs and milk.
Put onions in flour, then dip into egg/milk mixture.
Pour into breading.
Deep fat fry until golden.

title: frankfort cry-baby cookies
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar and eggs.
Add spices and flour alternately with molasses and coffee and vinegar.
Stir in raisins.
Spread this amount in two cookie sheets, with sides, or you may drop the dough by teaspoonful on a greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes.
Frost while warm with 4 cups confectioners sugar thinned with about 1/3 cup coffee.

title: tostado casserole
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add seasoning and 1/2 tomato sauce.
Put in pan (13 x 9-inch).
Combine remaining tomato sauce and beans. Spread over ground beef mix.

title: chocolate mint mousse pie
directions: In heavy saucepan, combine 4 tablespoons sugar, cornstarch and mint morsels.
Gradually stir in milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, over medium heat until mixture boils.
Boil for 1 minute. Transfer to large bowl; cover surface with plastic wrap.
Cool to room temperature.
In bowl, combine heavy cream and 2 tablespoons sugar; beat until stiff.
Beat chocolate mixture; fold in whipped cream.
Spoon into prepared crust.
Chill until firm (2 to 3 hours).

title: vanilla pudding
directions: Mix first three ingredients until well blended. Add milk and beaten egg yolks. Cook until thick. Remove from heat. Add vanilla.

title: congo squares
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Melt margarine and add to sugar.
Mix well and allow to cool.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well, then add dry ingredients and mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Bake in large greased cooking pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake in a 375° oven until set, 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chocolate cake
directions: *May be made with 2 teaspoons instant coffee and 1 cup boiling water.

title: elephant stew
directions: After 60 days required to cut elephant into small cubes, place in 5-ton casserole.
Add enough gravy to cover and cook in 250° oven about 4 weeks.
During final 7 minutes, cook macaroni as directed on box.
Drain; do not chill.
Mix immediately with elephant and serve.

title: he-man spanish rice
directions: Cook first 7 ingredients in skillet until meat is brown, breaking up meat particles as it cooks.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook 30 minutes or until rice is tender. Stir often.

title: josephines out of this world pie
directions: Measure sugar and cornstarch into saucepan and mix well. Add the pineapple with its juice. Mix well so no lumps will form. Stir in pie filling and food coloring. Use a wooden spoon and stir gently to avoid mashing cherries. Cook over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil and thickens. Remove from heat and stir in gelatin. Let cool. When mixture has completely cooled, gently stir in sliced bananas. Spoon into baked and cooled pie shell. Cover with whipped cream and garnish with nuts.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients, then add shortening, sugar, eggs and buttermilk.
In another bowl, mix the 100% Bran and boiling water.
Fold in the All-Bran, then add to the mixture.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.
Can add dry fruit, nuts, etc.
Mix at least one day ahead of use.
Batter keeps 4 weeks in sealed container.

title: strawberry pie filling
directions: Cook first 6 ingredients until clear.
Cool.
Mix with strawberries and pour into a baked pie shell.

title: dump bars
directions: Dump all ingredients in bowl except chocolate chips.
Spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over batter. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
No frosting needed.

title: mama's nut pie(microwave)
directions: Combine sugar, eggs, milk, walnuts and extracts.
Pour into prepared shell.
Heat for 10 minutes, giving dish 1/4 turn every 3 minutes, until center is almost set.
Let stand, covered with wax paper.
Just before serving, top with whipped cream.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Sift first 4 ingredients together.
In large bowl with mixer at medium speed, beat margarine and peanut butter until smooth. Beat in sugars, eggs, then vanilla.
Add flour mixture; beat until well blended.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix 1 stick margarine with crackers and place in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Beat for 15 minutes the eggs, 2 sticks margarine and powdered sugar.
Pour over crackers.
Slice bananas over top. Spread pineapple over top.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nuts and cherries.

title: egg dumplings
directions: Mix together
until sticky, but not as mixed as for bread or rolls.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into boiling chicken broth.
Simmer on very low heat until broth is cooked down.

title: almost potato chips
directions: Wash unpeeled potatoes.
Slice no more than 1/8 inch thick or they won't crisp up.
Dip slices in melted butter and arrange on nonstick or lightly greased jelly roll pan (not baking sheets as butter will run off and go into bottom of oven).
Sprinkle with salt and pepper (if you like).
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve hot.

title: raisin sauce for baked ham
directions: Cook raisins, sugar, water and lemon juice together for 20 minutes. Dissolve flour in 3 tablespoons water; add to boiling mixture. Turn heat lower and cook until clear-looking. Have ham cooked and sliced; arrange in dish. Pour sauce over ham and let cook until well heated.

title: perfect cornbread
directions: Sift flour with sugar, baking powder and salt; stir in cornmeal.
Add eggs, milk and shortening; beat with rotary or electric beater until just smooth (do not overbeat).
Pour into greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: bunny biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Place 5 biscuits on ungreased baking sheet. Cut remaining biscuits in half; lengthen halves to form ears. Press ears to whole biscuit to form bunny's head.
Press in raisin eyes, candied cherry for nose and slivered almonds for whiskers. Bake 8 to 10 minutes until golden brown. Frost ears with premade pink icing. Makes 5 bunnies.

title: christmas fudge sauce
directions: Melt chocolate chips and butter in heavy saucepan. Add powdered sugar and evaporated milk. Cook until thick, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.
Allow sauce to cool slightly.
Pour into small glass jars.
When completely cool, screw on lids.
Label jars and keep refrigerated.
These are good for gifts to special friends.

title: crustless coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
This makes one deep dish pie.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Mix together chicken soup, mushroom soup, black pepper, jalapeno pepper and chili.
Heat.
Add chicken pieces and 1 1/2 cups broth.
Heat.

title: la bruschetta perfecta
directions: Preheat broiler. Spray large skillet with nonstick cooking spray.
Heat over medium heat until hot; add onion. Cook and stir for 5 minutes. Stir in tomato, capers and pepper.
Cook 3 minutes.

title: mushroom stuffed tomatoes
directions: Cut stem end from tomatoes; scoop out pulp.
Turn shells upside down to drain.
Meanwhile, chop pulp fine, measure 1 cup and set aside.
Cook mushrooms in 2 tablespoons butter or margarine until tender.
Combine sour cream and egg yolks.
Add to mushrooms with the tomato pulp; mix well.
Stir in 1/4 cup bread crumbs, salt, pepper and thyme.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens and boils.

title: candied yams
directions: Boil potatoes with skins on until tender.
Let cool, then peel and slice thick and place in greased baking dish in layers.
In a saucepan, mix the water, sugar and flour; let come to a boil. Remove from the heat.
Add margarine and juice of orange.
Grate orange and add, also.
Pour mixture over potatoes.
Add marshmallows; sprinkle with nutmeg.
Place covered dish in a 350° oven for about 1 hour.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Wash and peel potatoes.
Put in cold water while peeling the others.
Grate potatoes very fine; squeeze out moisture.
Mix with eggs, flour, onion, salt and pepper, adding enough flour to make a fairly firm mixture.
Drop by tablespoon into hot fat in a skillet.
Fry until crisp and golden on both sides.
Take out with spatula and drain on absorbent paper.
Serve with applesauce sprinkled with salt.

title: pimiento cheese sandwiches
directions: Mix any amount of pimiento cheese with fresh, pressed garlic and add pecans or walnuts.
Serve on whole wheat bread, sliced.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Place potatoes in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together other ingredients.
Pour over potatoes and marinate overnight in refrigerator.
When ready to bake, sprinkle Cheddar cheese over the top.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Heat remaining ingredients to boiling; pour over chicken.
Bake at 250° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: fire and ice tomatoes
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients and boil rapidly 1 minute.
While hot, pour over tomatoes that are peeled and quartered.
Cut peppers in strips and slice onion.
Chill overnight.
Add cucumber slices before serving.

title: almost snickers
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Spread in 8-inch square glass dish.
Cover and freeze.
Makes 8 servings.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Combine sugar, eggs and shortening and mix well. Add all the spices and salt and mix. Add soda and mix. Add room temperature applesauce and mix. Add flour 1 cup at a time and mix. Add nuts and raisins and mix well. Bake at 350° for 2 hours in a large tube pan.

title: nutty chicken casserole
directions: Cook macaroni until almost tender.
Drain and put into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Scatter over the macaroni in layers the cheese, mushrooms, green peppers, pimento, chicken and
nuts.
Mix soup and broth and pour over entire contents of pan.
Top with crushed cheese crackers and bake until slightly browned and bubbles appear around edges at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: seven-layer cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Melt butter and pour into an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Press graham cracker crumbs into butter; layer nuts, coconut and chips over graham cracker crumbs.
Pour milk over mixture. Bake for 25 minutes.
Cool completely.
Cut into 2-inch squares.

title: toffee crackers
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Cover 14 1/2 x 15 1/2-inch jelly roll pan (with sides) with aluminum foil.
Line bottom pan with saltines (separate if they come in sheets of four).
Melt butter and margarine and add brown sugar.
Bring to boil and boil 3 minutes. Pour over saltines and bake for 5 minutes.
Watch closely so they don't burn during the last minute.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Spread as they melt.
Refrigerate and break into pieces.

title: pineapple-carrot bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients; add other ingredients as given. Line bottom of 2 large loaf pans with waxed paper. Bake 1 hour in 325° oven.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Melt 1/4 cup butter; add sugar and 1 1/2 cups crushed wafers. Press into bottom of 9 x 12-inch cake pan.
Separate egg yolks from whites.
Beat whites until stiff and keep cold until you need them.

title: nanny's dressing
directions: Toast the bread about 1 day ahead so it will be dried good. Break bread into small pieces.
Saute butter, onions, and celery for about 45 minutes or until done.
Add all the ingredients together (you should add enough broth to make soupy).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: bar cheese
directions: Melt over hot water (about 5 minutes).
Stir well to blend. Pour into decorative bowl or jar; chill.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: fluffy peanut butter pie
directions: Soften cream cheese and beat until fluffy.
Beat in peanut butter and powdered sugar.
Add milk.
Mix well and blend in Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Freeze.
To serve, let thaw a bit and serve.

title: buttermilk pepper dressing
directions: Mix ingredients well; refrigerate.
Serve with mixed salad greens.
Makes 1 cup.

title: pineapple pound cake
directions: Cream together Crisco, margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add cake flour and baking powder.
Beat in milk.
Add vanilla and 3/4 cup pineapple with juice.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours in tube pan.

title: green bean and corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except crackers in a baking dish. Sprinkle crackers on top and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: sweet potato pecan pie
directions: Cream together the butter and sugar.
Add mashed potatoes and slightly beaten eggs; mix well, then combine with syrup, milk, salt, vanilla and pecans.
Line pan with pastry, then turn mixture into pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat and continue baking in oven at 325° 35 to 45 minutes longer.

title: four bean salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Chill covered overnight.
Stir again before serving.

title: make ahead mashed potatoes
directions: Combine
all ingredients, mixing well.	Place in casserole. Refrigerate until ready to use.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.
May store in refrigerator for a week.

title: rhubarb cream pie
directions: Stir all together and pour in unbaked pie shell.
Dot with butter and cinnamon.

title: ruth's stuffing
directions: In large bowl, mix bread and cornbread. Saute celery, onion and mushrooms in butter. Add to bread. Add chopped eggs. Stir in broth until consistency you like. Don't make too dry. Pour into Pyrex dish. Bake at 350° for 10 to 20 minutes. Top with mushrooms or giblets if you prefer.

title: lemon lush
directions: Blend flour and margarine for pie dough.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put nuts on top.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350° and cool.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Mix dry Jell-O with cottage cheese; add drained pineapple. Stir in Mandarin oranges and Cool Whip.

title: mocha coffee mix
directions: Use 3 teaspoons per mug of Mocha Coffee.

title: fat-free fudge
directions: Mix cocoa and sugar together.
Add milk and corn syrup.
Boil this mixture until it comes to the soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and beat until it starts to thicken.
(Do not overbeat.)
Stir in vanilla.
Spray a 9-inch baking dish with nonfat cooking spray. Pour fudge into dish and let it harden.

title: cheesy buttons
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix biscuit mix and butter.
Stir in water and sesame seed until dough forms a ball.
Drop by scant teaspoonfuls into cheese.
(Shape into ovals, if desired.)
Coat with cheese.
Place 1-inch apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake until golden, 7 to 10 minutes.
Serve warm.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bring to boil.
Great for pork, beef or deer roast.

title: peter paul mounds cake
directions: Bake cake mix as directed on box.
Combine sugar, marshmallows and coconut.
Heat until melted; pour over warm cake.
Combine remaining ingredients in saucepan.
Cook for 1 minute at a rolling boil.
Beat until creamy.
Pour over cake.

title: pickled okra
directions: Makes enough for 3 quarts and 1 pint.

title: cheese ring
directions: Put cheese, onion, mayonnaise and seasonings into a bowl and mix well.
Shape into a ring on a small platter.
Press nuts into the sides and top of the ring.
Serve with a dish of strawberry preserves in the center of the ring.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix and
pour
into
1	(9-inch) pie shell.
Dot top of apples with
butter.
Top	with pie crust.
Flute edges. Brush top of crust
with evaporated milk and sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar. Bake
at
for 15 minutes.
Then turn down to 350° for 30 minutes.

title: celery seed salad dressing
directions: Mix all with oil and vinegar going in last.
Beat fast 20 minutes.

title: coconut-pineapple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan. Combine flour, baking soda and salt.
In separate bowl, whisk together oil, buttermilk, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in sugar, pineapple and 1 1/2 cups coconut; mix well.
Stir in flour mixture.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake on center oven rack 30 to 35 minutes or until wooden pick inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool in pan on wire rack.
Meanwhile, toast remaining coconut on cookie sheet in oven for 3 to 5 minutes until golden.

title: sabbath brunch casserole
directions: Butter bread.
Cube bread and place in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle cheese, sausage, red pepper and onion in order over the bread in a bowl.
Beat eggs.
Add soup, milk, mustard and pepper.
Pour over bread mixture.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: quick and moist sour bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine flour and sugar.
Add sour cream and beer alternately; mix well.
Pour batter into greased 2-quart baking dish.
Bake 45 minutes.
Brush top with melted butter.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes longer until center tested with toothpick comes out clean.
Cool slightly.
Serve warm.

title: italian cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix together in 1 bowl.
Beat with hand mixer.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until cake tester is dry.

title: pecan pie crust
directions: Combine
flour, pecans, sugar, salt and butter in mixing bowl and
blend well.
Cut in butter with pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse cornmeal.
Beat egg with 2 tablespoons water in small
bowl
or
cup.
Add
to flour mixture and toss lightly with
fork
until just moistened, adding an additional tablespoon of
water
if
necessary;
do not overwork, beat or stir.
Gather into
rough ball, wrap and refrigerate overnight. Lightly grease 2 (8-inch) pie pans.
Divide dough evenly.
Roll each
half
on lightly floured board to thickness of 1/8 inch. Gently and carefully fit into pans, trimming off excess.
Chill 1 hour.

title: grilled top loin steaks
directions: Place steaks on grill over ash-covered coals so they are 2 to 3-inches from coals. Broil at medium temperature. When first sides are browned, turn and season with salt and pepper and finish cooking on second side. Steaks 1-inch thick require about 12 to 15 minutes for rare, 18 to 20 minutes for medium. Steaks cut 1 1/2-inches thick require 22 to 25 minutes for medium. Serve Vegetable Packets with steaks.

title: bread pudding(very very good!)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°; cut bread into 1-inch cubes.
Place on pan and toast in oven 10 minutes.
Remove and drizzle with melted butter.
Lower oven temperature to 350°.
Beat eggs; add sugar and milk; stir.
Add cinnamon and raisins and vanilla.
Pour over bread; let set 10 minutes.
Bake 45 minutes until puffed and golden.

title: mock chicken liver salad
directions: Put all ingredients, except peanut butter, in food chopper and grind fine.
Mix peanut butter with ground ingredients.
Season with salt to taste.
Serve on lettuce leaf.
Garnish with slice of tomato on crisp toast.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix and stir everything together.
Roll into balls.
If you like, put peanuts on top or a peanut inside the candy ball.

title: chris' spiced applesauce
directions: Combine ingredients in a 4-quart saucepan.
Bring to boil. Cover, reduce heat and simmer until apples are tender, about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Combine eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla; mix well.
Combine dry ingredients and add to oil mixture; mix well.
Stir in grated zucchini.
Pour in greased pan (two loaves or Bundt).

title: chicken-n-rice bake
directions: Combine process cheese spread and rice; mix well.
Add chicken, peas and half of onions; mix lightly.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Top with remaining onions.
Continue baking 5 minutes or until onions are lightly browned.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Thaw and squeeze excess water from broccoli.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Pour dressing and mix well.
Marinate at least 2 hours before serving, mixing occasionally.

title: fried turkey breast
directions: Take sliced turkey breast and salt and pepper lightly.
When oil is hot, flour the turkey breast, put in hot oil and fry until done.
Be careful not to overcook.

title: hardees biscuits
directions: First, mix yeast and warm water.
Combine flour with sugar sifted in and soda.
Cut shortening into flour mixture.
Add yeast mixture, then add buttermilk and mix well.
Put in covered bowl; refrigerate overnight.
Next morning, cut out on floured board.
Cook at 450° until golden brown.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Sift flour, soda and spices together.
Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs and beat thoroughly.
Add dry ingredients, applesauce, raisins and nuts in small amounts, beating after each addition.
Bake in a Bundt pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: strawberry and pretzel salad
directions: Mix together pretzels, butter and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Press into 13 x 10-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Mix jello, boiling water and strawberries.
Stir until dissolved.
Place in refrigerator to cool for 30 minutes.
Mix cream cheese and sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread over pretzel mixture.
Pour cooled jello on top and refrigerate.
Let set 4 to 5 hours before serving.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: maids of honor
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add vanilla and dry ingredients.
Mold into small greased tins.
Fill centers with raspberry jam.
Bake in a 400° oven for 10 to 15 minutes. When cooled, top with cream.

title: apricot chicken
directions: Mix jam and dressing in a bowl.
Spread mixture over chicken. Bake at 350° for an hour.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together and shape into balls.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: tomato jelly
directions: Cook for 20 minutes. Take off stove and stir in jello. For yellow tomatoes use lemon jello.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Mix all together; form into 2 balls.
Roll in nuts.
Chill.

title: christmas pudding
directions: Lightly beat the egg.
Add the bread and egg nog; let stand 3 minutes.
Stir together the flour, soda and nutmeg; set aside. Stir into bread mixture the sugar, margarine and rum.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Add flour mixture.
Lightly grease a 6-cup mold (5 inches deep and 7 to 8 inches around; mold has to fit into pan for steaming).
Pour in mixture.
Cover with foil.
Place in pan; add 1 inch of boiling water.
Steam 2 1/2 hours, until wooden pick comes out clean.
Unless you use right away, cool on rack for 10 minutes.
To use later, reheat in microwave.

title: cooked play dough(for kiddies)
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add oil and water.
Cook in a large pan until it pulls away from the sides.
Knead a little.
Knead in powdered tempera and mint extract.
Form into balls and store in plastic bags.
This keeps quite a while.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix and sift flour, spices and soda.
Cream butter or margarine on medium speed.
Add sugar and eggs, one at a time. Add dry ingredients and water alternately.
Chop apples and nuts and fold into mixture.
Stir in ginger (or vanilla).
Pour into greased tube pan lined with wax paper.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or bake in layer pans at 400° for 30 minutes.
Garnish with rosy apple rings.
Serve with whipped cream or lemon sauce.

title: sausage and egg bake
directions: Beat eggs; add milk, cheese, mustard and salt.
Mix sausage and bread cubes and put in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour egg mixture over bread and sausage.
Stir lightly with fork so all is evenly mixed.
Refrigerate for 12 hours.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, until bubbling in middle and fairly firm.
Cover with foil first 30 minutes.

title: chicken bundles
directions: Combine 1/4 cup cereal, 2 tablespoons of the nuts, 3 tablespoons of the margarine and the remaining ingredients, except rolls.
Crush remaining cereal to coarse crumbs and mix with remaining nuts.
Separate rolls into 4 squares (2 triangles each), pressing perforations.
Place 1/3 cup chicken mixture in center of each.
Gather corners together, pinching to seal.
Brush with the remaining margarine.
Roll in nut mixture.
Place on baking sheet. Bake for about 25 minutes, or until browned, in a 350° oven. Serve with white sauce.
Garnish with chives.
Serves 4.
